INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('beau-rivage-restaurant-bar','standard','cmr07ig3d0048q8xdtve4q8ro','Beau Rivage Restaurant & Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Visited Beau Rivage whilst on a recent trip to Thailand. Went there around Mid afternoon, nice and quiet with great views!  Staff were friendly and polite, food was lovely and of course the price was amazing value.  This is located up on a quieter part of the island so if you''re passing definitely recommend stopping."
> **- LJ S (5/5/5)**

> "Stopped off for some snacks and coffee Views are lovely Road intermittently noisy  Would go back for a sunset cocktail"
> **- Coconut Emma (4/5/5)**

> ""
> **- ROBBY - System (Günter Reinhold) (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beau-rivage-restaurant-bar-1.jpg','093 151 2661','37 16 อ่างทอง Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 10:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Friday: Closed","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 9:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifxh0027q8xde6xqk8o6','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.161+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.161+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beau-rivage-restaurant-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beau-rivage-restaurant-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4187721504453875514',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('beauty-club','standard','cmr07ig3f0049q8xdz4rnznol','Beauty Club','## Top Reviews
> "Highly recommend!!  Very very pleased with the treatments I had here!  I messaged the night before to see if they could fit me in for 10am the following morning and was lucky to get an appointment!  The lady who did my nails was lovely and gentle and I am very pleased with my nails!! All of the staff are very skilled and polite and the aesthetic of the place is gorgeous! They offer many different services and the colour range is amazing!!  The prices I paid were 300 acrylic take off 900 biab new set 300 extra for chrome  Highly recommend!"
> **- emily nocera (5/5/5)**

> "So it’s hard to be traveling and find someone to do your lashes, nails hair, etc. If you’re seeing this review…100% drive to this location, I was extremely happy with everything & they do builder gel!!  All my services were amazing! I had a lash refill, a manicure and a spa pedicure, which was fabulous however, I didn’t add toenail polish because I had broken a toenail off and they actually fixed my toenail as well. I will be back before I leave the island"
> **- BROOKE EIXENBERGER (5/5/5)**

> "⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Highly recommend this beauty salon in Samui 🤍  I had hair removal done here — everything was extremely gentle and professional. The treatment room was perfectly clean, sterile, with a very pleasant atmosphere and smell — you immediately feel a high level of care and hygiene.  The procedure was completely painless, done very carefully, and my skin had no irritation at all afterward, which is quite rare for me. They use high-quality materials, and the attention to detail is excellent.  I also had a pedicure and foot spa here — absolutely amazing 🤩 So relaxing and beautifully done.  A strong recommendation. Definitely a place I would come back to ✨"
> **- Katerina Sekerina (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beauty-club-1.jpg','091 099 1990','119 30, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.instagram.com/samui_beautyclub?igsh=MWhuaWxoamVoZjE2MA%3D%3D&utm_source=qr','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.163+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.163+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beauty-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beauty-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=3585115654627572403',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('bedtime-hotel-samui','standard','cmr07ig3h004aq8xd38hsjcfj','BedTime Hotel Samui','## Top Reviews
> "Booked this hotel for 3 nights during our trip to Koh Samui. The room was perfect for what we needed. Clean and comfortable. The staff were also very friendly. They supplied guests with a complimentary coffee/juice and snacks in the morning which we thought was very kind!  The location was perfect as it was walking distance from most shops/restaurants and Chaweng beach. There was some road noise but this slowed down later at night.  Over all, would highly recommend this hotel."
> **- Rozelda Vdw (5/5/5)**

> "Very disappointing stay at EBS Residence Chaweng. The place is extremely dirty and has a very strong, unpleasant odor throughout the rooms and hallways. The furniture is old and already damaged, yet they require a deposit and try to blame guests for things that were clearly broken before.  The management and staff were also very deceptive. They charged me 500 BHT simply because I checked out at 12:15 instead of exactly 12:00, which felt completely unreasonable. Overall the place feels poorly maintained, unfairly managed, and not a safe or comfortable environment to stay in. I would not recommend staying here."
> **- Paul Levinsky (1/5/5)**

> "Love the decor, service and location of the hotel. The cat branding and lighting is sooo cute.  The only thing is the walls and windows are so thin and you can hear everything outside and next door, when people shower, traffic and I couldn’t sleep till post midnight. Bring ear plugs and it would be a good place"
> **- Wenjie Zhu (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/bedtime-hotel-samui-1.jpg','092 594 6649','155/36-42, Suratthani 84320, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.bedtimesamui.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.165+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.165+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/bedtime-hotel-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/bedtime-hotel-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16729469059162856722',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('belle-and-shine','standard','cmr07ig3k004bq8xd1zuft06r','Belle And Shine','## Top Reviews
> "This shop offers a charming and welcoming atmosphere, with carefully arranged displays showcasing a superb selection of quality jewelry which is rare in Koh Samui The prices are affordable, which makes this store accessible to all budgets. The staff is also very attentive and knowledgeable, always ready to help you. I will Come back !"
> **- Mimi Be (5/5/5)**

> "Jewelry Shop Newly opened in Samui, beautiful, lots of jewelry. The shop is beautifully decorated. There are bags, sunglasses, and dresses that can be worn for every occasion. Very good and not expensive"
> **- Jessadagorn Suwanna (5/5/5)**

> "Look luxury,and cute have so many style for lady , service good"
> **- Sutee Chukhan (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/belle-and-shine-1.jpg',NULL,'162, 51 หมู 2 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://belleandshine.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifs5000eq8xdeu148200','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.168+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.168+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/belle-and-shine-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/belle-and-shine-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4659914371346453244',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('benzo-sushi-bar-grill','standard','cmr07ig3n004cq8xd95tk631q','Benzo Sushi Bar & Grill','## Top Reviews
> "The shop is quite small and doesn’t have air conditioning, but surprisingly it wasn’t too hot. Also appreciated that there were no mosquitoes thanks to the mosquito trap machine — small detail but it made the experience more comfortable.  Food was okay overall. The rolls were reasonably priced and decent, but the sashimi wasn’t as fresh as expected, especially the tuna. Prices felt a little on the higher side, though I guess that’s expected for a tourist area."
> **- Oops i ate it (3/5/5)**

> "I first came here 3 years ago, and I still remember how amazing the sushi was. Since then, I’ve tried sushi in many different countries, but honestly nothing compares to this place. The quality, freshness, flavors, and presentation are all on another level. Every bite tastes perfect. This is easily one of the best sushi restaurants I’ve ever tried, and I’ll definitely keep coming back whenever I can. Highly recommended!"
> **- Shahed Tako (5/5/5)**

> "Three of us went for dinner last night and we really enjoyed ourselves. The service needed to be a little better specially as it’s not a big place but overall good. The food was superb and we will certainly go back, it’s in an easy location to get to and if you are staying on Chweng beach you can walk along the beach to get there. So give it a go"
> **- Goose (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/benzo-sushi-bar-grill-1.jpg','077 901 698','80, 29 Suan Uthit Rd, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://benzo-sushi-bar.com/','["Monday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.171+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.171+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/benzo-sushi-bar-grill-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/benzo-sushi-bar-grill-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9023976065669322915',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('bestway-samui','standard','cmr07ig3p004dq8xd1fg25uhq','Bestway Samui','## Top Reviews
> "We had to go to the Malaysian border for a same-day trip for our visa procedures. We were traveling with our children, aged 3 years and 10 months. From the very beginning, we were warmly welcomed at their office and all our questions were answered. Within a few days, we set off. On Sunday, from 4 a.m. to 8 p.m., we were extremely satisfied with every minute of the service we received. The drivers were very kind and helpful. I sincerely recommend them to everyone. It’s an excellent service"
> **- Nito Filiz (5/5/5)**

> "Excellent service.  I have used this visa service 3 times for tourist visa renewal and Lumpoon is always diligent, dependable and on time."
> **- Tom T (5/5/5)**

> "Me and my mom went for a visa run. The attention and service was great and I recommend!!! The trip itself is tiring bc we chose to do same day, but it was a thing we had to do. Just have that in mind, get comfortable clothes and maybe a pillow to sleep in the mini bus :) It was provided a small breakfast / snack for the road also."
> **- Hilda Amaral (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/bestway-samui-1.jpg','077 903 521','4169 Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'https://bestwaysamui.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifu0000zq8xdvll5tv7z','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.173+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.173+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/bestway-samui-1.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8168711890986566410',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('beyond-samui-resort','standard','cmr07ig3s004eq8xdu36ufv2y','Beyond Samui Resort','## Top Reviews
> "A fantastic, child-friendly hotel with lovely, spacious, and pleasantly clean rooms. Breakfast was delicious with lots of choice 👌 A beautiful, large pool with a stunning sea view. Incredibly friendly and helpful staff who make you feel truly welcome. The massage therapists were also very kind especially to the kids. The location was also perfect for us, on Chaweng Beach and within walking distance of many great restaurants and shops! We had a wonderful time!"
> **- Stefanie Diets -de Roover (5/5/5)**

> "They spoiled our whole staying experience at the checkout. Accusing us of stealing things they never placed in our rooms in the first place, as pity as disposable slippers, and made us pay extra hefty charges for the same. Above all, the staff doesn''t even speak English properly so you can''t even communicate the problem. Its terribly difficult to convey anything to them. Also, while our checkout time was 12pm, their cleaning staff kept entering our rooms without permission since 10am itself. When told to wait, they''ll simply utter "
> **- Shiva Sharma (1/5/5)**

> "Great place to stay and relax, only a 10-15 minute walk into town if required. Rooms are spotless, the cleaning staff do an amazing job. We generally ate at the resort by choice & it was amazing every time, Chef Nugna, Miew & Nong were very accommodating with our dietary restrictions, all the food was very well prepared, presented & extremely tasteful. Wait staff were amazing & very friendly, thanks to Pla, Aor, Lita, Nong, Pueng, Nom & Ng you made our stay most welcoming. Try the massage hut at the back of the resort, they were amazing, never felt so relaxed. The only thing this resort lacks is a beach, but walk a couple of hundred metres & there is plenty of sand to enjoy your day. Highly recommended, give this resort a go."
> **- Michael Acquaviva (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beyond-samui-resort-1.jpg','077 428 888','เลขที่ 20 หมู่ 2 ถนนเฉวง-เชิงมน, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://samui.beyondresort.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsv000nq8xdrwnu123q','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.176+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.176+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beyond-samui-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beyond-samui-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10124005703945454466',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('beyond-the-sea-siamese-brasserie','standard','cmr07ig3w004gq8xd8fg22u4g','Beyond The Sea Siamese Brasserie','## Top Reviews
> "Delightful offerings and views, staff experience was mixed, but overall was very enjoyable, could see going back to spend the afternoon in the resort space."
> **- Asa Trujillo (4/5/5)**

> "We had breakfast. It was decent, but outrageously expensive for Thailand. Pi paid like 24 bucks each person for breakfast.  Quality certainly did not match the price. But that''s a resort for you. Place was gorgeous though. Great view, too."
> **- Roy Shandy (3/5/5)**

> "Gorgeous location, restaurant is part of 5 star hotel. We took a canoe to their private beach and we seen locals catching fresh mussels! When we ordered from the restaurant I was craving seafood! We got the calamari to start, and it was very rubbery! You couldn’t break them, even if you pulled them apart! I ordered a seafood red curry as a main; when the waitress served them to me I asked if the mussels were fresh and she responded saying they were frozen. All the seafood was rubber! Overcooked and very overly priced! They took them off our bill. But I would highly recommend you do not dine here. Beyond the sea? More like beyond the frozen sea."
> **- Jess Cos (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beyond-the-sea-siamese-brasserie-1.jpg','077 913 888','116/1 Moo 2, ตำบล หน้าเมือง Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.9,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig3v004fq8xdw6q7afhh','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.180+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.180+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beyond-the-sea-siamese-brasserie-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/beyond-the-sea-siamese-brasserie-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13169943307079335588',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('big-horn-restaurant','standard','cmr07ig3y004hq8xdoa8f04at','Big Horn Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Big Horn Restaurant was honestly one of the best parts of our Koh Samui trip. We visited 4 times during our 5-day stay, which says everything about how much we loved it.  The food is absolutely amazing — delicious, fresh, beautifully presented, and consistently excellent every single visit. On top of that, the prices are extremely reasonable and truly value for money considering the quality and portion sizes.  What impressed us the most was the service. Every single staff member was warm, attentive, and genuinely cared about the experience. I can’t name just one person because the entire team was outstanding. Their attention to detail and hospitality were exceptional — honestly, even some 5-star hotels fail to provide service at this level.  They have won several awards, and after experiencing this place multiple times, I genuinely feel they deserve every one of them. Highly recommended to anyone visiting Koh Samui."
> **- jyoti soni (5/5/5)**

> "Delicious drinks and food. Highly recommend you visit this restaurant during your stay on Koh Samui island. The tuna steak was incredible and the deep fried bananas and honey were fantastic. All of the staff were so lovely and kind. We also received 2 plates for complimentary watermelon for dessert. :)"
> **- caroline doerksen (5/5/5)**

> "The food was some of the most flavoursome and well presented meals I’ve enjoyed in Thailand. For me the calamari is one of the best in the world prepared fresh by the chef. The restaurant is Thai owned, a refreshing change in Koh Samui where foreign ownership takes the lion share of the tourist market. I enjoyed Penang curry chicken, green papaya salad and the calamari. Fabulous experience, highly recommend"
> **- Happy Happy (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/big-horn-restaurant-1.jpg','099 222 8551','167, BoPhut, 36 Chaweng Beach Rd, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.bighornrestaurantsamui.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 11:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.183+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.183+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/big-horn-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/big-horn-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15835950576201607122',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('black-cat-white-cat','standard','cmr07ig41004iq8xdod7rs3ol','Black Cat & White Cat','## Top Reviews
> "During a visit to Koh Samui in December, I had the pleasure of attending several workshops at **Black Cat White Cat Yoga in Lamai**, and it became one of the highlights of my time on the island.  The studio has a beautiful, calm atmosphere that immediately helps you slow down and settle in. It feels more like a peaceful sanctuary than a typical yoga studio. The space is thoughtfully created, simple and grounding, allowing you to disconnect from the busy energy of the island and reconnect with yourself.  What makes the experience truly special is **Olya**, the founder and teacher. She brings a rare sense of serenity and true beauty to the room. Her presence is calm, attentive and quietly inspiring. She carries a natural beauty and grace that reflects the same balance and mindfulness she teaches. Her guidance throughout the workshops felt gentle, thoughtful and inclusive, making everyone feel welcome regardless of experience.  The workshops themselves go beyond a standard yoga class. They blend movement, breath and moments of reflection in a way that feels both grounding and meaningful. The small group setting also creates a warm sense of connection between participants.  Among the many wellness offerings on Koh Samui, please let yourself experience **Black Cat White Cat Yoga . I highly recommend visiting if you are looking for a thoughtful and inspiring yoga experience on the island.  Jason D - Australia"
> **- Jason Donofrio (5/5/5)**

> "Such a beautiful place to practice, share and connect with the community! Olga you''re an amazing person to help everyone and make magic happen in your "
> **- Tanu Bodhi (5/5/5)**

> "Why do we even travel? Probably, as many reasons, as there are places, people and experiences. And, sometimes, if we’re lucky, we get our answer.  It may reveal itself slowly, of course, in some form …  Cacao, tarot tells, Deep Sound Journey By The Sea, blue skies fade to stars ...  Is that luck? Or is that, when preparation meets opportunity? Does it even matter?  If you do get the chance, I highly recommend joining @yogastudiosamui for a deep sound journey by the sea. Where the vibrations from the gongs and singing bowls blend with the rhythm of the waves. A profoundly calming experience that nurtures body, heart, and mind."
> **- Simon (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/black-cat-white-cat-1.jpg','080 007 1601','133/8 M3, Lamai, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://booking-system.site/tabs/home-tab/organisations/a98b9544-08de-4c10-ee1d-08dd5d6b5725','["Monday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 1:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifuo0015q8xdfahzrsp4','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.185+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.185+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/black-cat-white-cat-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/black-cat-white-cat-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15952787892929357883',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('black-duck-sports-bar','standard','cmr07ig43004jq8xdxx16yqqy','Black Duck Sports Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Unfortunately, a very bad experience. Last night I was at this bar with my girlfriend. Three drunk men (from Austria, France, and Australia) approached our table. At first they started talking, but when my girlfriend was clearly tired, they tried to take her away from the table, despite me clearly stating that she was with me. When I stepped in between them and my partner to protect her, the situation became aggressive. I was provoked and had to push one of them away and use a chair defensively. Only then did they leave. What was most disappointing was the reaction of the staff. The bar staff did absolutely nothing to stop the aggressive and inappropriate behavior of these drunk guests. Instead of ensuring the safety of their customers, they told me to pay the bill and leave, as if I was the problem. I have lived in Thailand for over 10 years and have never experienced anything like this. Guest safety — especially the safety of women — should be a top priority. Sadly, it was not the case here."
> **- Caspa Z (1/5/5)**

> "I had a great time at this bar! The atmosphere is cozy and stylish, the drinks are well-crafted, and the staff is very friendly. Perfect place to relax with friends or enjoy a night out. Highly recommend!"
> **- Алина Базалевская (5/5/5)**

> "Ordered fish, fish was nor cooked. Understand fish should be wet. Have an advanced diploma in hospitality and catering. Beer absolutely flat no bubbles. Mind out people we can''t give a bad review"
> **- Mark Smedley (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/black-duck-sports-bar-1.jpg','093 678 2445','Chumchon Chaweng Yai Soi 4 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 2:00 AM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.187+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.187+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/black-duck-sports-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/black-duck-sports-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10755406823778641360',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('blackjack-bar-hostel','standard','cmr07ig45004kq8xdb6vayl9z','BlackJack Bar & Hostel','## Top Reviews
> "The location is actually decent, right on a street full of clubs/bars and not a long walk to the beach. The rooms are clean, and the bathroom is also alright. However, there is literally no one staying there. On my first night, I was the only one at the hostel, and the other three remaining nights I stayed there, it was just me and one other person. The owners are super weird, often high, and on my first day, a woman came into the dorm room, asking me why I was staying here. Basically, she wanted me to leave until I showed her my booking confirmation and explained (with the help of Google translator) that I had already paid for the room. Totally weird experience, would not stay there again!"
> **- Malena Reder (1/5/5)**

> "I''ll start with the obvious... It''s very central to the nightlife so it is noisy. I thought I was prepared for how noisy it was going to be, having been to this area before, but let me tell you, it is next level noisy. Like ear plugs don''t even work kind of noisy. Until past 6am. Every day. Now if you''re a party animal, this may not phase you and the location will be a real plus. It was simple digs and clean enough (though the blankets were ridiculously small) plus the lady at reception was super friendly. But if you do need your sleep, this may not be the place for you."
> **- Alex Poole (3/5/5)**

> "We were very well looked after. The manager always made sure that we were happy, always topped up our room supplies, and made us feel really welcomed. She was extremely kind and even let us check out later.  The bar/hostels theme is really new and unique. It’s well priced and has a happy hour that lasts for a long time.  I highly recommend the stay here as it’s comfortable, affordable and will soon be quite a popular place."
> **- Kurtis Jenkins (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blackjack-bar-hostel-1.jpg','077 961 986','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.blackjackbarand.thailandhotels.site/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifx90024q8xdg1rcf50m','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.189+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.189+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blackjack-bar-hostel-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blackjack-bar-hostel-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13459301112684051863',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('blackyellow-beach-club','standard','cmr07ig49004lq8xdgqz9gh1u','BlackYellow Beach Club','## Top Reviews
> "We went here 3 days and it was great. Very good service and great food. Papaya sallad, stir fried pork with rice, sir fired chicken with cashew and tempura chicken everything was excellent."
> **- Kim Lifvenborg (5/5/5)**

> "What a lovely bar this is. The food is superb. The service is superb. The price for food and drink is cheap. The views of the beach are stunning. When we return to Koh Samui we will be eating and drinking here again. Thank you to the staff for looking after us."
> **- Rachel Burbidge (5/5/5)**

> "Lovely chilled vibe right on the beach.  Really good thai food at very reasonable prices, friendly happy staff. What a pleasure to spend some time here.  Thank you, Black Yellow Restaurant....you''re doing things really right!"
> **- Wendy Morris (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blackyellow-beach-club-1.jpg',NULL,'F27W+WFP, Maret, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.193+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.193+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blackyellow-beach-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blackyellow-beach-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9467792295743965464',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('blockhouse-hostel','standard','cmr07ig4c004mq8xdfahq142q','Blockhouse Hostel','## Top Reviews
> "Absolutely loved this hostel. Solar is a ray of sunshine (I miss him) so are all the staff and wonderful owners. The owners cats are adorable and were very entertaining.  Food was so yummy, and the common space was perfect for hanging out with other travellers.  I definitely recommend a scooter for this hostel as it’s a bit out of the way and walking into town/the beach you will see some dogs so if you are walking, make sure to go back before sunset. We had some dogs that were not the most friendly chase us. Not the hostels fault at all, just be aware of this if you are on foot.  If I am back in Samui one day I’ll be back at Blockhouse! Thank you for welcoming us. 🇨🇦"
> **- Ella Capri (5/5/5)**

> "I had an amazing stay at Block House ! The accommodation is excellent, very clean, comfortable, well designed, and perfect for a relaxing stay. Everything was exactly as expected (and even better). The managers are truly outstanding, friendly, professional, responsive, and always happy to help. They really care about their guests and make you feel welcome from start to finish. I highly recommend Block House to anyone looking for a great place to stay. Fantastic accommodation and top-quality management 10/10 experience!"
> **- Sacha Mokotowitch (5/5/5)**

> "I was very very pleased to see how welcoming and sharing the entire crew was at this establishment. Sola is incredible, really making sure that his guests are taken care of and informed with how to move and what to do. Elle was great as well, great personality and caring to make sure guests and house are taken care of. There are a couple cats in the property that you will most likely fall in love with and want to take back home! i highly recommend Blockhouse Samui,, i felt at home. it was easy to walk around or arrange transport if needed. the high street is a 5 minute walk away and the beach 4 more after that.. restaurants, markets and shops all around.. I will be back !! Thank you BlockHouse samui!"
> **- Maria | CBD Alchemy (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blockhouse-hostel-1.jpg','083 104 5260','121, M2 Magnum, 8 Soi 3 Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.196+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.196+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blockhouse-hostel-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blockhouse-hostel-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5499148110334581427',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('blue-gems','standard','cmr07ig4e004nq8xdnvmlhiya','Blue Gems','## Top Reviews
> "The Blue Spice is absolutely a must-visit! The food is delicious and always fresh, especially the seafood dishes - they''re amazing. The restaurant is clean with a great ambiance, and the staff are so friendly and attentive. Great value for the quality you get. Perfect spot for family or friends to enjoy a relaxing meal. Will definitely be back again!"
> **- Lwan Eaindra Hset (5/5/5)**

> "The atmosphere here is lovely, on the beach so the view is amazing and you get a great breeze! The service is so friendly and staff are all great! They have live music as well which really added to the experience!"
> **- Ang Groom (4/5/5)**

> "Overpriced & deeply frustrating New Year’s Eve dinner – disappointing food, hidden costs & unbearable noise:  We visited The Blue Spice on Choeng Mon Beach on New Year’s Eve after being convinced by the many 5-star Google reviews. Based on those reviews, we genuinely expected a special beach restaurant with good food and a relaxed atmosphere. Unfortunately, this turned out to be the worst dining experience of our entire 14-day stay in Koh Samui.  Let’s start with the food. The menu is extensive, cocktails, seafood, European dishes, alcohol, everything you could imagine. So in terms of variety, there is little to complain about. However, the quality absolutely does not justify the prices. The most expensive dish we ordered was a steak costing 1,100 THB (around 30 €, close to German prices). It was ordered medium but arrived completely dry, served with only a small amount of pepper sauce, and was barely enjoyable. For that price, this was simply unacceptable. The seafood was decent, but again: not nearly good enough for the prices being charged.  The biggest issue, however, was the lack of transparency and hidden costs. We had reserved a table in advance and even paid a deposit of 4,000 THB, which we were explicitly told would be deducted from the final bill. In the end, we had to pay another 4,000 THB, plus additional charges. Altogether, we ended up paying 21,000 THB for 6 adults and 2 small children (who barely ate anything). There were only two cocktails ordered, nothing extravagant at all.  That comes out to roughly 600 €, which is absolutely outrageous for what we received.  Only after questioning the bill did we learn that an additional 8,000 THB had been charged for a New Year’s Eve show ticket (1,000 THB per person). This was never communicated in advance, not during the reservation, not when paying the deposit, and not when we explicitly asked about costs. We assumed the short shows were part of the restaurant experience, especially given the already very high menu prices.  Yes, there was a fire show (about 12 minutes), a few very short traditional Thai dance performances, and a saxophonist (see photos). The fire show was actually quite good. But honestly, one could have enjoyed the same show simply by sitting on nearby loungers or beach seating without paying this ticket fee at all. Charging 8,000 THB extra for this, without prior notice, feels like nothing but a cash grab.  When we raised these concerns, the restaurant management showed no willingness to compromise, not even a small gesture of goodwill, despite the obvious misunderstanding and the high amount paid.  What truly ruined the evening beyond repair was the extreme noise from the hotel/restaurant directly next door. This was not some distant background music – it was very loud Thai karaoke, with speakers pointed directly toward The Blue Spice. The screaming and distorted singing started before 8:00 pm (when we arrived) and was still blasting at full volume when we left around 10:15 pm. It was impossible to relax, talk, or enjoy any kind of atmosphere.  No matter how much effort The Blue Spice puts into ambience, it is completely pointless if guests have to endure screaming karaoke throughout their dinner, especially at these prices.  Final conclusion: High prices, mediocre food, hidden or poorly communicated extra charges, no flexibility, and an unbearable noise situation. In our personal experience, this felt like a classic tourist trap. Our honest recommendation: skip this place and go to a traditional Thai restaurant instead, you will get better food, better value, and a far more authentic experience."
> **- Smoke (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-gems-1.jpg','+66949511655','24, 37, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://thebluespice.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.198+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.198+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-gems-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-gems-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-gems-3.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-gems-4.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13572649212439563129',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('blue-house-coffee-shop','standard','cmr07ig4j004pq8xdazpcc9i3','Blue House Coffee Shop','## Top Reviews
> "Great roadside coffee shop, very nice if you are going to the waterfalls or if you are going from the west to the east of the island.  Very nice lady owner with affordable prices and delicious coffee !"
> **- Ferhan Serbest (5/5/5)**

> "Delicious coffee, pleasant atmosphere, and a wonderful owner. She showed me a nearby temple and explained interesting details. Thank you for a wonderful time!"
> **- Анна Pup (5/5/5)**

> "A super cute little local café.  The green tea with lemon is absolutely delicious and refreshing!  Highly recommended!"
> **- Charlene Ernst (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-house-coffee-shop-1.jpg','088 788 3524','133 4, Tambon Na Mueang, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 7:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 7:00 AM – 8:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig4i004oq8xdv207xuh2','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.203+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.203+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-house-coffee-shop-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-house-coffee-shop-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13865262615142094525',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('blue-turtle-beach-club','standard','cmr07ig4l004qq8xd3zrpomuv','Blue Turtle Beach Club','## Top Reviews
> "We really enjoyed our stay at Blue Turtle Hotel. The hotel is located near a busy street, however, it was always peaceful and not too loud. The Restaurant/bar area is located right at a beautiful beach, the food and drinks are reasonably priced and good. The rooms are designed very nicely, super clean and we were never missing anything. There is a construction site on the front side of the hotel (they are expanding), but this was declared before arrival and did not affect us, especially because we were out doing activities all day. The receptionist was really friendly and kind. We would be happy to stay at Blue Turtle Hotel again."
> **- Ella L (5/5/5)**

> "It was an absolutely exceptional stay and without hesitation we can say that we have never encountered such a wonderful, friendly, and truly homelike atmosphere anywhere else.  We travel extensively throughout Thailand, and over the past three weeks we visited the islands of Koh Samui, Koh Phangan, and Koh Tao. During this trip, we stayed in 10 different accommodations, yet none of them can compare to this resort in terms of atmosphere, warmth, and genuine care for guests.  From the very first moment, we were welcomed with huge smiles and kindness. The staff are incredibly friendly, helpful, and dedicated. We received assistance at every step—from organizing shopping trips and arranging taxis to treating my brother’s wound. Such care and genuine willingness to help are truly rare.  We would especially like to thank Niki and Eiei for their professionalism, dedication, and constant readiness to assist. Thanks to them, we felt exceptionally well cared for throughout our entire stay. We would also like to express our heartfelt gratitude to Daisy for providing first aid to my brother and for her extraordinary empathy, kindness, and care. Her response and support were invaluable to us. We also thank you Celio for nice welcome and all information about resort and all issues around .  Special recognition also goes to the housekeeping team, who do a fantastic job. Thanks to their dedication, the rooms and villas were always perfectly prepared, spotless, and impeccably maintained. Honestly, throughout our entire journey across Thailand, we did not encounter such a high standard of cleanliness anywhere else.  The cuisine also deserves special praise. The dishes served were absolutely delicious, prepared with great attention to detail, and among the best meals we had during our entire stay in Thailand.  The villas themselves are beautifully crafted and decorated with exceptional taste. Their interiors are unique, modern, and still look brand new. It is clear that every detail has been thoughtfully designed with passion and care.  We would like to thank the entire team for creating a place that people truly want to return to. This is not just a resort—it is a place where you feel as though you are among friends and family. We wholeheartedly recommend this resort to anyone looking not only for a beautiful place to relax, but also for genuine hospitality. We sincerely hope to return again in the future ❤️"
> **- Magdalena Magrejan (5/5/5)**

> "We had the best 4 night stay here! The staff are so kind and friendly. The hotel was immaculate, room was cleaned everyday, offering beach and body towels fresh everyday. They gave reusable water bottles and had a purified water fountain in the restaurant and kitchen which was fab. We also loved that the pool was open 24/7 for a late night dip!  Location: right on Chaweng beach, there are many loungers available (never struggled to get one at any time of the day). Right opposite a 7/11 which is helpful. It’s around a 10 min walk from the main “strip” and livelier part of Chaweng with lots of restaurants, nail salons, massage parlours, bars etc. Nextdoor is a restaurant which is open from breakfast-late, also offering cocktails under a really nice lantern setting.  Highly recommend, super reasonable price for the size of the villa and upkeep!!"
> **- Tegan Hurst (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-turtle-beach-club-1.jpg','099 279 9073','119, 1, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.blueturtlehotelsamui.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.205+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.205+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-turtle-beach-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/blue-turtle-beach-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13778516509879075039',NULL,NULL);
