INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chandra','standard','cmr07ig8b0069q8xdyrnjvun9','Chandra','## Top Reviews
> "Picked up some gems at Chandra Boutique in Fisherman’s Village, Koh Samui. The clothes nail that island romance look—perfect for paradise vibes. Handmade leather bags for guys and gals, plus versatile accessories for any occasion. Loving this holiday haul! 🌴 #KohSamui"
> **- Adrian (5/5/5)**

> "I recently had the pleasure of visiting **Chandra**, and I must say, this store is an absolute gem for anyone who appreciates **beautiful, high-quality clothing**. From the moment I stepped inside, I was captivated by the **stunning assortment** of garments—each piece more elegant and stylish than the last. The selection is so impressive that I genuinely wanted to buy **everything**! Whether you''re looking for chic everyday wear, sophisticated office attire, or something special for an evening out, Chandra has it all.  One thing to note is that the **prices are on the higher side**, but in my opinion, they are completely justified. The fabrics, stitching, and overall craftsmanship of the clothing reflect true luxury, making each purchase a worthwhile investment. If you value **durability, unique designs, and premium materials**, you won’t be disappointed.  What truly sets Chandra apart, however, is the **exceptional customer service**. The staff is warm, professional, and always ready to assist without being pushy. A special shout-out goes to **Pat**, who was an absolute delight! Her attention to detail is remarkable—she ensures that the store is **immaculately clean and visually appealing**, creating a shopping experience that feels both luxurious and welcoming. It’s clear that she takes great pride in her work, and her dedication enhances the overall atmosphere of the store.  If I had to mention one downside, it would be that the prices might not be accessible to everyone, but for those who can afford it, Chandra offers **unmatched quality and style**. I left the store not only with a beautiful new outfit but also with a strong desire to return soon.  **Final verdict:** Chandra is a **must-visit** for fashion enthusiasts who appreciate **elegance, quality, and outstanding service**. I highly recommend it and will definitely be back for more!"
> **- Olya Kharitonova (5/5/5)**

> "I love the vibe at Chandra Boutique. I’ve enjoyed shopping for festivals, birthdays and no reason at all. The ladies are always helpful and I keep coming back for sexy vibes!"
> **- Emily Thompson (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chandra-1.jpg','084 291 5588','66, 1, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://chandraboutique.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifs5000eq8xdeu148200','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.339+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.339+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chandra-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chandra-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17105885720671917653',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('charm','standard','cmr07ig8d006aq8xd7ogijam4','Charm','## Top Reviews
> "We visited Charm Samui for dinner based on a recommendation, and it exceeded all our expectations.  The restaurant itself is simple and cozy, creating a very relaxed and welcoming atmosphere. The cocktails were outstanding, but the food was truly exceptional. My husband had the beef cheeks, and the meat was so tender it practically fell apart with just a fork.  We also shared a starter, which was absolutely delicious and the perfect beginning to the meal. Throughout the evening, we felt genuinely cared for and very well looked after by the staff. The service was attentive, warm, and professional without ever feeling overwhelming.  Overall, it was a fantastic dining experience, and we can highly recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting Koh Samui. We would definitely come back again."
> **- Melinda Inauen (5/5/5)**

> "Unfortunately, I had the chance to visit only once, but it was truly a wonderful experience. The atmosphere is beautiful, just as the food is excellent. A place that perfectly combines the warmth of Thailand with the organization and professionalism of a Western-style restaurant. Carlos is a fantastic host, and the entire team truly stands out: attentive, professional, genuinely kind, and always smiling, creating a welcoming and relaxed dining experience from start to finish! Thank you all for the lovely evening you offered me. 🙏 Advance reservation is highly recommended"
> **- Chris Ps (5/5/5)**

> "If you’re in Samui go this absolute must-visit! From the moment we arrived, the hospitality was beyond anything I’ve ever experienced. The owner was extraordinary — so warm, welcoming, and genuinely passionate about creating a beautiful experience for every guest.  The food was simply outstanding. The red snapper was cooked to perfection — fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. And the chocolate fondue… absolutely to die for! It was the perfect indulgent finish to an already incredible meal.  The service was flawless, attentive without being intrusive, and every detail felt thoughtfully considered. You can truly feel the heart and soul that goes into this place.  Highly recommend and would absolutely be back without hesitation. A true five-star experience in every way!, from Elle, Sydney Australia"
> **- Elle Hookham (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/charm-1.jpg',NULL,'8/2, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://charmsamui.com/','["Monday: 2:00 – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: Closed","Wednesday: 2:00 – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 2:00 – 11:00 PM","Friday: 2:00 – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 2:00 – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 2:00 – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.341+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.341+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/charm-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/charm-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9468175187991793836',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-bliss-bungalow','standard','cmr07ig8g006bq8xdx8jdzc3e','Chaweng Bliss Bungalow','## Top Reviews
> "I love that its towards the end instead of being in the middle.   Theres still lots of restaurants down this way and its not in the busy area. The rooms are great for the price but the shower head needs getting used to lol The papaya salad is the best on thr island. Also I think its cleanest pool I''ve ever seen."
> **- Talun Ting (PNW attaché) (5/5/5)**

> "Great stay at Chaweng Bliss Bungalow. The staff were very friendly and helpful, especially the receptionist Noc who was always kind and willing to help. The place was clean and good value for money. Recommended."
> **- Meir Semo (5/5/5)**

> "Rooms were clean, staff were friendly and accomodating allowing us to have a late check out. Accessible to the beach, pool, beach bars, massage and 7-eleven."
> **- Kiani Rowling (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-bliss-bungalow-1.jpg','077 413 740','17/37 Chaweng Beach บ่อผุด Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'https://chawengblissbungalow.top/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.344+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.344+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-bliss-bungalow-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-bliss-bungalow-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13952269088557538607',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-buri','standard','cmr07ig8j006cq8xd1b0sp88j','Chaweng Buri','## Top Reviews
> "Considering the price compared to other hotels in the area, this hotel offers excellent value for money. The rooms are spacious bungalow-style cabins, and the location is fantastic, with easy access to everything nearby.  The hotel is also very clean and well maintained. The only downside for me was that the bathrooms still have bathtubs instead of separate showers, which may not be as convenient for some guests.  The highlights of my stay were definitely the gym and the location. Overall, I would happily stay here again and would recommend it to anyone looking for a comfortable and affordable place in the area."
> **- Guillermo Rufas Puyuelo (4/5/5)**

> "We absolutely loved our stay at Chaweng Buri Resort in Koh Samui. The location is beautiful, the beach access is amazing, and the overall vibe of the resort was peaceful yet lively at the same time.  A special mention to Kris at the reception — his hospitality, warmth, and professionalism truly made our experience even more memorable. He went above and beyond to make us feel welcomed and comfortable throughout our stay.  The staff, service, and atmosphere were all top-notch. Highly recommended for anyone looking for a perfect stay in Chaweng. We’ll definitely be coming back again."
> **- Vishal Vats (5/5/5)**

> "I am writing to express my extreme dissatisfaction regarding my stay at your hotel. Unfortunately, what should have been an enjoyable experience turned into one of the worst hotel experiences I have ever had.  The most serious issue was the discovery of a cockroach inside my pillow. Finding such an insect in the very place where a guest is expected to sleep is absolutely disgusting, unacceptable, and raises serious concerns about the hygiene standards of your establishment. This is not a minor inconvenience; it is a major sanitation issue that completely ruined my sense of comfort and security during my stay.  Beyond this shocking incident, the room itself was far below expectations. It lacked natural light, making it feel dark and unpleasant throughout the day. The bathroom was outdated and poorly maintained, giving the impression that the facilities have not been properly renovated or cared for in a long time. On top of that, the constant noise from passing aircraft made it extremely difficult to rest and enjoy the stay.  What disappoints me even more than the condition of the room is the way this situation was handled by both the staff and management. I expected professionalism, accountability, and a genuine effort to resolve a serious problem. Instead, I was offered complimentary transportation worth only a few euros. Frankly, this felt insulting considering the severity of the issue. Finding a cockroach inside a pillow is not something that can be brushed aside with a token gesture equivalent to a few euros.  The manager completely failed to demonstrate effective leadership or provide a meaningful solution. At no point did I feel that the seriousness of the situation was properly acknowledged. Rather than addressing my concerns with care and professionalism, I was left with the impression that the hotel simply wanted the matter to disappear as quickly as possible.  To make matters worse, when I continued to seek a proper resolution, I was informed that your latest response would be your “final response.” This is particularly frustrating because that response did absolutely nothing to solve the problems I experienced. Simply declaring a response to be final does not erase the fact that a guest found a cockroach in their pillow, nor does it compensate for the poor condition of the room, the excessive noise, and the overall negative experience. Closing the conversation without offering a genuine solution is not customer service; it is avoiding responsibility.  Overall, this experience reflects poorly on both the hotel’s hygiene standards and its management practices. I am deeply disappointed by the lack of professionalism, the inadequate handling of a serious complaint, and the complete absence of a satisfactory resolution.  I sincerely hope that you will reconsider the way this matter has been handled and take the necessary steps to improve both your hygiene standards and your approach to guest complaints.  I look forward to hearing from you with a response that genuinely addresses the issues raised rather than dismissing them."
> **- simon cattan (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-buri-1.jpg','093 584 8079','14, 4, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.chawengburi.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.347+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.347+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-buri-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-buri-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12467146339721417076',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-cove-beach-resort','standard','cmr07ig8m006dq8xd6luwjm7v','Chaweng Cove Beach Resort','## Top Reviews
> "Excellent location by the beach, maybe the best part of Chaweng beach for swimming, quiet aera. Many bars, restaurants around as well as 7/11. You can’t fault the location. The entrance is not the most welcoming but once you find you bungalow you will feel better. Our room was beachfront, with a private little pool on the terrace. We like to stay outside and the seaview. The room itself was okay nothing fancy. 2 beds, one fridge, simple bathroom but large shower aera. Only drawback is they provide only 1 room key which ignites the power and A/C. That means when you go out, it’s getting really hot inside. They argued it was to save energy… Other hotels don’t do that. The breakfast food was okay and we have tried the lunch once which was not the best we had. Paid about 7500 THB a night in April. I wouldn’t pay more here. Overall a good stay."
> **- P-A Nordmann (4/5/5)**

> "The staff was very friendly. They surprised me with a little birthdaycake and helped me apply disinfectant after I slipped outside the hotel due to rain, i appreciate this alot! The cleaningstaff were also very friendly in explaining me some questions about the minibar and towels. The room and facilities and the friendly baarkeeper of their restaurant were all great. Totally recommend and would stay again :)"
> **- Nicolas Fuchs (5/5/5)**

> "What words can we use to describe this hotel. Amazing, fantastic, unbelievable, stunning Why this hotel only has a 3* rating is crazy, because everything about it is 5*. It really is like paradise. The reception staff listen to any concern you may have, and it gets sorted within 5 mins. The hotel manager Ananya, goes out of her way to personally make sure everything is to your satisfaction. This is no ordinary hotel, it''s like a tropical village within itself, with immaculate gardens which are tendered every day. Individual bungalows, either detached or semi detached, gives you a peaceful nights sleep. Your rooms are cleaned every day to an incredibly high standard. The onsight beachfront restaurant has incredible sea views. Full range of drinks and a great food menu. Every bungalow has the following as standard Free air conditioning Free safety deposit box Free Wi-Fi 2 free bottles of water every day The bathroom has Free toothbrushes, toothpaste, shampoo, shower gel, soap, shower caps, clean towels each day, a hairdryer, and much more. All my wife and I can say about Chaweng Cove is that it is simply amazing, and will make sure you have the best holiday of your life. There are 3 swimming pools of various depths to cater for all ages, and their own private section of the beach, has numerous free sunbeds and parasols for their guests. When they found out it was my wife''s 70th birthday during our stay, they decorated the bed and left a birthday cake, which was delicious all at no extra cost. (See pictures) It''s location is perfect for a peaceful nights sleep, but only a 20 minute walk the very noisy lively area of town, but there are numerous restaurants only a few metres away as you walk into town. Thank you from Gary and Jackie Lamb. Rooms B14 and B4 for giving us a wonderful time."
> **- Gary Lamb (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-cove-beach-resort-1.jpg','077 422 509','17 4 Chaweng Beach Rd, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.chawengcove.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.350+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.350+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-cove-beach-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-cove-beach-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=14428269806963684205',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-dental-care','standard','cmr07ig8p006eq8xdjz6ym1sd','Chaweng Dental Care','## Top Reviews
> "I have come here twice now. I have struggled finding a good dentist in the UK. I saw the amazing reviews here and tried it out! I saw Nuntida who immidiately advised me on what was needed, and helped me by smoothing out some chips on my front teeth I was very self conscious of. I needed feelings and they sorted them quickly and pain free and I instantly have less sensitivity. I recommend to everyone to come here for your dental needs. Amazing staff all round, fairly priced for the amazing quality and excellent dental work! 🦷"
> **- Lucie Smith (5/5/5)**

> "Best Dental Experience in Samui I visited 3 other Dentist in Samui before finally coming to this clinic. I highly recommend. The X-ray is up to date, which means it’s less toxic. The staff and the Doctor were very professional and she took her time explaining the problem and solution. She didn’t treat me like another number. I found her to be honest and thorough. She also put me at ease during the procedure. The prices were also fair. You are my new dentist now! Thank you so much for your kindness 🙏"
> **- Julie Hartzog (5/5/5)**

> "I had a wonderful experience with the doctor and staff. I came in for a routine cleaning and teeth whitening. Everyone was knowledgeable, friendly, and kind. I would certainly recommend."
> **- BaliBert1 (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-dental-care-1.jpg','085 889 1234','84/13 Moo 2, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Samui, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.2,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.chawengdental.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 7:30 PM"]','cmr07ig1d003gq8xdfxkqj28w','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.353+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.353+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-dental-care-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-dental-care-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5552151567108924973',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-hill-village','standard','cmr07ig8r006fq8xdjarbuihi','Chaweng Hill Village','## Top Reviews
> "We had a great experience overall. First off, addresses are a bit different in Thailand, just type in Chaweng Hill Village for directions or to give to a taxi. It''s a pretty steep hill up the driveway, so if a taxi isn''t happy to take you all the way just get dropped at the restaurant at the bottom of the driveway and hike up from there. The rooms are very clean and tidy, high ceilings and AC works a treat. The building manager hooked us up with bike rentals and taxis smoothly, but you can rent from the cafe next door too. Great views and quiet atmosphere, excellent for a relaxing stay if you want to avoid party beach 😉"
> **- John Murray (5/5/5)**

> "Overall a good stay, but with conditions Liked... The view and pool area. Kitchen is decently equipped. The Kitchen also has appliances like rice cooker, cooker hob, food processor and coffee grinder Disliked... The scheduling was messed up so that the cleaning was not done, even though I arrived late afternoon. Therefore there was not enough time for proper cleaning. The hot water in the shower was inconsistent and the wifi failed on day 3 of my trip. Fortunately there was another WIFI network available that I could use which was provided after some time. Be aware that most taxis do not want to drop off or pick up on the hill, so it is advisable to book a powerful or 4wd vehicle during your trip."
> **- Leynard Theseira (4/5/5)**

> "Very bad hosts. They change the terms of the deal and postpone the deadlines. We paid a deposit for an apartment. The hostess named Nong postponed the date of settlement twice. Then she said that she wanted to put us in a completely different apartment. We demanded the deposit back, as this is a disgusting breach of agreement. Nong refused to return the deposit. I had to say that we would go to the police. Only after that we got our money back."
> **- Kate Kate (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-hill-village-1.jpg',NULL,'G29R+2H3, Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifw3001mq8xdy3gf4igo','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.355+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.355+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-hill-village-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-hill-village-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6191568595813890621',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-khaosan-restaurant','standard','cmr07ig8t006gq8xdk1e7125r','Chaweng Khaosan Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "I visited your restaurant today and had an amazing experience! 🍴 The ambience was inviting and cozy, making the dining experience even more enjoyable.  *Ambience:* The place was clean, well-decorated, and had a positive vibe. The interior design and lighting added a nice touch.  *Service:* The staff were prompt and professional, from taking orders to serving dishes. Kudos for the efficient service!  *Staff:* Your team was friendly and helpful. They provided great recommendations and were attentive throughout.  *Food:* The dishes were delicious! Flavors were spot on and well-balanced. Loved it!  Hope you keep up the good work. Highly recommend 💯❤️"
> **- Yasir Aziz (4/5/5)**

> "With a rating of 4.4 on Google reviews I was hoping for some tasty grub.  Unfortunately the scallops were overcooked, rubbery, and had little taste.  The chicken burger whilst huge, was nothing to write home about, and the french fries tasted cheap.  Good portion size and lovely staff, but with so many places to eat along Chaweng, I''d look elsewhere"
> **- Christian Hoffman (3/5/5)**

> "Fabulous find in busy Chaweng. Its also known as Side Walk, opposite the Central Samui shopping centre. Fabulous food, service and best reasonably priced white and red wine by the glass. We have visited twice during our trip and going back for more ... our last night! Air con and lovely decor. Couldnt fault it. Peppered steak to die for and only 450 baht. Aroy :)"
> **- Susanne Greig (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-khaosan-restaurant-1.jpg','092 732 0951','เลขที่ 200/10 หมู่2 ถ. เลียบหาดเฉวง, 200 10 m, G3J6+4F, 2 Chaweng Beach Rd, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://linktr.ee/ChawengKhaosanSamui',NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.357+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.357+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-khaosan-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-khaosan-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9188563503722532601',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-noi-pool-villa','standard','cmr07ig8v006hq8xdh0sqxcva','Chaweng Noi Pool Villa','## Top Reviews
> "We booked 2 rooms for our family stay from 31/5/2026 to 4/6/2026, but unfortunately we had to check out after just one night.  The photos shown on Google and booking platforms were very different from the actual condition of the rooms. The rooms appeared old, poorly maintained, and had a strong musty smell. The bathtub in the bathroom was dirty, and the wooden panel above the bathtub was covered with visible mold.  Most concerning, all of us woke up feeling extremely itchy after sleeping in the beds. We also noticed small insect-like debris and dirt on the bedding, which raised concerns about cleanliness and hygiene.  Due to these issues, we decided not to continue our stay and had to spend extra money to book accommodation elsewhere for the remaining nights.  We hope the management will take these concerns seriously and improve the cleanliness, maintenance, and overall condition of the rooms."
> **- Sadshadow0399 Shadow (2/5/5)**

> "We only stayed for one night here but immediately wished we had booked more when we arrived. We were a group of 6, and they put our rooms next door to each other (something hotels seem rarely to do when you book as a group!) which was so appreciated. The rooms were very modern and clean, with comfy beds, a safe, pool towels, and hairdryers provided. The pool and communal areas are lovey and well maintained. You definitely feel like you get a lot for your money and this hotel is very reasonably priced for the quality of service and room. We would definitely stay here again!  The only thing I would say is a slight downside is the location, if you do not ride a scooter then you are limited on where you would be able to get to without getting a grab or a baht bus. You can walk to Chaweng Noi beach, and there is a 7/11 and shops not too far away to walk to, however you have to walk alongside a busy dual carriageway with no path which feels very dangerous"
> **- Eleanor Dore (5/5/5)**

> "Not sure how this place is a 4star resort, but it is. The place looks tired and so does the staff. Not that we had an issue with our stay, just trying to give an honest opinion.  I will however say that if we had an issue, the staff were on to it immediately.  The location is only good if you want to lie around the pool or cross the road for the beach. There is not a great lot nearby.  The breakfast leaves a lot to be desired. Not a lot was actually hot, except the eggs that you order.  One more thing, which really isn''t the hotels fault, but the smell of marijuana throughout the resort is horrendous."
> **- Keith McNamara (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-noi-pool-villa-1.jpg','077 310 641','4/20 Moo3 Chaweng Noi -Main Road, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://chawengnoipoolvilla.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 4:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ig5c0051q8xdykrbexft','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.359+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.359+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-noi-pool-villa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-noi-pool-villa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13905108464196404356',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-park-place','standard','cmr07ig8x006iq8xdva05253g','Chaweng Park Place','## Top Reviews
> "The Hotel is ok. We got quite a big room for a good price. Anyway the bathroom was not properly cleaned, there were used pimple patches on the wall. The pool area was super nice and clean. The Hotel staff was friendly. A big minus is that next to the Hotel is a nightmarked were they play music super loud until 2am in the night, it was impossible to sleep. We stayed there for 4 nights and 4/4 it was that case."
> **- Bella (3/5/5)**

> "Best place in chaweng, far enough from the noise of the side beach road. Only 10 min walking so its very peaceful in the night. Located beside the lake , good for jogging in the morning. The rooms are very spacious and comfortable.  Staff very nice and kind. I loved stay here , very good energy. Feel so peaceful. I recommend it ."
> **- Fabio Gradara (5/5/5)**

> "Worst hotel ever! Do yourself a favor and stay somewhere else.  Don’t be fooled by the lovely pics of the pool. It’s definitely NOT what it looks like.  What it is: Super loud from the busy street, constant noise even with closed windows, broken furniture, super loud aircon, spiderwebs, dirt and mold smell in the halls, no breakfast, no bar, no stairs on one side of the pool, piles coming off everywhere, super dirty materacces on the plastic sunbeds. To the hotel manager: do you really think it could be relaxing for anyone to swim in your dirty pool?  I hated my stay there with all that constant  noise and dirt. The area itself is a place for masses, I wish I had knew that before! High food prices and not tasty at all and unfortunately very unfriendly locals - no one greeting back and seemed like they felt annoyed by you wanting to buy something. Beach wasn’t great at all - millions of people and bars, no relaxation there neither. Super loud everything & everywhere! Don’t get me wrong, I love Bangkok and it’ can also be loud, but this…this is just yaaaaack I would have skipped Chaweng alltogether, had i known what a nasty place it’s become.  By the way, I’m posting here, because Agoda wouldn’t publish my review. Hmmm. The selctivness is never fair."
> **- aga (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-park-place-1.jpg','077 300 671','147/49-50 147 42, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.9,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.sasitara.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.361+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.361+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-park-place-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-park-place-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4031025853713998120',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-regent-beach-resort','standard','cmr07ig8z006jq8xd5jq4oqv0','Chaweng Regent Beach Resort','## Top Reviews
> "I''m writing this review from the hotel right now. My wife, son, and I had a very comfortable 10-day holiday. The hotel is located at the beginning of the main street in Chaweng Beach, a famous area of ​​Koh Samui. It''s situated in the lively atmosphere of Chaweng, but also offers endless peace and relaxation when you retreat to your room or hotel. The staff are generally very kind. I don''t know about all the rooms, but the suites are quite spacious and provide all the comforts. The mini-bar is replenished daily. The breakfast has a wide variety. The internet speed is acceptable. The deposit they take upon arrival is a bit high. There are two beautiful swimming pools, one on the beach and one in the inner courtyard. And the inner courtyard pool bar is especially nice, and the staff there are very polite. The biggest problem at the pools is that even in the early morning hours, guests occupy the sunbeds by placing their towels there. The hotel management needs to be stricter about this. The beach is very beautiful and peaceful. During our visit (the second half of January), due to the tide, the beach disappeared until late afternoon, but in the evening it was incredibly peaceful. The gym is very clean, and although there isn''t a lot of equipment, you can still keep up with your workout while on vacation. There were complaints about neglect on booking sites and in reviews here. While these comments are valid, I didn''t see much neglect or wear and tear. Yes, there are minor things. And also, the resort is practically in the sea, so this kind of wear and tear is normal. But still, I don''t think it''s a 5-star hotel. However, I was quite satisfied with my stay and, as someone who has seen other parts of Koh Samui, I highly recommend it to anyone coming to Koh Samui."
> **- Koray Cankara (5/5/5)**

> "Love this hotel, location is perfect for beachlife and nightlife. Staff are friendly and attentive. Breakfast is excellent. Rooms are large with good air con. Pools are kept immaculately clean. Having stayed 5 times here my only complaint is that check in is always a little chaotic and could be smoother."
> **- Robin Innes (5/5/5)**

> "We have just had 14 nights at this resort and  have had a wonderful experience.  The staff are fantastic, the facilities are clean, well maintained and the location is ideal. We had the pleasure of meeting Joakim ( Hotel Manager) at one of the nightly events , who was a delight and very engaging. We will be booking in the future."
> **- Darin Shipp (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-regent-beach-resort-1.jpg','077 300 500','155/4 ถนน เลียบหาดเฉวง Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.chawengregent.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.363+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.363+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-regent-beach-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-regent-beach-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6517242781606261887',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chaweng-villawee-hotel','standard','cmr07ig92006kq8xdw6xhb4su','Chaweng Villawee Hotel','## Top Reviews
> "Booked in 4 nights ..and this hotel is lovely. Good location in Chaweng, not on beach side. Very clean, modern flair and very welcoming staff. After we checked in to our poolside room, we realised that this older pair had difficulty accessing the pool...no small steps just a large drop and no railing. Great for the younger folk with no joint problems lol... We advised the reception that we would be checking out after one night and that we were not looking for a refund. However, the manager and staff were brilliant and organised a 50% refund which was absolutely grand and very appreciated. The overnight stay was great, really lovely bed, great bathroom (we reported a leak in plumbing and that was fixed within 30 minutes ). We had brekkie the next morning, although limited choice the food was fresh, brekkie egg options available and strong coffee... what else do you need !!! The pool waterfall is lovely to hear and see in the brekkie room, with lovely large louvres which give lovely breezes. If our old bones were not so old ..perfect, quiet part of Chaweng to stay !!!"
> **- Rob Andrews (4/5/5)**

> "We were welcomed by very friendly staff, which made a great first impression. The room was clean, cozy, and well soundproofed, allowing for a comfortable stay. Breakfast was good, and the location was convenient. Due to the hotel’s proximity to the airport, airplane noise could be heard quite often. However, it didn’t bother us at all. We actually enjoyed watching the planes take off and land. The pool looked great as well, although unfortunately we didn’t get to use it due to bad weather. Overall, a pleasant and enjoyable stay."
> **- Bohdana Kráľová (5/5/5)**

> "Really enjoyed our stay at Chaweng Villawee Hotel. Even though it’s in a busy area, we slept very well. You can walk to all the shops easily. You can hear airplanes occasionally, but it didn’t bother us. The pool area is very nice and perfect for relaxing. Great overall experience!"
> **- ashyy (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-villawee-hotel-1.jpg','077 332 999','174 ม.2 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.chawengvillawee.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.366+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.366+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-villawee-hotel-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chaweng-villawee-hotel-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17821506898791255561',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chawenghill-village','standard','cmr07ig95006lq8xdm7r4dfcm','Chawenghill Village','## Top Reviews
> "We had a great experience overall. First off, addresses are a bit different in Thailand, just type in Chaweng Hill Village for directions or to give to a taxi. It''s a pretty steep hill up the driveway, so if a taxi isn''t happy to take you all the way just get dropped at the restaurant at the bottom of the driveway and hike up from there. The rooms are very clean and tidy, high ceilings and AC works a treat. The building manager hooked us up with bike rentals and taxis smoothly, but you can rent from the cafe next door too. Great views and quiet atmosphere, excellent for a relaxing stay if you want to avoid party beach 😉"
> **- John Murray (5/5/5)**

> "Overall a good stay, but with conditions Liked... The view and pool area. Kitchen is decently equipped. The Kitchen also has appliances like rice cooker, cooker hob, food processor and coffee grinder Disliked... The scheduling was messed up so that the cleaning was not done, even though I arrived late afternoon. Therefore there was not enough time for proper cleaning. The hot water in the shower was inconsistent and the wifi failed on day 3 of my trip. Fortunately there was another WIFI network available that I could use which was provided after some time. Be aware that most taxis do not want to drop off or pick up on the hill, so it is advisable to book a powerful or 4wd vehicle during your trip."
> **- Leynard Theseira (4/5/5)**

> "Very bad hosts. They change the terms of the deal and postpone the deadlines. We paid a deposit for an apartment. The hostess named Nong postponed the date of settlement twice. Then she said that she wanted to put us in a completely different apartment. We demanded the deposit back, as this is a disgusting breach of agreement. Nong refused to return the deposit. I had to say that we would go to the police. Only after that we got our money back."
> **- Kate Kate (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chawenghill-village-1.jpg',NULL,'G29R+2H3, Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.369+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.369+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chawenghill-village-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chawenghill-village-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chawenghill-village-3.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chawenghill-village-4.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6191568595813890621',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chef-wayz-shabu','standard','cmr07ig97006mq8xdh09olrnj','Chef Wayz Shabu','## Top Reviews
> "Amazing Hot Pot Experience! ★★★★★  This place is a true gem for hot pot lovers! The dual broths were both flavorful and satisfying—perfect for cooking a wide variety of fresh ingredients. We especially enjoyed the tender slices of meat, udon noodles, and colorful vegetables like baby corn and okra. Everything was fresh and of great quality.  The takoyaki was also delicious—crispy on the outside, soft and savory on the inside, with generous toppings that added a perfect touch.  The setting is clean, modern, and welcoming, and the service was friendly and efficient. We loved the interactive dining experience, taking our time to enjoy each bite as we cooked it ourselves. Great value and an overall fantastic night out!  Highly recommended—we’ll definitely be coming back!"
> **- Jérémie Rasumny Cohen (5/5/5)**

> "Extremely disappointing experience. The place was filthy — tables left uncleared, floors sticky and unmopped, and the toilet in a terrible state with sewage overflowing from the handwashing basin. Hygiene was clearly not a priority. Service was just as bad; after waiting over 20 minutes, even the broth hadn’t arrived. We eventually gave up and went to another restaurant."
> **- shivanpillay (1/5/5)**

> "The menu was a bit confusing, they didn''t only have japanese food, but also mexican, italian and other dishes, that didn''t really fit the outside apperance. The interior is really cheap looking and also cold, not cozy at all. The food was actually fine, my sandwich was just way too sweet for a savoury dish."
> **- Amelie S (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chef-wayz-shabu-1.jpg','086 434 4227','22, Meanam, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/chefwayzshabu','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 3:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Wednesday: 3:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Thursday: 3:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Friday: 3:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Saturday: 3:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Sunday: 3:00 PM – 12:00 AM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.371+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.371+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chef-wayz-shabu-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chef-wayz-shabu-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15947407906702904226',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('cherish-restaurant-bar','standard','cmr07ig99006nq8xdpp91b9ks','Cherish Restaurant & Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Amazing vibes! The sunset view from restaurant was absolutely stunning — the perfect backdrop for a great meal. The staff were super friendly and helpful. Big shoutout to Khun San who made our experience truly special with his warm and attentive service. 100% recommend. Will definitely be back! 🌅🍽️​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​"
> **- Chanyanin Kasinakaunggoon (5/5/5)**

> "Cherish Restaurant & Bar is absolutely amazing! The food is top class — truly outstanding. The Cherish beef burger is the best burger I have ever had in my life.  The staff are wonderful, incredibly kind and attentive to every detail. They really make you feel welcome and well taken care of. Nothing but praise for this place — highly recommended!"
> **- Ana Marija Bertic (5/5/5)**

> "Cherish is an absolute must-visit! The food is beyond wonderful—honestly, whatever you choose from the menu, you simply cannot go wrong. Every dish is prepared to perfection. The atmosphere is extra special, creating the perfect vibe for a great meal. What truly sets this place apart, though, is the staff. They are incredibly kind and attentive, going above and beyond to make sure your dining experience is absolutely perfect. A 10/10 experience that I would recommend to everyone!"
> **- Djordje Ivanovski (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/cherish-restaurant-bar-1.jpg','080 249 4528','Koh Samui, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://cherishsamui.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifs1000cq8xdfo2aau32','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.373+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.373+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/cherish-restaurant-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/cherish-restaurant-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=7112944841614171182',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chez-bartoch','standard','cmr07ig9b006oq8xd8jacgl7m','Chez Bartoch','## Top Reviews
> "It was amazing!!! I''m French and completely addicted to Italian food. I''ve tried several French restaurants on Koh Samui, and this is by far the best. It''s even one of the best pizzerias I''ve ever eaten at."
> **- nicolas leroy (5/5/5)**

> "Delicious woodfire pizzas. Been there few times. Tried a number of things. The 4-cheese calzone was our favourite.  The melting cheese was just mouthwatering. Insatiable! Will definitely go again."
> **- Martlet (5/5/5)**

> "Really good and nice pizza. Tasteful mozzarella cheese, well prepared tomato sauce , great dough. Owner and staff are all friendly and nice. Only one small suggestion : seating needs regular cleaning in my opinion, as it gets dusty from the road nearby.  Recommended for groups and couples."
> **- XXX XXX (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chez-bartoch-1.jpg','064 026 5551','83 81 Chumchon Chaweng Yai Soi 4 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 12:00 – 2:30 PM, 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 2:30 PM, 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Wednesday: Closed","Thursday: 12:00 – 2:30 PM, 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 2:30 PM, 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 2:30 PM, 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Sunday: 12:00 – 2:30 PM, 5:30 – 10:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.375+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.375+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chez-bartoch-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chez-bartoch-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13579798564211094804',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chez-francois','standard','cmr07ig9e006pq8xdhe9g5dht','Chez Francois','## Top Reviews
> "Chez Francois Koh Samui is truly one of the most impressive dining experiences in Koh Samui. The food is absolutely delicious — every dish is beautifully presented, rich in flavor, and crafted with clear attention to detail. It genuinely feels like a fine dining experience comparable to top French restaurants.  The restaurant itself is small and intimate, with only a limited number of tables, which makes the atmosphere cozy and exclusive. Because of this, it is highly recommended to make a reservation in advance to secure your spot.  Service is exceptional — the staff are attentive, professional, and very welcoming, making the entire evening even more enjoyable. In terms of value, it is definitely worth it considering the quality of food and overall experience.  One small drawback is that the wine list is relatively limited, which might not fully satisfy wine enthusiasts. However, this does not take away from the overall outstanding experience. If you are visiting Koh Samui, this restaurant is absolutely worth trying."
> **- Chaiyo Jiarachaikul (4/5/5)**

> "We celebrated my birthday at this lovely French restaurant with my husband and our two children, and it turned out to be an absolutely exceptional evening. We chose the four-course tasting menu, and every single dish was beautifully presented and full of incredible flavor. The beef cheeks were especially unforgettable — we highly recommend trying them.  This is exactly the kind of place that may look modest at first glance but is truly a hidden gem. The wine pairing was outstanding and complemented each course perfectly.  Chef, we wish you good health and continued success in your craft. Thank you for such a memorable dinner and warm atmosphere."
> **- Olesia (5/5/5)**

> "Make sure to book in advance. There are limited spaces, and for a good reason.  This is a must go to if you like fine dining with excellent service.  The restaurant is very quaint, there are al a cart or a tasting menu, a great wine menu too.  You''ll love it."
> **- Richard Griffin (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chez-francois-1.jpg','096 071 1800','33/2 Moo1 Fisherman''s Village, Bophut, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.chezfrancoissamui.com/','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 6:30 – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 6:30 – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 6:30 – 11:00 PM","Friday: 6:30 – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 6:30 – 11:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.378+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.378+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chez-francois-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chez-francois-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6839621499127236697',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chi-beach-club','standard','cmr07ig9g006qq8xd92zmnrsh','Chi Beach Club','## Top Reviews
> "If you’re on the strip in Ko Samui and want somewhere that actually has a bit of life to it, this beach bar is easily the standout. Based on the time I spent in Samui, it was the only spot in the area that consistently has atmosphere — relaxed during the day, then gradually picking up energy into the evening without ever becoming chaotic.  The music is one of its strengths. Instead of blasting one genre, it is changed each day which adds variety. In the time I was there this included a local DJ in the day and then a singer who set the mood for dinner.  The service was great throughout the time we spent there. The staff are attentive and welcoming. The way in which they present themselves demonstrates a clear passion to cater to customer needs.  Food-wise, it’s better than you’d expect from a beach bar. The menu is broad — proper breakfasts, hearty English comfort food, solid Thai specials, pizzas, and more casual bites. Portions are reasonable (not oversized tourist traps), and the meals feel balanced rather than greasy, rushed or inconsistent. The quality of the food was noticeably high, and you can tell they care about presentation and ingredients.  That said, it is on the pricier side for the area. You’ll definitely notice you’re paying more than at some nearby local spots or the general average on the island. Whether it’s “worth it” depends on what you’re after — but in fairness, the quality of the food, the beachfront setting, and the overall experience do justify the premium.  If you want good food, decent music, and a proper beach atmosphere rather than just a quiet row of chairs and speakers, this is the place on Ko Samui that delivers and we will definitely return next time we are in the area."
> **- Louis Lamb (5/5/5)**

> "Initially I thought "
> **- Blake Rodwell (5/5/5)**

> "Very tasty lamb leg, octopus… champion breakfast good, but maybe next time will not order this dish. Very luxury design. Nice pool and beach area. Very kind staff. Tasty mimoza. Sangria to sweet."
> **- Rimvydas Baltrusevicius (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chi-beach-club-1.jpg','092 271 7439','16 H25X+2HW 4, H25X+2HW, 4 ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.chisamui.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 12:00 AM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrv000aq8xdn6zpp33d','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.380+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.380+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chi-beach-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chi-beach-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=18029436696661860073',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chi-the-residence','standard','cmr07ig9i006rq8xddyj4pv2c','Chi - The Residence','## Top Reviews
> "Our stay at the luxury apartment hotel was nothing short of outstanding. From the moment we arrived, we were welcomed with warm, attentive service that set the tone for an unforgettable experience.  The apartment itself was beautifully designed—spacious, modern, and impeccably clean. High-quality furnishings, plush bedding, and thoughtful touches throughout made it feel like a true home away from home. The views were stunning, and having a fully equipped kitchen and private living space added an extra layer of comfort and convenience.  The facilities were equally impressive: a pristine pool, a well-equipped gym, and serene common areas that radiated elegance. Every detail was curated to create a relaxing, luxurious atmosphere.  What truly stood out was the staff. Professional, friendly, and always willing to go above and beyond, they made our stay effortless and memorable.  A perfect blend of luxury, privacy, and comfort — highly recommended for both short and long stays. We can’t wait to return."
> **- GOLAN TACTICAL (5/5/5)**

> "We were in general ok staying here for a month. Service ladies and people in general, especially the gardener who sings outside, were cute and helpful. Managing team was ok. Water quality was almost all the time pretty bad though, and even if there are fancy baths you might not want to lie down in brown water.  Facilities in our villa (2nd floor) were good quality and we didn’t really lack anything. If something was broken they fixed it straight away. Cleaning was impeccable too.  What really left a bitter taste was a bit of nickel and diming. You pay 3k for a monthly apartment and then they charge 10 dollars for a chipped plate, and say they counted electricity extra for the last night in case we used a lot. We had to check out at 6:45 in the morning for our flight and we informed them in advance.  They also stood there counting all the pillows and each spoon in front of us to make sure we didn’t take anything. Pillows, umbrellas, beach bag too. That made us feel very uncomfortable. At 6:45 we did not expect someone knocking on our door, checking again and telling us it is time to check out and basically forcing us to leave immediately, so we ended up standing on the street with our luggage. Nice start of the day.  Location is in the middle of nowhere so you have to know you will have to drive everywhere. No one informed us that the beach bar would be closed this month, we only found out from the bartenders later. We were told we have 20 percent off there but it was closed anyway.  It is premium in terms of amenities, we were glad to have a pool for ourselves, and tenants living here were lovely people."
> **- Mary (3/5/5)**

> "We came at 10am, the reception told us our room would be ready by 2pm (as stated in their policy). When 2pm came, the workers were being dismissive and told us our room wouldn’t be ready for another hour, everyone else was able to get their room but us. What I presumed to be the manager was rude and disrespectful. Nice hotel but TERRIBLE service. If you have a flight that arrives to koi samui early, don’t expect early check in, book somewhere else."
> **- aya abdel (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chi-the-residence-1.jpg','092 271 7439','4171, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.chisamuiresidence.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifrv000aq8xdn6zpp33d','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.382+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.382+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chi-the-residence-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chi-the-residence-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6242752309279335038',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('chill-by-the-pool','standard','cmr07ig9k006sq8xd9t2lsohn','Chill By The Pool','## Top Reviews
> "Most everyone who worked here was very friendly and helpful.  The bungalow style rooms are pretty nice.  Maybe a little expensive for what you get but overall it’s a nice place to stay.  The breakfast buffet is fine but simple and nothing special. The pool is really nice and the beach is too but the sand isn’t very soft."
> **- Tai Ler (4/5/5)**

> "Came here to enjoy some nibbles over the afternoon. I was recommended one of their signature menu which is the "
> **- Wunda Stone (5/5/5)**

> "The pool area at New star beach has now just re opened, and non hotel residents can use the pool and restaurant area. We had a some fantastic food at the Chill by the pool restaurant and the whole family loved using the huge pool area. The pool and restaurant looks onto a beautiful quiet part of Chaweng Noi beach. The grilled marinated beef salad was the best I’ve had! Toom took really good care of us and the staff are super friendly and welcoming. You just need to message new star beach in advance to preorder food and let them know you’re coming and you get a discount and use of loungers, pools and towels provided."
> **- Alison (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chill-by-the-pool-1.jpg','077 414 500','83, Moo 3, New Star Beach Resort, Tambon Bo Phut, Amphoe Ko Samui, Surat Thani, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.newstarresort.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig5c0051q8xdykrbexft','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.384+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.384+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chill-by-the-pool-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/chill-by-the-pool-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=1193361306616075399',NULL,NULL);
