INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('ecopest','standard','cmr07igf00090q8xdt06i4hm4','Ecopest','## Top Reviews
> "We’ve been using EcoPest’s services for almost 6 years and without reservation, we can recommend them as being absolutely the best pest service in Samui 🥇. Always perfectly punctual, the monthly service is professional and thorough. We have many varieties of fruit trees that have been saved by EcoPest. When an insect infestation started to effect our papaya and mango trees, EcoPest’s spraying immediately took care of it; the trees are back to perfect health. When a tick was discovered walking on our puppy’s fur, EcoPest’s spraying of our property’s grass areas completely eliminated the problem. Their treatments killed a giant centipede, and scorpion —- we were certainly happy to find them dead rather than alive ☠️. For peace-of-mind, EcoPest’s services are definitely well worth the cost!"
> **- Jamie Knapp (5/5/5)**

> "Ali, Marie and their elite team have been servicing our property for well over a year now and we have only good things to say about the entire process from start to finish.  Their initial survey of the scope was thorough and personal. The price is more than fair and their team has consistently been the promptest, politest, most professional and efficient that we have encountered amongst all contractors of any type on the island.  Ecopest serves as a paragon of how a successful business can easily be managed!"
> **- Michael Mullen (5/5/5)**

> "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Excellent service – highly recommended  Ecopest Samui have been absolutely brilliant. Their staff speak excellent English, are very polite, and always punctual. They arrive exactly when they say they will, work efficiently, and do a very thorough job every time.  It’s refreshing to deal with a company that is professional, reliable, and genuinely cares about the quality of their work. I wouldn’t hesitate to recommend Ecopest Samui to anyone looking for a dependable pest control service on the island."
> **- Jon Kononowicz (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ecopest-1.jpg','+66857912496','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.ecopestsamui.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.580+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.580+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ecopest-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ecopest-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ecopest-3.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=18060257679187692098',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('eda-na','standard','cmr07igf20091q8xdb4nxinhg','Eda Na','## Top Reviews
> "The best place with Russian food in Thailand! The restaurant is owned by a friendly man who enjoys his job and gives a warm welcome. All the dishes we tried tasted great and reminded of homemade food from my gran in Russia. Divine herring salad!Also, the ambience is lovely and the space was decorated for NY’s with good taste. Don’t miss this cafe if you are in Samui."
> **- Daria Kirbai (5/5/5)**

> "So good! They have vegetarian borscht on request and a lot of veggie options. Free bread is served to the table. Tea is delicious. Potatoes are great along with blinchiki with mushrooms and cheburek with cheese."
> **- Sara Fischer (5/5/5)**

> "Wow, never had such good Russian food. I went here with a Russian friend and he agrees that the food is delicious. Some real Russian favourites like borscht, this noodle dish with minced meat, and the dumplings are amazing."
> **- Z (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/eda-na-1.jpg','099 303 9115','128/53 Moo 3 Koh Samui, ตำบล มะเร็ต อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.2,0,0,0,NULL,'https://taplink.cc/edanasamui','["Monday: 12:00 – 7:00 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 7:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 7:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 7:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 7:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 7:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.582+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.582+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/eda-na-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/eda-na-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16805877440632070896',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('eden-beach','standard','cmr07igf30092q8xd4v10ayvi','Eden Beach','## Top Reviews
> "The food is delicious and the drinks are excellent. The beach view and atmosphere are fantastic. The service is friendly and the staff are lovely. I highly recommend everyone visit at least once. 👍👍😍"
> **- Supranee Noonkliang (5/5/5)**

> "⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ A truly wonderful place – food, people, and atmosphere are amazing The food is simply outstanding – beautifully prepared, full of flavor, and clearly made with care and quality ingredients. The service is wonderful. The staff are incredibly kind, attentive, and seem to fulfill every wish before you even say it out loud. You feel genuinely cared for and welcomed here."
> **- Beatrice Framboise (5/5/5)**

> "Nice place for a drink and a day out. The beach is pretty and all the staff are amazing.  However, the food is pretty average if you are used to tasty Thai food. The food is actually very average.  Ordered a few dishes. The most dissaponted dish was the pad krapao sea food as we got a frozen squid like the one you can buy at the supermarket. How can you not offer fresh sea food on a beachfront location on a popular Thai island?  Chicken skewer plate 300 THB served without salad pretty strange. To be honest, for a French owner, you would expect a higher standard.  Besides that, the pizza was good. Great taste.  Anyhow, it''s a nice place to have a drink and perhaps to have a snack or 2 but nothing more.  Would love to see the kitchen improving!  Cheers."
> **- Gilles Van geit (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/eden-beach-1.jpg','089 316 8730','122, Lamai, 68, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.583+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.583+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/eden-beach-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/eden-beach-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16233752378729033730',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('edgewater-family-beach-club-and-bar','standard','cmr07igf60093q8xd0o5bmxo4','Edgewater Family Beach Club And Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Myself and my partner have just had a wonderful stay at the Outrigger hotel in Ko Samui. From the airport pickup to our last day - everything was perfect. The staff are wonderful (a big shout out to May and the kind reception staff). The rooms are beautiful and cleaned daily, there is always plenty of water topped up in the rooms and little touches that make the stay enjoyable. It is often busy around the pool if it is sunny so get there early. We couldn’t find sun beds yesterday but the staff made sure to let us know as soon as some were available. Breakfast was lovely and plentiful. We were worried before our stay about the road between the hotel and beach resort but it really is no issue. There are friendly security staff on hand 24 hours to ensure you cross safely and it’s worth it! We really liked the beach resort. Thank you Outrigger, cannot fault the wonderful service."
> **- Grace L (5/5/5)**

> "Fabulous team and surroundings. Nice food. Main big pool area across the road but 2 lovely men will flag down traffic to get you across the street. Pools are really nice. Beach is small I front of the hotel area but you can walk further up to an area which has more white sand. Rooms were very well kept. Breakfast was lovely and location was great. Some parking for cars too. Has a small gym a games room  for the kids too with a pool table. Slide on one of the pools too. There is also a pool near the bedrooms too but shaded due to its location. Still lovely to use. Would defo saty there again.thanks to all the team there..they were so friendly."
> **- Annmarie Hurley (4/5/5)**

> "Hotel and the staff were great and friendly! They remembered our names and made us feel welcome from the beginning. The main pool is across the road but that did not inconvenience us because it was easy to get across with the security helping to control traffic.  The only thing that hampered our stay was the house keepers did not have our room cleaned by 3pm. We went to breakfast and the pool by 9am and thought if we stayed out till 3 or 4pm the room would be cleaned and done which did not happen 2 of the 3 days we stayed. I had to find a maid cart for TP and ask for clean towels. The third day I found a housekeeper early in the morning and asked to please have our room cleaned and she obliged kindly.  Town is about a 15 min walk from the hotel and we did not mind that at all as we like to walk but a Grab ride is only like 300 or 400bht which is cheap.  I enjoyed our stay and would recommend the Outrigger hotel as a great place if you are in the area!"
> **- GT3 RS (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/edgewater-family-beach-club-and-bar-1.jpg','077 458 560','173, 41 Rob Koh Road, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.outrigger.com/thailand/outrigger-koh-samui-beach-resort','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.586+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.586+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/edgewater-family-beach-club-and-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/edgewater-family-beach-club-and-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16803426513922100969',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('el-barril','standard','cmr07igf80094q8xdjs070z9p','El Barril','## Top Reviews
> "Increíble. One of the best steaks I’ve ever had. I cook in a Michelin star kitchen and have eaten steak all over the world from France to Argentina and I have never had Onglet so good. The au poivre sauce was delicate but rich - just amazing. The filet was fantastic as well. The appetizers, the creme brulee, the sunset, the chef… incredible. Food cooked with passion. 10 stars if I could."
> **- Jake Agarwal (5/5/5)**

> "It was a great romantic experience with my partner. We walked in without a reservation but were seated right in front of the beach, with a beautiful view of the sunset. The food arrived quickly and was absolutely delicious. The service was amazing, the chef/owner even came out to talk to us about our dishes and shared a bit of his story.  Each plate was perfectly flavorful, and we ended our dinner on a high note with a soft and delicious crème brûlée. We loved the place! Definitely recommend, please support this wonderful spot."
> **- Christina Martinez Mundo (5/5/5)**

> "Im in love with Spanish food and culture, and I rarely leave reviews but after staying at 5star resort where the food was questionable, it was a great experience to come to EL BARRIL to feast with my family on the most flavoursome food we have had on the island. Even the French beef, and being Australian this is hard to say was 11 out of 10 Thankyou for the service and flavour burst in my mouth, oh and owner is the best chef."
> **- Shane Hay (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-barril-1.jpg','084 842 0181','134, Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Nathon, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 1:30 – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 1:30 – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 1:30 – 9:00 PM","Friday: 1:30 – 9:00 PM","Saturday: 1:00 – 9:00 PM","Sunday: 1:00 – 9:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig1h003iq8xdb1g9nifo','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.588+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.588+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-barril-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-barril-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4655687216398313513',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('el-dorado','standard','cmr07igfa0095q8xda73340nt','El Dorado','## Top Reviews
> "Hy husband and I had a wonderful dinner at this restaurant. Everything was perfect. I had the Swedish Meatballs and he had the mixed grill with chicken,  pork and beef. He said all the meats were cooked perfectly. My meatballs were melt in your mouth. The service was also great. I would return here."
> **- Carlotta Audain (5/5/5)**

> "excellent restaurant. we go here several times a year and it is always excellent, I recommend visiting, the gambas shrimps are the best I have ever eaten, we also had meat, always excellent"
> **- Lucia Hrajnohová (5/5/5)**

> "Probably the best value, and one of the best restaurants in Lamai.  They have a wide variety of dishes, including european and Swedish specialties like meatballs, plankstek (on select days) and more. They have vegetarian and salads, didn''t try that but given what i did try (have gone 10-20+ times over the years) i''m sure it''s great. Their Pizza is considered one of the best if not the best in Lamai. Every day they have different daily offerings so it''s a good idea to check their Facebook page.  One of the best things, though, is their staff. They''re not only super friendly, but sharp and quick."
> **- Jonas Jansson (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-dorado-1.jpg','094 409 0614','124/104 M.3 T Lanai Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/eldorado.lamai/','["Monday: 3:00 – 10:30 PM","Tuesday: 3:00 – 10:30 PM","Wednesday: 3:00 – 10:30 PM","Thursday: 3:00 – 10:30 PM","Friday: 3:00 – 10:30 PM","Saturday: 3:00 – 10:30 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.590+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.590+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-dorado-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-dorado-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=14341143281401038648',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('el-gaucho-fishermans-village','standard','cmr07igfb0096q8xdioiy7nez','El Gaucho','## Top Reviews
> "El Gaucho Chaweng is in Central Samui. I ordered the Australian 7oz filet steak done medium. You have as accompaniments a choice of fries or mash and pepper/ mushroom sauce or salad. The meat was so tender it cut like butter. To make it a whole dish I feel they shouldn''t have skimped and instead have given the sauce and salad."
> **- Maria Mammen (5/5/5)**

> "High end high quality steakhouse. Beautiful meats. Can be expensive... have a specials board...check this out. Service from staff was 5 star and service skills were impeccable..would return..meals approx 1000 per main..elegant seating and bar area. Nice place"
> **- Paul (5/5/5)**

> "Good food, great steak just a little pricy for what you get. No other complaints . Tried it at lunch time this maybe be worth the price and fun in the evenings with a crowed having dinner before going out"
> **- Gurpreet Bawa (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-gaucho-fishermans-village-1.jpg','093 278 8945','209/1-2 ตำบล บ่อผุด Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://elgaucho.asia/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.591+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.591+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-gaucho-fishermans-village-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-gaucho-fishermans-village-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5238766875444397313',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('el-gaucho','standard','cmr07igfd0097q8xd4pyjbp9o','El Gaucho','## Top Reviews
> "We made a reservation and were lucky enough to get a table outside right by the water — what a setting! The service was excellent, attentive and friendly throughout the evening. The food was outstanding. The steak was cooked to perfection and the burger was absolutely delicious — easily some of the best we’ve had. Yes, prices are on par with what you’d expect back in Europe, but given the quality of the food, the service, and that stunning waterfront atmosphere, it’s absolutely worth every penny. Highly recommend if you’re looking for a premium dining experience in Fisherman’s Village!"
> **- Yannick (5/5/5)**

> "We had a great spot at beachfront dining at El Gaucho.  We had a White Asparagus and Tuna Tartare for appetizers. Both were delicious. We were guided about out meats and fish selections . Everything was cooked to perfection and delicious! Pretty pricy dinner without alcohol."
> **- Nanda Sundri (5/5/5)**

> "Had dinner at El Gaucho which is a last minute plan as we did not have reservations anywhere. It’s a pleasant surprise, service is very good and attentive. Not a cheap place to dine (also have VAT and service charge) but the food is good. Love the complimentary bread with homemade mayo, chichiri sauce, butter and bread. Can really taste the freshness of the ingredients. Though is a steak restaurant, the lobster bisque is good. Can taste the umami freshness."
> **- Cheryl Koh (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-gaucho-1.jpg','098 889 5968','51/7 Fisherman''s Village, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://elgaucho.asia/','["Monday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.593+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.593+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-gaucho-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-gaucho-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16606617522933408049',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('el-torro-salvaje','standard','cmr07igff0098q8xds30yqdgl','El Torro Salvaje','## Top Reviews
> "El Toro has become our favorite local place to visit. From the outside, it might look a bit expensive, but once you step inside, you realize it’s absolutely worth it — the experience is amazing and truly memorable.  The staff truly make this place special — incredibly attentive, welcoming, and thoughtful. You can feel genuine care in the way they look after guests, always checking in without being intrusive. Small touches like cool hand towels on arrival make a great first impression and set the tone for the whole experience.  The food and drinks are consistently excellent. The variety of tapas is impressive, everything is fresh, and every dish we’ve tried has been delicious. Cocktails are also a highlight — high quality with great presentation. During happy hours, prices are very reasonable, which is quite rare for a place with this level of service and atmosphere.  The interior design also deserves a special mention — stylish and beautifully done, it’s a real treat for the eyes.  Every Saturday there’s live music, and Suzy and Angel are incredible — such a great atmosphere."
> **- Nadiya Bondarenko (5/5/5)**

> "This is one of our favourite places on the whole island.  The setting is beautiful, especially for sunset, but even before and after, as the decor is so lovely.  The music playlists never fail to disappoint, and I always find myself singing along to some great tunes.  The food is really good, from the array of large size Tapas to the full Sunday Roast lunch/dinner. The team here always deliver great service with a smile!"
> **- Deborah Bannon (5/5/5)**

> "The food was good. Especially the sliders. The burger buns were made of rich butter, like a brioche. Every bite you could taste the richness of the butter throughout the bun. It was one of the nicest buns in Samui.  Every dish tasted homemade which I loved! However, one dish that could be improved upon was the pork belly. It was a bit oily and the skin was not crispy enough and stick to the teeth.  The cheesecake that I ordered tasted homemade and it was delicious. Tasted fresh from the kitchen with a slight hint of lemon lingering aftertaste.  I would definitely come again and even bring a friend. 8/10"
> **- Yale Chen (陳頁真) (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-torro-salvaje-1.jpg',NULL,'63 217, เทศบาลนครเกาะสมุย อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://eltorosalvaje-samui.com/','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 3:00 – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 3:00 – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 3:00 – 11:00 PM","Friday: 3:00 – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 3:00 – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig6y005pq8xd4jrvheih','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.595+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.595+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-torro-salvaje-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/el-torro-salvaje-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=1521569483955423808',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('electric-forest-art-park','standard','cmr07igfh0099q8xdth4zgghy','Electric Forest Art Park','## Top Reviews
> "⭐⭐⭐☆☆ Electric Forest Samui – great idea, mixed execution. Stage two was the highlight. The music there was genuinely good—warmer, more intimate, and it felt alive. That said, a friendly heads-up: the walkway between areas is made of stepping stones, paired with blinding lights. Whether intentional or not, it’s a near-perfect booby trap for anyone a couple of drinks deep. Genius design if the goal is crowd-based slapstick. Stage one didn’t really land. It felt cold, unfinished, and a bit hollow. The stretch tent would benefit massively from a starlight canopy or anything other than a stark white void—it drained the atmosphere instead of building it. The sound system added to that feeling: too much pressure in the speakers, a cold resonance that pushed into the crowd rather than wrapping around it. Stage two, while smaller, initially felt about four degrees warmer—instantly more human. That illusion disappeared once you clocked that you’re essentially dancing inside a cage in the forest. Interesting concept, slightly claustrophobic reality. The speakers were undersized, which forced the DJ into the red at one point (credit where it’s due: it was corrected within minutes). Lighting in parts was overly direct when it should’ve been calming and immersive. Overall, it was an enjoyable evening. It’s genuinely nice to see something different happening on the island, and the ambition is there. But the pricing raised eyebrows. Entry at 500 baht felt hard to justify given the uneven sound delivery. Water at 40 baht for a tiny bottle, served without a glass, didn’t help. Toilets at the back of a bus and no cold towels available—even for purchase—felt like missed open goals. Cold cloths are an easy win. Absolute game-changer in this climate. In short: strong concept, flashes of brilliance, but execution needs tightening. With better sound balance, warmer staging choices, and a bit more care for crowd comfort, Electric Forest Samui could be something truly special. Right now, it’s a promising draft—not the final mix."
> **- Luke Pol-in (3/5/5)**

> "My favorite location in Samui. Charming, inviting and such a great line up. If you’re in Samui-a must experience"
> **- Anna Elise Buchter (5/5/5)**

> "A unique place for Thailand, and even more so for the island. Charming atmosphere and stylish sound at parties. I am glad that there is a party culture here and, as a rule, there are no overly drunk people. The gloss!"
> **- AXIMM NOOM (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/electric-forest-art-park-1.jpg','062 974 1756','57, 1 Moo1, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifx90024q8xdg1rcf50m','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.597+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.597+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/electric-forest-art-park-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/electric-forest-art-park-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5390569958952415478',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('elephant-jungle-sanctuary','standard','cmr07igfj009aq8xd8ty052tb','Elephant Jungle Sanctuary','## Top Reviews
> "Absolutely incredible place. You can see how well taken care of these elephants are. You can feed them and delicately touch them if they allow you too, nothing is really forced. I saw the elephants playing with the staff and I could see how much they like them. You can learn so much being there. Price - 900 baht, that includes feeding and spending as much with animal as you wish to. I’ve visited other sanctuaries and they were also nice but liked this one the most. I highly recommend the visit, especially that you support the sanctuary in this way. Each elephants needs 200kg food daily so they are not that easy to take care of. They do an amazing job there 🤍"
> **- Veronica Bielik (5/5/5)**

> "We had a completely amazing morning on the feed and shower with elephants experience booked via GetYourGuide.  The experience was fantastic from start to finish. After a short introduction, we went to feed the elephants with plenty of opportunities for photos along the way. We also learned a lot about the elephants and their care, which made the experience even more special. After a quick snack and water break, it was time for the shower — and wow, we did not appreciate just how wet you get! Definitely wear a swimming costume for this part.  Afterwards, it was time to head back. The only downside was feeling a little rushed by the driver while drying off and getting changed after washing the elephants.  Overall, it was an incredible experience. The staff clearly care deeply about the elephants, and it’s absolutely worth taking the time to do. We loved it and would 100% recommend it!"
> **- Jeff 95 (5/5/5)**

> "The elephant sanctuary was really touching. I loved seeing the elephants in good hands without being mistreated or used for entertainment. These were rescued elephants from circuses and riding camps.  At this sanctuary you can only feed and gently interact with the elephants without causing them harm while also supporting the sanctuary through the ticket fees. They have 7 elephants and all of them seemed very well taken care of.  Thank you for rescuing these animals. I hope you’ll be able to rescue even more in the future and that elephant riding and exploitative activities in Thailand will eventually be banned. So much love for the elephants 😍😍😍🐘🐘🐘❤️❤️❤️🙏🙏🙏"
> **- Dale De Dios (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elephant-jungle-sanctuary-1.jpg','099 295 4551','141/53 Moo 3, ตำบล แม่น้ำ อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://elephantjunglesanctuary.com/samui/','["Monday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.599+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.599+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elephant-jungle-sanctuary-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elephant-jungle-sanctuary-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4879847892853194465',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('elite-fight-center','standard','cmr07igfl009bq8xdz0mlhvm4','Elite Fight Center','## Top Reviews
> "Elite Fight Center Koh Samui is easily one of the best training spots on the island! I spent time on both the functional fitness side and in the fight gym, and the experience was awesome. It’s the perfect setup if you want to combine high-level combat sports training with a serious strength and conditioning routine. • Functional Fitness: The area is well-equipped with everything you need for a versatile workout, from weights to space for dynamic movement. • Fight Gym: The atmosphere is electric and professional, making it a great environment to sharpen your skills or get into fighting shape. Whether you''re a local or just visiting Samui, this place is top-tier. Highly recommend it!"
> **- Sasha Gurevich (5/5/5)**

> "If you''re staying in Koh Samui and want to take boxing lessons with professional fighters, this is the gym you should sign up for. It’s definitely worth your money. The gym is clean and well-maintained, and the staff are very respectful and friendly. They are always willing to help and guide you whenever you have questions. Truly the best gym!"
> **- Moaad El Makkaoui (5/5/5)**

> "Super gym! Came here for 3 classes (muay thaï, hyrox and mma) and each one was very good! Trainers are super positive and helpful. They had a promotion with free classes before the high season so my friends and I took advantage of it. The gym is clean and the girls at the reception are the sweetest. I definitely recommand coming here for classes!"
> **- Cloé Gernaey (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elite-fight-center-1.jpg','081 882 8402','202 B Chaweng Beach Rd, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.elitefightcentersamui.com/','["Monday: 7:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifuo0015q8xdfahzrsp4','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.601+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.601+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elite-fight-center-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elite-fight-center-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15862815122932629692',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('elite-gym-and-fitness','standard','cmr07igfm009cq8xdpkj9kt98','Elite Gym And Fitness','## Top Reviews
> "Excellent gym! You can tell the owner truly loves the place — nothing is missing. The hammers are a dream, all types of barbells are available, and it’s a pleasure to train here. Only the ellipticals squeak a bit. Entry is 350 baht for a single visit. I’ve been to much worse gyms on the island at the same price. The staff at the entrance is very pleasant, and the people training here are among the most attractive I’ve seen anywhere in the world"
> **- Eva Gur (4/5/5)**

> "Solid gym with everything you need to get a good workout in. The equipment selection is great and there’s even a nice separate room for stretching, yoga, or mobility work, which I really appreciated. Overall, it’s a good space to train and easy to get a full session in. The only downside is that the drop-in rate is quite overpriced for what you get."
> **- Grace Chizawsky (4/5/5)**

> "Paid about 350thb for a day pass. Little bit on the pricey end but they also offer a locker and towel for a 100tbh deposit which you get back, and was super handy for storing your stuff. Good range of equipment, from pin loaded, plated loaded, cables and dumbbells. Some sections of the gym lack a bit of lighting. But overall good space to workout in and we would recommend it."
> **- Jeff (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elite-gym-and-fitness-1.jpg','062 150 3841','202, Chaweng Beach Rd, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.elitegymsamui.com/','["Monday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 6:30 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifuo0015q8xdfahzrsp4','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.602+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.602+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elite-gym-and-fitness-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elite-gym-and-fitness-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16390639880641669072',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('elixir-beach-club','standard','cmr07igfo009dq8xd1xdwdszo','Elixir Beach Club','## Top Reviews
> "This is an absolutely enchanting spot where you can truly escape the island’s hustle and bustle. The beach is beautiful, intimate, and secluded, offering a stunning view of the nearby island. The food is exceptional, and the roasted chicken is, without a doubt, the best I''ve ever tasted. With soothing music and a laid-back atmosphere, it’s the perfect place to relax and recharge 💗"
> **- Katerina B (5/5/5)**

> "Very unassuming and chilled out seaside bar and restaurant. Small but very friendly crowd of locals and expats and there was a lovely relaxed atmosphere. The owner and his wife both took the time to introduce themselves and chat with us which we appreciated. There is seating inside the restaurant or on the beach and they have a separate bar area showing sports. There were a lot of dogs lounging around which may put some customers off but as my wife and I are both dog lovers this just enhanced the homely family vibe.  The informal atmosphere did not prepare us for the food which was genuinely fantastic. I had the grilled white snapper with the mango salad and chips (nice and chunky) and it was delicious. Wifey ate the seafood salad and we both had the exact same dish on our second visit. They also do Sunday roasts here but we missed it this time round."
> **- Mbr (4/5/5)**

> "Love this place!  It has a cool, local, beachy vibe with friendly staff and amazing food.  The dishes were so tasty, authentic and generous in size, at great prices.  We came for happy hour, stayed for dinner and enjoyed the most beautiful sunset.  The owner is an awesome guy who made us feel so welcomed and made sure we were happy with everything.  Highly recommend this great beach bar."
> **- Margaret Paul (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elixir-beach-club-1.jpg','099 259 7422','30/6 หมู่ที่ 5 Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07igdj008fq8xdhc2mye6x','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.604+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.604+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elixir-beach-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/elixir-beach-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=7025395141267361792',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('emporio-caff','standard','cmr07igfr009eq8xd7k31o008','Emporio Caffé','## Top Reviews
> "Omg. Best Italian food we have had in 2 months travelling. And the chef / owner is actually Italian (which is when you know it’s good). We both went for Arrabbiata and it’s one of the nicest I’ve ever had (and I’ve had a few)! The garlic bread was also to die for, the bread was freshly homemade bread. It is more than some other local Thai restaurants but you get that with all western food. This one wasn’t really expensive and 10/10 would recommend!"
> **- Beth (5/5/5)**

> "So yeah, as expected from the reviews the food was really good. We ordered Carbonara and the special Bruschetta with buffalo mozzarella. The Carbonara was very rich with lovely flavour from the guanciale and the creamy sauce and parmesan. The bruschetta was divine, packed with so much flavour and crunchiness of the beautiful bread, just perfect. Both dishes were working very well together as of the richness of the pasta dish and the freshness of the bruschetta. Absolutely beautiful. Service was also great, very polite staff, very sweet. Definitely worth trying and give it a go."
> **- Krasimira Valkanova (5/5/5)**

> "A Taste of Italy in Lamai – Unmissable!  During our one-week stay in Lamai, we found ourselves returning to Emporio Caffé Samui three times – that alone should speak volumes. This charming little spot instantly transported us to Italy with its warm ambiance and truly authentic flavors.  I had the Carbonara twice – it was so good I couldn’t resist a repeat – and the Amatriciana, which was just as delicious. The pasta was perfectly cooked, the sauces rich and flavorful, and everything had that homemade Italian touch that’s so hard to find. My husband tried the Lasagna, which he absolutely loved, and the Antipasto misto, a beautiful, well-balanced starter full of quality ingredients.  To finish, I had an affogato, and it was the perfect way to end the meal – simple, bold, and authentically Italian.  Chef Alessandro clearly pours his heart into every dish, and the hospitality matched the food – warm, personal, and passionate. If you’re in Koh Samui and craving real Italian cuisine, Emporio Caffé is a must. We’ll be dreaming of it until our next visit!"
> **- Pandy TheCat (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/emporio-caff-1.jpg','062 235 4798','หมู่ที่ 3, 131/2 Thanon Had Lamai, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.instagram.com/emporiocaffesamui?igsh=Nm50b3J4anFtb3I5&utm_source=qr','["Monday: 5:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 5:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 5:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 5:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 5:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 5:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:11.607+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:11.607+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/emporio-caff-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/emporio-caff-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10358565915438234054',NULL,NULL);
