INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kanda-spa','standard','cmr07igqp00e1q8xdejh85zl5','Kanda Spa','## Top Reviews
> "I got a coconut oil massage and it was amazing the masseuse was incredible, very relaxing long strokes instead of stretching like a Thai massage, went with a friend and we got a private room for both of us which was nice. They had massage beds with a hole for the face which I loved since you don’t always get them in Thailand and the other ones make my neck uncomfortable. Would definitely recommend!"
> **- Vania Medel (5/5/5)**

> "We had a great Thai massage and were very satisfied. The therapists were experienced and professional. I’d definitely recommend this place!"
> **- Enroutee_ (5/5/5)**

> "Meow was my massage therapist and she was wonderful. Very professional, with good English, and she fully respected my request for a soft massage, with extra attention to the head and face.  The place is very clean and peaceful, and the massage room feels calm and relaxing. Soft background music plays during the treatment. Even if there is another person nearby, the space is well separated by curtains, and there is no noise or talking from the therapists, which I really appreciated.  The massage ends with a lovely herbal tea served outside, a nice finishing touch. I paid 400 baht for a one-hour oil massage, and it was excellent value for the quality of the experience."
> **- Marion Athané (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kanda-spa-1.jpg','064 423 2629','79/28 kanda massage Tambon Ko Pha-ngan, Amphoe Ko Pha-ngan, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84280, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/KandaMassage/','["Monday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM","Tuesday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM","Wednesday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM","Thursday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM","Friday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM","Saturday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM","Sunday: 9:30 AM – 11:30 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.001+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.001+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kanda-spa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kanda-spa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13152579336149193707',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kankaew-verjus-design','standard','cmr07igqr00e2q8xdir62nfdw','Kankaew - Verjus - Design','## Top Reviews
> "A very reputable Shop, art, construction and design. The owner is good and I had wonder experience with them in terms of life, propertybabd company ownership and integration into the beautiful island of Koh Samui"
> **- Emmanuel Chibuike Oguejiofor (Shaka) (5/5/5)**

> "Kankaew Verjus Design is a contemporary and designer furniture store on the island of Koh Samui. It showcases furniture from renowned designers such as Le Corbusier, Philippe Starck, Verner Panton, and many others.  It also features contemporary home decor, an art gallery, an architecture and construction office, a restaurant, and a co-working space.  It is located on the roadside in Hua Thanon."
> **- Bernie Samui (5/5/5)**

> "Located near the K.O.B. cafe in Hua Thanon, this boutique is very attractive, featuring high-quality contemporary designer furniture.  The owner is a top-rated interior designer.  Further back of the boutique is the "
> **- Instant Lydie (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kankaew-verjus-design-1.jpg','+66897281947','C2VF+GJ5, Koh Samui, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://kankaewverjusdesign.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifpz0001q8xd0aml2ucx','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.003+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.003+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kankaew-verjus-design-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kankaew-verjus-design-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kankaew-verjus-design-3.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kankaew-verjus-design-4.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17604308857770275674',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kanok-buri-resort','standard','cmr07igqx00e3q8xdcxbqqrz4','Kanok Buri Resort','## Top Reviews
> "“Rooms are nice, reception staff is terrible ” The reception staff is terrible. Had we not already paid for the room, we would have turned around and walked out. The girl at the counter was incredibly rude, she had a nasty attitude before I even said anything to her. No hello, no welcome to Kanok Buri Resort. Nothing, just a “give me your passport”. I showed her my Agoda booking while looking for my passport and she snapped at me again asking for my passport, it hadn’t even been 20 seconds. I gave her my passport, my Thai pink card and my daughter’s Thai pink card and my husband’s Thai ID. Then she tried to charge me extra for my daughter even though their policy stated that 12 and under are free. She said it was 4 and under, I showed her the hotel’s website and their policy. She still tried to argue, even though she was looking right at it. She tried to insist that my daughter was 12, even though she was holding my daughter’s Thai pink card with her age clearly displayed. She also started yelling at me to make sure the sitcom was turned any lower than 22. I told her 22 is cold enough, I usually keep it at 25 at home anyways. Then she screamed at me again about not going lower than 22.  This lady was a nightmare, she should not be in any position where she’s dealing with customers. She’s 100% rude and unprofessional. Finally, another staff person came out and told the girl that she was wrong about trying to charge extra for my daughter. She charged my daughter for an extra breakfast, I didn’t even care at that point. After that, I had zero desire to even stay at this hotel. I’ve never felt so unwelcome anywhere in my life, especially where I am a paying customer. We stayed in one of the private plunge pool suites. The room was ok, but as I said, I already felt very uncomfortable in the hotel and at that point, I just wanted to go home. The breakfast wasn’t very good, but the staff that worked the breakfast area were very nice. We live in Koh Phangan, but have to come to Samui quite often for things we can’t get on the other island. We will not be staying at this hotel again. There are plenty of other, nicer hotels that make people feel welcome when they stay. I have included photos of their policy for children staying in rooms and another review, where the child was not charged extra for breakfast."
> **- Devon Geddes (1/5/5)**

> "We booked the private pool villa (not tropical, the other). We stayed in 708 and it was a great pleasure.  The entryway towards the villa is filled with beautiful tropical flowers and plants. The villa intself had a ring, was lockable and had a sign „clean up / do not disturb“ - I found that very helpful and discrete.  Inside, we had a wonderful pool which was refreshing in the summer heat, two pool loungers with a parasol. And a table with two seats under a pagoda. Twice a day - and on request - the pool had a little waterfall. The pool was not for swimming and was quite flat, but if you sat down inside the pool you could get your whole body in.  The room itself was nice and pretty, bedroom had an AC. Bathroom did not but I’ve never missed it.  The beach was really beautiful, super clear water and not at all crowded. You can see a really beautiful sunset there. The included breakfast was okay, you get toast and Marmelade, fruits, sausages, fresh eggs.  I would definitely go there again and the price-quality-relation was great.  Could easily order grab for food and groceries or walk by foot."
> **- frvrsummerle (5/5/5)**

> "Quirky set up,  situated in palms with walkways around. Breakfast good but other food average. Shut the bar early every night.  Not suitable for anyone with mobility problems,  too many steps,  no railings/banisters.  Small pool"
> **- Philip Leaver (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kanok-buri-resort-1.jpg','077 914 444','84 หมู่ที่ 2 Tambon Lipa Noi, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'https://kanokburihotel.com/th/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.009+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.009+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kanok-buri-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kanok-buri-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16728981569462042401',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kapuhala','standard','cmr07igr100e4q8xd1nkfss1u','Kapuhala','## Top Reviews
> "We had an amazing stay at Kapuhala Koh Samui, and everything exceeded our expectations. We stayed in one of the farmhouses, which offered beautiful views and plenty of space for a couple. The accommodation was very clean and comfortable.  The service was outstanding, both the staff and owners were incredibly accommodating, friendly, and always happy to help. The food was exceptional: entirely plant-based, beautifully prepared, and absolutely delicious. You can really see the care and effort the chef puts into every dish. We also attended the New Year’s Eve dinner, which was a fantastic experience from start to finish.  The facilities are top-notch. We used the gym several times and found it well equipped, and we made the most of the infinity pool with its breathtaking sea views.  What truly sets Kapuhala apart, though, is its ethical approach. Beyond serving healthy vegan food, they actively rescue animals and give back to the local community. This made our stay even more meaningful and perfectly aligned with the way we like to travel. We would absolutely stay here again :)"
> **- Luisa Bruce (5/5/5)**

> "Kapuhala is a heaven in Samui. Elevated up in the hill allows one to enjoy absolute tranquility minutes away from the bustling streets and beaches. The infinity pool is one of the best I’ve experienced with views to match. The tented accommodation is comfortable and well appointed with a scenic surrounding wodden deck. Breezes flow but there is AC for sleeping cool and mosquitoes free. Overall the absolute reset that we needed and only sorry we didn’t find this gem earlier. Last but not least wonderful staff to look after every single need. Will be coming back."
> **- G R (5/5/5)**

> "Took my bf there for his birthday & had the best experience. Beautiful location overlooking Samui, mountains, ocean & with an infinity pool. Service was incredible, especially from Arthur who talked us through the tasting menu which I highly recommend and he made the experience feel incredibly special. Food was delicious, plant based which catered for us and well worth the money. Staff sang happy birthday to my partner, & took a Polaroid picture with of us with a signed card which was lovely! Highly recommend! Will definitely be back here for the whole experience. A must try place whilst in Samui! Thank you so much to Arthur and the staff, we will see you soon!"
> **- Shemara Clifton (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kapuhala-1.jpg','095 308 6978','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.kapuhalasamui.com/','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 9:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 9:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 9:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 9:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 9:30 AM – 8:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ig5c0051q8xdykrbexft','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.013+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.013+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kapuhala-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kapuhala-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5951557919266817357',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('karma-beach-club','standard','cmr07igr400e5q8xdu2kkq101','Karma Beach Club','## Top Reviews
> "Breakfast and food are typical hotel standard — nothing special. We stayed for three days without breakfast before, and that was a much better option, as there are many excellent breakfast spots in town. The hotel’s Pad Thai was worse than any street version, even those costing around 70 baht.  There are definitely too many outside guests, which makes the place very crowded. Jet skis operate constantly along the beach, making it difficult to relax, and we were even afraid to swim or float on an inflatable mattress because they ride very close to the shore.  We came to this hotel to relax, but instead we found crowds during the day and an atmosphere full of show-off type guests."
> **- Kuba (1/5/5)**

> "We went there on our anniversary and we booked in advance. The Manager Mr. Vincent managed to give us a very nice table by the beach and a curated name on the table. It was so lovely and romantic. The food is amazing. The wine is perfect. Thanks to him for creating such a memorable night for us!"
> **- Kanokkorn Lamlert (5/5/5)**

> "The beach club is a Stunning hidden gem well worth visiting! Super attentive staff keeping an eye on guests every need, Aom was my waiter for the day. Cosy ambience with seating area around the pool and on the beach, cool infinity pool with shallow part for the minors. Plus for the live guitar performance 👏🏼"
> **- Fredrik Svanstrom (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-beach-club-1.jpg','065 410 5211','182 3, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.karma-resort.com/dining/','["Monday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 7:30 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.016+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.016+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-beach-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-beach-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13709490064158071370',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('karma-deli','standard','cmr07igr700e6q8xda9yt2y83','Karma Deli','## Top Reviews
> "This place is very good, and affordable. We did not expect much bc of it being in the corner of a very busy street in fisherman’s Village. Happy to report that we are very satisfied customers. The appetizer of mussels heaping out of a giant bowl piled high, and deep with a delish sauce for dipping warm bread. The chicken Milanese was generous and the sauce was pretty good. Steak Bavet…was delish and generously portioned. Service was attentive but not intrusive. Music had me dancing in my seat. We appreciated a fun night on the town.  Pic of mussels was taken after we came up for air and realized how fantastic they were!"
> **- Tif M. (5/5/5)**

> "A taste of Europe in Fisherman’s Village  If you’re in Koh Samui and looking for a break from Thai food, Karma Deli in Fisherman’s Village is definitely worth a visit.  We’ve had the pleasure of dining here several times, and the quality has been consistently outstanding.  From a perfectly crafted brioche perdue to a tenderloin with spinach, or a beautifully arranged meat & cheese platter paired with a good rosé – every dish delivers.  The restaurant is spotless and thoughtfully designed, creating a relaxed and welcoming atmosphere. A special mention goes to Joy, a lovely Thai lady whose warm, attentive, and genuinely caring service truly elevates the entire experience.  If you’re craving something different and want to enjoy high-quality European cuisine, Karma Deli is the place to be.  Fisherman’s Village, Koh Samui  Kurz gesagt: Top Qualität, super Service (Joy 💛) und perfekte Abwechslung zu Thai Food."
> **- Walke_Travel (5/5/5)**

> "Don’t let the Deli part of the name fool you.  This is not a deli.  This place is a true high quality restaurant.  The French inspired food menu has a very good variety.  The service is welcoming, friendly and professional.  The corner location has a good breeze so it’s not hot while you are dining.  The ambiance is laid back but classy.  They play good music that is not too loud (during lunch). The food is incredibly delicious.  You can tell they use high quality and fresh ingredients.  If you are looking for a break from Thai food and a more casual upscale experience try this restaurant."
> **- Vu Tran (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-deli-1.jpg','091 821 3150','25, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.karma-deli.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 10:30 PM"]','cmr07ifs5000eq8xdeu148200','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.019+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.019+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-deli-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-deli-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=2543938471145966880',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('karma-resort-samui','standard','cmr07igra00e7q8xde7nud6ni','Karma Resort Samui','## Top Reviews
> "We are staying in a 3 bedroom villa. Each bedroom is having an outdoor bathroom which is spacious and very comfy. The rooms are big and stylish and offering privacy. The outdoor space of the villa is large and offers a big pool and outdoor kitchen & barbie. Kitchen is fully equiped and we had already 2 cooking sessions. The atmosphere of the villa is cozy and relaxing and offers 100% privacy. Room service and staff is super friendly and brings the brekkie in the morning, which you order easily by whatsapp the evening before. The choice of breakfast is great and portions are far enough incl juice and coffee, tea. Restaurant offers international food (Pizza etc) besides Thai Food. Prices are absolutely reasonable ( of course street food is cheaper) but here you get full service, big portions, nice view. Beach is cleaned every day and sunbeds are always available. Sand is extremely nice as it is not the fine sand and the water is shallow to walk in. There is nothing to complain, one of our best stays in Thailand so far. Outside there is a brand new 7Eleven in 300m and a brand new karting track 500m. Additionally plenty of street food bars, excellent massage places and a cat coffee in short walking distance."
> **- Sven Waldhaus (5/5/5)**

> "Beautifully designed and stylish hotel with stunning rooms. We loved the village-style layout of the complex and the sleek design. Really couldn’t fault anything here! Staff was overall very friendly and attentive, and the quality of the food was very good. However, there were a few minor details which could do with some improvement. The gym is very small and could be better equipped. After we’d settled our final bill, we were presented with additional charges for something which had been overlooked. This was a genuine mistake and is no big deal as such, but the member of staff didn’t extend us the courtesy of apologising for what was their mistake. We also found it inappropriate to see a senior member of staff smoking whilst working behind the bar. The sun loungers on the beach are very comfortable , but could have been spaced apart a bit more. And finally, this hotel should in my opinion be an adults only hotel, simply because the facilities are not really suitable for families. The pool area is rather small and there is no separate kids pool, which made it feel very crowded when there were a couple of families with kids. Overall, a truly beautiful hotel in a good location, but in some areas more attention to detail would be advantageous."
> **- Barbara Dietrich (4/5/5)**

> "In February 2026 we held my daughter and son in law''s wedding at the Karma Resort. Family and friends travelled from Australia, South Africa, the USA, etc. to attend the wedding. The families and many of the guests stayed at the Karma Resort. The wedding itself was magical, with the Karma staff doing everything possible to work with the wedding planner to make not only the wedding but our entire stay at Karma memorable. The rooms were beautiful, especially with the outdoor showers. The staff were extremely friendly and helpful, the restaurant food was excellent and the location, within walking distance of Fisherman''s Village was very convenient. Overall, we were extremely happy that we chose the Karma Resort as the venue to host the wedding and the place for us to stay over the wedding period. Thank you to Yulia and the amazing staff."
> **- Sharon Lessing (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-resort-samui-1.jpg','077 427 111','182, 3, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.karma-resort.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.022+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.022+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-resort-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/karma-resort-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6304578270572845880',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('karma-resort-spa','standard','cmr07igrc00e8q8xdp8xqszda','Karma Resort Spa','## Top Reviews
> "We are staying in a 3 bedroom villa. Each bedroom is having an outdoor bathroom which is spacious and very comfy. The rooms are big and stylish and offering privacy. The outdoor space of the villa is large and offers a big pool and outdoor kitchen & barbie. Kitchen is fully equiped and we had already 2 cooking sessions. The atmosphere of the villa is cozy and relaxing and offers 100% privacy. Room service and staff is super friendly and brings the brekkie in the morning, which you order easily by whatsapp the evening before. The choice of breakfast is great and portions are far enough incl juice and coffee, tea. Restaurant offers international food (Pizza etc) besides Thai Food. Prices are absolutely reasonable ( of course street food is cheaper) but here you get full service, big portions, nice view. Beach is cleaned every day and sunbeds are always available. Sand is extremely nice as it is not the fine sand and the water is shallow to walk in. There is nothing to complain, one of our best stays in Thailand so far. Outside there is a brand new 7Eleven in 300m and a brand new karting track 500m. Additionally plenty of street food bars, excellent massage places and a cat coffee in short walking distance."
> **- Sven Waldhaus (5/5/5)**

