> **- darunwan pirom (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/khun-cho-accounting-1.jpg','063 615 5445','2/8 Tambon Lipa Noi, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifu0000zq8xdvll5tv7z','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.041+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.041+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/khun-cho-accounting-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/khun-cho-accounting-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16757887907261754054',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('khwan-beach-resort','standard','cmr07igrw00egq8xd2tl4zpz5','Khwan Beach Resort','## Top Reviews
> "We were very disappointed with our stay here. When we arrived, the accommodation was full of mosquitos to the point where it was almost impossible to relax or sleep comfortably. We immediately asked if we could receive a refund and stay elsewhere, but this was declined.  The property did provide mosquito spray and a bed net, however the net did not fully cover the bed and the spray made little difference. After being bitten constantly for two nights, we decided to leave early even though we had originally booked for four nights.  The location was also not ideal. The small town has very little in terms of restaurants, entertainment, or things to do, so you really need a moped or taxi to get anywhere worthwhile. On top of that, the road leading down to the accommodation was not very appealing and did not match what we would expect from a 4-star property. That said, the decoration and style of the rooms were nice and well presented.  Unfortunately, this stay did not meet our expectations and we would not return."
> **- Moya Fortune (1/5/5)**

> "Not a luxury hotel, extremely inhospitable staff.  We came here in May, and this tent style room is absolutely inhabitable in summer. The vents don''t close, so it never really cools down even when the AC is in overdrive. The bathroom is outdoor and the windows are just nets in the tent.  Secondly the ferries arrive in Koh Samui by around 11-12 noon. However the hotel doesn''t give you a room until 3pm. I arrived at the hotel feeling extremely overheated and dehydrated because of the heat. I told them I was feeling sick and needed help, however they didn''t even offer me a glass of water or ask me what''s wrong. We offered to pay for an early check in and had even requested it when we booked the hotel at first.  We had to wait in the afternoon sun without any help for hours until we got our room. I ended up falling quite sick and it ruined our whole trip. Their lack of help or hospitality or help felt quite inhuman."
> **- Nayanatara Tampi (1/5/5)**

> "Rooms and service were great. However, the AC in the rooms does not completely cool the rooms down. We are aware tents can be difficult to contain the coolness but fans or something extra should be provided to guest."
> **- Waseem Hussain (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/khwan-beach-resort-1.jpg','062 565 0796','67/61 Moo 1, 67, 61 ตำบล แม่น้ำ Ko Samui, Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.khwanbeachresort.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: 12:00 AM – 11:59 PM","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.044+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.044+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/khwan-beach-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/khwan-beach-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=14426959918150199743',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kiddie-garden-nursery-preschool','standard','cmr07igry00ehq8xdknpvs7l7','Kiddie Garden Nursery & Preschool','## Top Reviews
> "We reached Kiddie Garden by a recommendation of friends, and yet, it was absolutely a good surprise to us. My 2 years old daughter went for only 3 weeks, and she got comfortable quickly. There are several nannies taking care of everything the kids need, so every child gets treated. This place was the reason we stayed so long in Samui. I highly recommend it!!"
> **- tal nahari (5/5/5)**

> "Thank you Jenny and all teaches for taking such a great care of Anna.  Strongly recommended. The teachers are very attentive, they have a lot of activities with kids. We will come back!!!"
> **- Nina Fojtova (5/5/5)**

> "We absolutely love Kiddie Garden, it is a fantastic nursery that is an absolute pleasure to send our children to. Jenny and all of her staff are so lovely and are amazing with all of the children. Our 1 year old and 4 year old both love going to school there and it has been so lovely to see how much they enjoy it.  We would highly recommend Kiddie Garden to anyone thinking about sending their children to nursery."
> **- Leo Winspear (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kiddie-garden-nursery-preschool-1.jpg','063 085 4244','141, Chaweng, 30, Tambon Bo Put, Koh Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://kiddiegardensamui.wixsite.com/website','["Monday: 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM","Thursday: 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM","Friday: 8:30 AM – 5:00 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifwy001zq8xdppgaj2cs','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.046+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.046+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kiddie-garden-nursery-preschool-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kiddie-garden-nursery-preschool-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=11030614364881656869',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kidomo-kids-club','standard','cmr07igs100eiq8xduhtxz6h3','Kidomo Kids Club','## Top Reviews
> "This was our favorite kids club during our 4 week stay on the island. The small space is packed to the brim with toys, games, books, art & crafts etc., all quality stuff in good condition, and organized so as not to suffocate the space. The kids (2.5 and 6 years old) had endless options! The staff was extremely warm and welcoming, and functioned pretty much like kindergarten teachers, engaging with the children, finding things for them to do and sitting down with them for activities. The owner is also lovely and welcoming, and basically we just got the feeling that everyone here loves hanging out with kids and making human connections. Thank you for supporting our family while we were far away from home :)"
> **- Shira Elazary (5/5/5)**

> "My family and I found Kidomo a few months ago and since then my 4 year old daughter keeps asking about going. It''s a beautiful little kids club, intentionally set up with all the things kids like without being too intrusive and overstimulating. Patricia, the owner, is great and really passionate about creating a space where kids can come together, be creative and explorative, and simply play. The rest of the staff, a few Thai women, are also lovely and as a parent I feel completely safe knowing my child is well taken care of.  Next door to Kidomo is our favourite cafe and there''s also a few good food places which give you, as a parent, a great place to be while your kids are having the best time.  I recommend Kidomo highly to anyone living on or coming to the island looking for a kids club with a soft, gentle and loving environment.  Thank you, Patricia and the team at Kidomo, for your beautiful care."
> **- Niki Lundberg (5/5/5)**

> "Kidomo Kids Club  is an absolutely amazing place for children! From our very first visit, we felt like we were among friends, and it’s all thanks to the incredible Patrycja – the owner with a huge heart and a true passion for what she does.  Patrycja puts her whole heart into this place, taking care of every detail and creating an atmosphere where kids feel happy and parents feel at ease. We had the great pleasure of organizing our son’s birthday party there, and it was the best decision we could have made! Everything was perfectly planned, with fantastic attractions, wonderful care, and endless smiles on the children’s faces – that says it all.  Kidomo Kids Club is a space full of joy, warmth, and amazing fun. We highly recommend it to all parents looking not just for a playroom but for a place where their children will truly be happy! Patrycja, thank you for everything – you’re doing an incredible job!"
> **- KS Gold Sport (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kidomo-kids-club-1.jpg','091 393 2000','26, 31, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.kidomokids.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: Closed","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 12:00 – 5:00 PM"]','cmr07ifwy001zq8xdppgaj2cs','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.049+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.049+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kidomo-kids-club-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kidomo-kids-club-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9254513256197423735',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kimpton-kitalay','standard','cmr07igs300ejq8xdgr89ozkv','Kimpton Kitalay','## Top Reviews
> "Good value for your money. I’ve stayed at other resorts on the island but Kimpton is one I’d be willing to repeat. The sea view room was spacious, clean and comfortable. Nice balcony to watch the sunrise. The service is spectacular and the food on premise is good enough you don’t need to venture out if you don’t want to. Some days we didn’t.  I also like that you can walk to your room and not need a buggy to get there.  I went in June and it was not crowded.  The ocean is a bit rockier here compared to where I stayed last time."
> **- LPN (5/5/5)**

> "Had a 4 nights stay and so memorable one. Very beautiful location with infinity pool and beach access. Great breakfast variety with so welcoming staff. Chef Deepak and rest of the team did a great job with the breakfast and other events. Poolside service was also very quick. Complimentary evening refreshments were also a highlight. Would love to come back 🙏🏼"
> **- Gurbir Sidhu (5/5/5)**

> "Wish I could give 7/5 for service. The amount of kind touches, attentiveness, detail were above and beyond consistently. The top service hotel I have ever experienced. Consistently remembering my name when seeing me out, and seemingly chomping at the bit to keep me from being inconvenienced in even the smallest ways. I cannot express my appreciation and respect for the fantastic staff and their incredible attitude and outstanding service.  Place is very peaceful, and the on site restaurants are great - one Michelin recommended. Don''t expect a party, but this was low season. Also a little out of the way from the more happening areas which some may prefer, I don''t, but a reasonable sacrifice to have this experience. Booked with chase the edit and got the upgrade and $100 credit along with 4 drink vouchers due to ihg status."
> **- Tom A (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kimpton-kitalay-1.jpg','077 951 999','10, 79, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.kimptonkitalaysamui.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsv000nq8xdrwnu123q','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.051+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.051+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kimpton-kitalay-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kimpton-kitalay-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=1792967035450585232',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('king-lawyer','standard','cmr07igs600ekq8xd0nhodzfx','King Lawyer','## Top Reviews
> "My bank account was blocked because I exchanged my cryptocurrency into baht through my account. This often happens in Thailand. I turned to Mr. Wan for help. Unfortunately, I shared with him my concern that the police might accuse me of trading cryptocurrency without a license. Because I had heard that in Thailand the police, if they wish, can interpret everything the way they want, and the presumption of innocence does not exist there. He said it was possible but promised to help. His “help” dragged on for more than four months. He kept saying it was difficult to reach the police officer in charge of my case. Then he flew to Bangkok and claimed he had solved my problem, but later told me that I needed to give testimony again and that more money was required to handle my case. By that time, I had already realized that asking this lawyer for help was a mistake. I called the police myself, reached the right officer on the first try, flew to Bangkok, and resolved the entire issue in one meeting. My bank account was unblocked. Then the worst happened. I was suddenly charged with trading cryptocurrency without a license. No one had ever faced such charges before. Many foreigners exchange cryptocurrency, and at most their accounts get blocked. Then I remembered that during our very first meeting I had shared my concern with Mr. Wan. I suspect this did not happen without his involvement. Please be careful with him!"
> **- Ramil Nigma (1/5/5)**

> "1.	Thailand Litigation Service 2.	Legal counseling/Notaries/Notice 3.	 Legal cases counseling, and Civil cases/Criminal cases 4.	Juristic act and contract/ Apply to the court for administrator. 5.	Last will and testament. 6.	Litigation/Mediation/Authorization -	Civil cases -	Criminal cases -	Administrative cases -	Child, Juvenile and family cases -	Labor cases -	Bankruptcy cases -	Rehabitation -	Drug cases -	Petition for the return of a juristic person -	Appeal level/Supreme level -	New trail -	Execusion 7.	Business counseling -	Company set up -	Accounting - Closing financial statement -	Agent of Buying and Selling property Due diligence -	Reservation agreement/ Escrow account of the reservation deposit -	Arbitration"
> **- Chanannisa Sriya (5/5/5)**

> "Honest and reliable lawyers. Wan will go through and beyond to make sure you understand Thai law. Top quality"
> **- James (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/king-lawyer-1.jpg','063 894 1553','115 27 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.2,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.shorturl.asia/rEMYs','["Monday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifu0000zq8xdvll5tv7z','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.054+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.054+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/king-lawyer-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/king-lawyer-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9090600554470603860',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kings-garden-resort','standard','cmr07igs900elq8xdglr9h6qn','King''s Garden Resort','## Top Reviews
> "We decided to stay here for a week because of the owner''s exceptional kindness and warm hospitality. There are few adorable dogs on the property, and they truly made our stay special. As a dog lover, spending time with them was incredibly comforting and healing. Their affection brought so much joy to each day.  The room was cozy, comfortable, and felt like a home away from home. The beachfront location is amazing—you can enjoy beautiful sea views and the peaceful sound of the waves right from the property. It was the perfect place to relax, unwind, and reconnect with nature.  We also loved the Southern Thai breakfast options, which were delicious and gave us a chance to try authentic local flavors. Everything about our stay was relaxing, memorable, and filled with warmth. We would happily return and highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a peaceful beachfront getaway. ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐"
> **- Kathy Aiadaui (5/5/5)**

> "Thank you for saving our vacation!!! After we made a very poor research and choice with our initial holiday booked, we were super lucky to get a last minute cancellation availability here! Beautiful property with amazing staff and great breakfast. Very cosy family atmosphere with a lot of repeat and long stay clients. A well run - animal friendly- resort with the owner staying on property to ensure smooth operations. If you don''t need a pool for your vacation,  this is the best choice in Chaweng!!!"
> **- Hafen Koller (5/5/5)**

> "This is our sixth time at Kings Garden, which I suppose says everything. The resort, the location are perfect and the staff are absolutely incredible , from the cleaners to the gardeners, the breakfast crew and reception, they are all fantastic and incredibly friendly. The accommodation is perfect for a long or short stay close enough but far enough from the centre of Chewang. I cant recommend this place highly enough."
> **- Bruce Kermack (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kings-garden-resort-1.jpg','077 422 304','12 Chaweng Beach Rd, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.kings-garden-resort.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.057+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.057+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kings-garden-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kings-garden-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16966882197173150384',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kirikayan-boutique-resort','standard','cmr07igsh00emq8xd8p7np7rx','Kirikayan Boutique Resort','## Top Reviews
> "We absolutely loved our stay at Karikayan Resort! The place is wonderfully secluded, and the atmosphere is pure bliss. There’s a 7-Eleven and a small fruit shop just around the corner, so you can enjoy fresh fruit or grab some snacks any time you like.  The nightlife area is also nearby—about a 15-minute walk if you fancy an evening out. There are several local restaurants, tailors, and everything else you might need within easy reach. The resort itself isn’t large, which makes it feel cozy and peaceful, and the location is just perfect.  The beach is literally a 30-second walk away, and most of the time it was just us and maybe a handful of other people—so it really feels like your own private island.  Breakfasts were simple but satisfying: eggs cooked any way you like (scrambled, omelette, poached), with tomatoes, cucumbers, pasta or steamed vegetables, some cheese, and bread. Nothing fancy, but definitely enough to start your day well.  My only small suggestion to the management would be to add some shelves or cupboards for better storage in the rooms.  Overall, I totally enjoyed my two-week stay and would love to come back again. Highly recommended for anyone looking for a relaxing getaway and a taste of local culture."
> **- Galyna Seleznova (5/5/5)**

> "This hotel was lovely, nice clean rooms and comfortable beds. The sunbeds were super comfy and there was always enough. The lack of shade was a bit of an issue as i prefer to be in shade the whole time when im in a sunbed, i had to keep moving the umbrella which is normal of course but it was really heavy and the staff only helped me once as he said that he can’t keep helping me move it every hour, which was a shame. The hotel next door has lots of shade, i would have preferred to use their sunbeds and stayed here haha. The hotel itself is great, its nice and small so you get good service mostly, the breakfast was great for vegetarians and they have an egg station. Staff are super friendly."
> **- Nanda Hirani (5/5/5)**

> "Great hotel, lovely staff member and Yhi helped us to have a very smooth check in. It is out fifth time we staying here and absolutely love Kirikayan. Great location and easy for travelling to Central shopping centre and night market. Try opposite door restaurant which called Noi and perhaps best Thai food I ever had in whole Thailand 👌 Can not wait to come back here in Christmas"
> **- Mehrdad Vahabi (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirikayan-boutique-resort-1.jpg','077 413 888','หาดเฉวง Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.kirikayan.com/kirikayanboutique/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.065+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.065+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirikayan-boutique-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirikayan-boutique-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=1159619475900555468',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kirikayan-luxury-pool-villas','standard','cmr07igsl00enq8xdtlr6s41h','Kirikayan Luxury Pool Villas','## Top Reviews
> "i paid for a full-year rental at Kirikayan, which used to be a proper hotel before COVID and has now turned into some kind of low-effort residence/apartment complex. The price I paid was extremely high compared to the terrible quality of both the service and the apartment itself.  Since the day I arrived, I''ve had constant issues with the hot water: the heater (Leuleu?) only delivers cold water or barely lukewarm at best, and the water pressure is ridiculously weak. It''s been over a month now, and despite repeatedly reporting it, nothing has been properly fixed. They come, say "
> **- Asia Labs (1/5/5)**

> "The villa we are currently staying in has an acceptable layout, however, the facilities are clearly outdated.  What is most unacceptable to me is that the basic standard of cleanliness has not been met.  For example: •	Simply walking barefoot on the floor immediately leaves my feet completely black, which indicates the floor has not been properly cleaned for a long time; •	When opening the wardrobe, the clothes rail is covered in thick dust — wiping it once leaves visible dirt.  For a rental villa, regardless of its positioning or price range, basic cleanliness and hygiene are fundamental requirements, not optional.  Unfortunately, this standard has not been met, and this is the part I find most difficult to tolerate. I hope this issue will be taken seriously and that a clear solution can be provided as soon as possible."
> **- Bow (2/5/5)**

> "I paid for a full-year rental at Kirikayà. What used to be a decent hotel before COVID has turned into a poorly managed apartment/residence complex with very low standards.  The price I paid is outrageously high compared to the terrible quality of the service and the apartment itself.  Right from the start, major issues with the hot water: the heater (Leuleu?) only gives cold or barely warm water, and the pressure is extremely weak. More than a month later, despite reporting it almost daily, nothing has been properly fixed. They come, say “it’s done”, pretend it’s resolved every single day, but it’s exactly the same. They clearly take people for idiots.  There are at least 23 things broken or wrong in the apartment. I didn’t even complain about most of them because I’m an easy-going person and don’t ask for much.  But when I asked the staff for basic help (carrying a sofa from security to my unit), they immediately asked for extra money because “it’s not in their job”. Yet when it’s about fixing serious problems like hot water or pressure, they do nothing or just lie about having fixed it.  The staff does whatever they want — or nothing at all. Promises mean zero. “Yes yes it’s fixed” = still broken.  The owners/management are completely absent and don’t care about the residence. It’s pure neglect and messing people around.  I strongly do NOT recommend anyone to rent here at Kiri Cayenne. Save your money — the price is way too expensive for this level of lies, poor service, and total lack of care."
> **- So Close (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirikayan-luxury-pool-villas-1.jpg','077 332 299','Maenam Soi 1, Tambon Mae Nam, Maenam, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.kirikayan.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.069+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.069+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirikayan-luxury-pool-villas-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirikayan-luxury-pool-villas-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5542576548183264822',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kirin-spa','standard','cmr07igsn00eoq8xdirv28i5x','Kirin Spa','## Top Reviews
> "Extremely friendly and welcoming staff — truly some of the nicest people. I loved every part of the premises; it’s beautiful, peaceful, and very well designed in nature. The massage itself was very good and relaxing.  We booked a couple’s massage and also experienced the caves, natural spring areas, and body scrub treatments, which made the whole experience feel very complete and unique.  The only area I feel could be improved is hygiene standards in certain parts of the facility, which would make the experience perfect.  Overall, a wonderful experience and I would still recommend it for anyone looking for a relaxing spa day in nature."
> **- Ghada Mallah (4/5/5)**

> "We visited Tamarind Springs Samui as a wedding gift from our friends and chose the “Stoned on Samui” package — and it was absolutely worth it.  From start to finish, the experience was incredibly relaxing and thoughtfully curated. We really appreciated the no-phone policy, which allowed us to fully disconnect and enjoy the peaceful surroundings. It made the whole spa day feel even more special and immersive.  The treatments were amazing, and everything was beautifully set in nature. One thing to keep in mind is that there’s quite a bit of walking and stairs involved, so you do need to be reasonably fit. But honestly, it just adds to the charm of the place.  We loved every moment and would highly recommend it for a special occasion or a proper treat!"
> **- Zaza Meerveld (5/5/5)**

> "We had an absolutely wonderful experience at Tamarind Springs. We spent a beautiful afternoon immersed in nature, following a peaceful path through the forest that truly felt magical. The entire setting is unique, serene, and incredibly well integrated into the natural surroundings.  The spa itself is simply amazing and unlike anything we had ever seen before. The sauna carved directly into the rocks is something truly special – a one-of-a-kind experience that you won’t easily find elsewhere. It feels authentic, original, and perfectly in harmony with the forest. Without a doubt, the experience is worth every penny and absolutely justifies the price.  The massage was exceptional: deeply relaxing, professional, and perfectly executed. On top of that, all the staff were incredibly kind, welcoming, and attentive in every aspect, making us feel comfortable and well taken care of from start to finish.  This is not just a spa, but a complete experience in nature. Highly recommended for anyone looking for something unique, relaxing, and truly memorable.  Renato"
> **- Renato Rottmann (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirin-spa-1.jpg','085 926 4626','265, 1, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.tamarindsprings.com/','["Monday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.071+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.071+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirin-spa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kirin-spa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=363410939101283574',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('ko-samui-boat-charter','standard','cmr07igsq00epq8xdm3n461sq','Ko Samui Boat Charter','## Top Reviews
> "A fantastic all-day boat tour of the Koh Samui Ang Thong National Marine Park islands. Our tour guide Two was great, he was very approachable and spoke incredible English. We learnt a lot about the islands as well as being able to see so many of them. All soft drinks were included and there was no shortage available for everyone. Our group was about 25 people, which was ideal as it still felt personal but we had others to share the experience with. The food provided was fantastic, it was all cooked fresh on the boat and was some of the tastiest Thai food we had. They made sure to cater for everyone and provided plenty. The pick-up and drop off direct to our hotel, included in our ticket, worked smoothly without any issues. The additional activities of kayaking, snorkelling and going onto one the main islands to see the lagoon were well organised and managed. Certainly an experience that we would recommend as was great value and completely worth it."
> **- Hannah Price (5/5/5)**

> "⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️ Absolutely Perfect Day in Koh Samui!  We had an incredible day on this luxurious yacht — truly one of the highlights of our trip! The whole experience felt so exclusive and peaceful; we didn’t encounter a single other cruise the entire day, which made it feel like we had the ocean all to ourselves.  The kayaking was so much fun, and the snorkeling was simply breathtaking. I’ve visited many beautiful places, but the sheer amount and variety of fish and corals here blew me away.  The atmosphere on board was wonderfully relaxed and fun for everyone — we had kids and adults of all ages, and everyone had a fantastic time. Meeting and chatting with people from all over the world added to the charm and made the day even more special.  The crew was amazing — so friendly, attentive, and genuinely eager to make sure we were happy. They constantly checked in, served drinks, and made everything effortless for us.  And the food… wow! Everything was freshly prepared and absolutely delicious — we even got fresh fruit and ice cream! I had the best green curry of my entire two weeks in Thailand. We felt blissfully spoilt from start to finish.  If you want a truly special experience away from the tourist crowds, this tour is an absolute must-do."
> **- Tine Schafhauser (5/5/5)**

> "Lovely day out Got to see some buddha whales briefly. Facilities good, nice relaxing day. Good safety instructions, equipment and team watching you as you kayaked and snorkelled. Food and snacks  were nice. Staff very pleasent and attentive. Nice long relaxing day."
> **- S Hampson (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ko-samui-boat-charter-1.jpg','081 535 7768','404, 68, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://kosamuiboatcharter.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.074+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.074+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ko-samui-boat-charter-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/ko-samui-boat-charter-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=3475962376345482163',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kobori-sunset-view','standard','cmr07igss00eqq8xdz2qj6glh','Kobori Sunset View','## Top Reviews
> "As an island resident, I’m always on the hunt for new favorite spots, and Samui Kobori is a total standout! This is easily some of the best Japanese food I’ve tasted—everything was incredibly fresh and beautifully presented. ​We went for a sunset meal, and the atmosphere was perfect. Beyond the food, the staff are wonderful; they were so helpful and genuinely friendly throughout the evening. If you live on the island or are just visiting, you need to check this place out."
> **- moby (5/5/5)**

> "Reasonable pricing and yummy sushis. I have been here several times.  The restuarant is right by the sea.  Staffs are not the most service minded as you can see it was a little aggressive on serving miso soup, the soup spilled all the way down. Other than that everything was decent. Staffs are a little nicer (meaning neutral and not grumpy) when it isnt busy hours."
> **- Winter Ray (4/5/5)**

> "This is probably one of my favourite restaurants on the island of Samui.  It’s on the main road near the ferry terminal in Nathon.  It’s right on the water with an amazing sunset view.  They also have a vegetarian menu that makes me feel like I’m still eating sushi 😂. We have been coming here for 10 years now and have never had a bad meal.  The food is always fresh and the service is excellent.  All meals look amazing when they come out of the kitchen. They have fresh Wasabi and it is truly delicious, though a little hot.  Make sure you go at around the time of the sunset, it is truly a spectacular place to view it with the Ferries going in and out. Best sushi on the island in my opinion."
> **- Melissa JMK (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kobori-sunset-view-1.jpg','083 174 6530','310/19 Moo 3 Preedharad Road, Angthon, Koh Samui, Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.samuikobori.com/','["Monday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM","Tuesday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM","Wednesday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM","Thursday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM","Friday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM","Saturday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM","Sunday: 11:30 AM – 9:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig1h003iq8xdb1g9nifo','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.076+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.076+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kobori-sunset-view-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kobori-sunset-view-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13336131426781887092',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('koh-fit','standard','cmr07igsv00erq8xd35gpcn4m','Koh Fit','## Top Reviews
> "I‘ve already visited Fitkoh for the second time now and I‘m the biggest fan! It‘s the perfect place to spend some time in paradise and get fit at the same time (especially when travelling solo - you‘ll find friends immediately!). The staff is incredible, the food absolutely amazing (the even write down all the macros) and the gym as well as the Muay Thai area has everything you need. The coaches are fantastic. I worked on my pull up with the one and only Gareth and I had several PTs with the Muay Thai trainers (thanks to Cheng, Nick and Kob!) and all of them were great. Will come back!"
> **- Mira Bella Weingart (5/5/5)**

> "My one-month transformation program at Fitkoh was an excellent experience. I wasn’t an active person when I started, but the team was very accommodating and supportive from day one. Special thanks to my PT Ethan—he focused on proper conditioning from the start, helped correct my posture, form, and technique, and guided me steadily toward my goals in a very practical, result-oriented way.  The group classes were fun yet challenging, especially HIIT, Muay Thai, and Hyrox, which really helped build my strength and core. The yoga sessions with Yin were calming and deeply relaxing, providing the perfect balance to intense training.  The food was well-curated to match my fitness goals, and the restaurant staff were always welcoming and helpful. Fitkoh’s beach café and yoga venue are extremely calming and added a great sense of relaxation to the overall experience.  Overall, Fitkoh offers a focused yet relaxed environment with a strong, supportive community. I would definitely come back again. Thanks to the entire Fitkoh team and Ethan for the great support."
> **- jacob kurian (5/5/5)**

> "Had the most amazing week at fitkoh and did not want to leave. There was a variety of different classes to try and was a great opportunity to try new things. The location is beautiful only a few minutes walk to the beach, and some classes such as morning yoga are hosted there.  The fitkoh beach cafe was amazing, the setting was beautiful and the food was super healthy and tasty. All the staff are so attentive and really go the extra mile for you.  I really recommend my personal trainer Gareth, he was really encouraging and really helped me become more comfortable in the gym doing my own workouts."
> **- Keely Thomas (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/koh-fit-1.jpg','093 683 4920','32/8, Moo 5, Bantai, ตำบล แม่น้ำ อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.fitkoh.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifuo0015q8xdfahzrsp4','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.079+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.079+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/koh-fit-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/koh-fit-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12120514969356079630',NULL,NULL);
