INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kohabitat','standard','cmr07igth00ezq8xdzhcj6wyi','KoHabitat','## Top Reviews
> "i LOVED staying here. the vibe is leafy greens and dark woods and it’s just chef’s kiss. the bed is genuinely the softest i’ve had since being in Thailand and the dorm was really quiet at night. The owner is really friendly and helpful, she’ll wash, dry, fold and return your washing to you for 150thb (correct at time of writing) which is so convenient. I also had a nightmare of a journey so arrived quite late and frazzled but she was wonderful and chilled out about it which was so nice 😭. the hostel is about 20 min walk from fisherman’s village and there’s the big C super centre next door and 7-11’s also super close. Everything was clean and felt safe. Also omg the shower was brilliant, I almost cried."
> **- Verity Wilkinson (5/5/5)**

> "Rooms are very nice but there is not much space or things to do with the other people staying at the Hostel. The Lady owning the hostel is super friendly, speaks fantastic english and is very helpful. Location is not really good, as it is directly at the main road and the windows dont keep the sound out. Also you need the drive a while to get to the places you want to see at the Island, which results in very few visitors at the hostel during rainy season especially. Overall i enjoyed the stay."
> **- Oskar (4/5/5)**

> "Could have stayed longer, if I had the time. Very aesthetically pleasing inside and cozy. The bed was comfortable to which very seldom in hostels in Thailand. I love that there’s a basic equipped kitchen. They are located in the main road so everything is in a walking distance. The owner made my visit very easy with their knowledge of the island. She can hook you up with almost everything you need, may it be tours, motorbikes rental, taxi services, etc., It was a wonderful experience to find this hostel gem! Will stay again when I get back!"
> **- Maria Frias (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohabitat-1.jpg','065 957 1833','120/29, ตำบล บ่อผุด Bophut Koh Samui, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.101+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.101+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohabitat-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohabitat-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=7705545333153699702',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kohco-beach-restaurant','standard','cmr07igtj00f0q8xd9k6skjto','KOHCO Beach Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Such a gem!!! They have absolutely nailed it… the food is so good, not complicated, not pretentious, just good!! We had lunch and dinner few times and each time we were amazed by the quality and flavours. The service is very very good. Super attentive, knowledgeable and friendly. We really liked it and kept on coming back. Well done team for creating something truly special."
> **- Souraya Gyves (5/5/5)**

> "This place was a great vibe! My wife and I (mid 30s) are on our honeymoon and wanted a quick break from Thai Food. We had a great dinner (Pizza and Caprese). Service was great and so was the ambiance. It felt like we were in the Mediterranean for a bit."
> **- Ward Jones (5/5/5)**

> "Superb place for seafood! We spent several hours here enjoying a selection of seafood platters. Although all dishes were great, I particularly enjoyed the rainbow fish and the spicy calamari. On a more practical note, between 17:00 and 19:00 they offer a happy hour, with - among other things - promotions on some of their wines by the glass."
> **- Julius Lussenburg (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohco-beach-restaurant-1.jpg','094 912 3937','180, 5 ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.kohcobeach.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.103+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.103+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohco-beach-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohco-beach-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=509442688363252358',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('kohinoor-indian-restaurant','standard','cmr07igtm00f1q8xdmdpwcsi0','Kohinoor Indian Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Such a great place to eat in this area! The food is absolutely delicious with authentic Indian flavors, and the quality is really good. Every dish was well prepared and tasted fresh. The staff is friendly and welcoming, and the service is quick. The ambience is clean and comfortable, making it a nice spot to enjoy a proper Indian meal in Thailand. If you’re around this area and craving Indian food, you should definitely try this place. Highly recommended!"
> **- Shivendra K Jha (5/5/5)**

> "​The Food: The menu offers a perfect balance of classic favorites and rich, aromatic spices. The curries are perfectly seasoned—not just "
> **- Tarashna (5/5/5)**

> "Kohinoor in Koh Samui is an absolute gem! We loved the food so much that we ended up visiting twice. The Indian cuisine was authentic, flavorful, and easily the best we had on our Thailand trip. The service was excellent, and the owner’s warm, humble, and welcoming nature made the experience even more special. Highly recommend for anyone craving amazing Indian food in Koh Samui!"
> **- Ankita Sharma (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohinoor-indian-restaurant-1.jpg','084 063 8285','74 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 11:30 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.106+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.106+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohinoor-indian-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/kohinoor-indian-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10262032582213544849',NULL,NULL);
