INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('lek-tattoo','standard','cmr07igxa00gaq8xdtvkr4ihg','Lek Tattoo','## Top Reviews
> "I’ve been coming here many times, and it truly feels like home. The atmosphere is warm and welcoming like being surrounded by family and friends.  The tattoo artists are highly skilled, definitely among the top professionals, and you can truly trust their work. Everything is clean, hygienic, and safe, and the quality is consistently excellent.  Khun Kae, Khun Lek, P’Noo, Nong Ice, and the rest of the team are all incredibly kind and attentive. They genuinely care about every detail of their work, making the whole experience feel comfortable, personal, and special 🤍  Highly recommended! ❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥"
> **- Namtan RS (5/5/5)**

> "I got a 10×12 cm coloured nature‑themed tattoo from the master named himself “Boy”, and the result is beautiful (beyond my requested version). His skill shows in every detail, and his preparation work is meticulous and reassuring. The shop ambience is calm, and the indoor music helped me relax throughout the session. The whole experience felt professional, and the price is fair for the quality of the artwork and service."
> **- david frozz (5/5/5)**

> "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐  Amazing experience at LEK Tattoo Samui! The artist was professional, friendly, and very talented. The studio was clean and comfortable, and the attention to detail was outstanding. My tattoo turned out even better than I expected. Highly recommended for anyone looking for quality work in Koh Samui!"
> **- Kyaw Swar (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lek-tattoo-1.jpg','084 192 8266','14 50 หมู่ที่ 2 ตำบล บ่อผุด Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://instagram.com/lektattoothailand?igshid=OGQ5ZDc2ODk2ZA==','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07iftc000rq8xdiyhsa78o','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.238+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.238+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lek-tattoo-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lek-tattoo-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6959072291307654177',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('lets-eat','standard','cmr07igxd00gbq8xdvhk01ncp','Let’s Eat','## Top Reviews
> "Massive props. We hit Let’s Eat tonight and it absolutely smacked. From the moment we walked in the vibe was dialled: retro-rock posters, guitars on the wall, a bun as golden as the early evening light over the Pacific. The bun was buttery, pillowy and toasted just enough to hold the load without going soggy — a proper foundation. Then came the patty: char-crusted, juicy in the middle, beef flavour blasting like a BC summer campfire. The cheese pooled around the edges like molten lava and the pickles snapped with that briny pop you crave. Lettuce crisped, tomato sliced thick and ripe, onions with a bit of sting, each bite full of contrast.  The sauce was wicked — a smoky-sweet swirl that pulled the whole ensemble together, none of that weak-sock thing, but full throttle. Bacon? Check. Crispy, salty, maple-whispered. The build was rock-solid: two-hand job, but not a falling-apart mess. Napkin intensive? Maybe. Worth it? Abso-friggin-lutely.  We chatted, we laughed, we watched the burger disappear. Price point about ฿200-400 but felt like a steal given the quality. Staff were laid-back but on the ball — good service never killed the vibe. Post-burger we walked out full of that “wow, we found a gem” energy.  This place doesn’t just do burgers — they own burgers. It’s one of those eateries you’ll drop friends off at and brag about later. If you’re in the area and feeling like a cheat-meal done right, this is your go-to. End of story."
> **- MIke Armstrong (5/5/5)**

> "We love Let''s Eat. Amazing food and some of the best burgers in Lamai. Three fish and chips are also great, as is the spicy chicken sandwiches. Great atmosphere and very friendly owners and staff."
> **- Simon Walker (5/5/5)**

> "Amazing Burgers here. Incredible bacon and juicy beef patties. Great price and cool rock diner atmosphere. Super friendly staff and passionate family run business. Highly recommend!"
> **- Tony Stephens (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lets-eat-1.jpg','083 181 4205','174, สมุย, 52-53 หมู่ที่ 4 Thanon Had Lamai, Tambon Maret, อำเภอ กาะ, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.letseatbestburgers.com/','["Monday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.241+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.241+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lets-eat-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lets-eat-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17232700347794645636',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('lexi-atv-tours','standard','cmr07igxf00gcq8xdtbvzueya','Lexi ATV Tours','## Top Reviews
> "Went here with my girlfriend yesterday, we got 1 quad for the both of us. We went with a small group but our guide took just us on the hard jungle trail which i really really enjoyed, it gave me the possibility to drive fast, and i think our guide enjoyed that too, he took us to an amazing viewpoint and got us a nice drink for free, when my girlfriend fell he helped her up and had gause and bandaids ready.  Eventually he even took a little detour for more stunning views, and he even took cool pictures and videos for us!!  We really had a blast and i would definetly recommend when visiting koh samui!  Thanks guys for an unforgettable experience!!!"
> **- filip van es (5/5/5)**

> "Fantastic experience! Super fun route and a really cool destination in the jungle. The staff even provided us with a dedicated guide who took amazing care of our small children, making the trip both safe and highly enjoyable for the whole family. Very sweet guides and excellent service. Highly recommend"
> **- Henrik Rathje (5/5/5)**

> "Have done quad biking many times but this is probably the most fun experience I’ve ever had. Our instructor Bird was very knowledgeable and made sure we a lot of fun, teaching us how to do jumps and donuts, whilst filming it all on one hand!  Highly recommend you try this place if you’re in Koh Samui and looking for an experience through the jungle!"
> **- Alexis Skitini (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lexi-atv-tours-1.jpg','098 676 0411','Maenam Soi1, Tambon Bo Put, Maenam, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://wa.me/66986760411','["Monday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM","Tuesday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM","Wednesday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM","Thursday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM","Friday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM","Saturday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM","Sunday: 8:30 AM – 5:30 PM"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.243+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.243+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lexi-atv-tours-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lexi-atv-tours-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=3696685574749310214',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('link-lounge-rooftop','standard','cmr07igxl00gdq8xdbscymb2h','LINK Lounge Rooftop','## Top Reviews
> "I had a disappointing experience at Link in Koh Samui. I ordered the Black Angus steak, but what was served was definitely not Black Angus. The meat had a strange taste and texture, and I honestly couldn’t even identify what cut or type of meat it was — but it certainly wasn’t what was advertised. I double checked and they still said it was a black angus…  My son ordered a pizza, which was also very poor in quality and flavor.  To be fair, the service was ok and the staff were polite and attentive. However, when it comes to food, this place is not something I would recommend. The quality simply doesn’t match the menu description or the prices"
> **- JuMK (2/5/5)**

> "Great atmosphere with live singer…. However the food was pretty rubbish. Thai cashew chicken was crap breaded chicken, no flavour. Calamari chewy and inedible. Chips had a bizarre dip. The pizza should have been the star and taste was good… however last slice had massive long hair baked in which I ended up having to pull out of my mouth. So much great food in Samui, this was absolutely awful. Total let down on last night!"
> **- Claire Grant (1/5/5)**

> "Nice ambience. They moved us to a table by the beach once there was space. They also made vegetarian food for us. It was quite tasty. The Pad Thai portion could have been a bit more."
> **- Sop U (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/link-lounge-rooftop-1.jpg','080 460 2670','Fisherman village, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM","Friday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 5:00 – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifx90024q8xdg1rcf50m','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.249+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.249+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/link-lounge-rooftop-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/link-lounge-rooftop-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12601322468274886485',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('lion-rolling-circus','standard','cmr07igxo00geq8xd34wu1krg','Lion Rolling Circus','## Top Reviews
> "I love this place. It''s so upmarket and the staff are just so lovely. Free water and a bowl of fresh fruit when you stop in. This is by far the cheapest place for ready rolled. At least 50% less than anywhere else. This place stands out amongst the hundreds of weed cafes. It''s a class  venue and you will be made to feel very welcome. If you over 50''s like us wanting a giggle then come here. You will be glad you did. The cleanliness is amazing the toilets are so clean. Great ventilation and Aircon makes it even better. A real find."
> **- Niles Hemming (5/5/5)**

> "Having smoked over 15 years around the world, this is THE BEST coffeeshop, ever. 🙌💯 Not only the service and products are great, the manager of this place must have designed the customer experience with excellence 😍🍃 Everything you see in below pictures was free(except sunglasses & tobacco 🙈😅😎) there are board games, clean bathrooms. This place is not for you if you are looking for the lowest cost for flowers or edibles to buy and go. but again, THE BEST coffeeshop to chill especially during the day when it’s less crowded"
> **- Deniz ‘the seabass’ (5/5/5)**

> "Tried them all this is the best place by a mile. Great selection of Ndola/sativa and hybrid strains plus pre rolls and edibles . Hispitality amazing they give you a bottle of water I mean shit some of them do t even have water let alone give it you ! Overall for me best product and not trying to rip you off either. Would recommend"
> **- Dave Firth (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lion-rolling-circus-1.jpg','061 492 9349','Chaweng Beach Rd, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/lionrollingsamui.th/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 1:00 AM"]','cmr07ifs5000eq8xdeu148200','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.252+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.252+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lion-rolling-circus-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lion-rolling-circus-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16640476508256976032',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('lipa-bay-resort','standard','cmr07igxq00gfq8xdlo7f0150','Lipa Bay Resort','## Top Reviews
> "Could have stayed longer this place was gorgeous. We had wrap around windows which meant we had loads of natural light, and all the plants make for a gorgeous view. Beach is just down the path and there are places to eat and drink a short walk away. Bit out the way for hustle and bustle stuff but it was perfect for us and only a 15 taxi into the Nathon pier are"
> **- Erin Lloyd (4/5/5)**

> "Last year, in June, I had the opportunity to spend almost three weeks at Lipa Bay Resort on Koh Samui.  It was a very special and important time for me, and this place gave me exactly the peace and comfort I needed at that moment in my life. I found there a sense of calm, kindness and quiet beauty that stayed with me long after I left.  The atmosphere was truly wonderful — peaceful, warm and welcoming. I felt very well taken care of by the whole team, and also by the owner — her kindness made this stay feel even more personal, heartfelt and meaningful.  Lipa Bay Resort will always remain in my heart as a very special place — a good place on this earth, full of peace, warmth and gentle energy. I am truly grateful for the time I spent there."
> **- Magda Ka (5/5/5)**

> "Can''t recommend this property enough having spent 4 nights here. Breakfast has a set menu and the pool has a beautiful view. Sunsets are best here as it''s the west side of the island.  There''s a scooter rental shop just few metres away while restaurants are towards the right side on the main road about 500 metres away. There''s no kettle in the room but there''s hot water available 24x7 on the ground floor. If you''re looking for a more peaceful, relaxed and less commercialised location to for it"
> **- Nicolai Nayak (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lipa-bay-resort-1.jpg','083 636 4846','Lipa Noi, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.254+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.254+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lipa-bay-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lipa-bay-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9505587943165817909',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('lipa-lodge-beach-resort','standard','cmr07igxt00ggq8xd6a8y6gb2','Lipa Lodge Beach Resort','## Top Reviews
> "Visit #2 to Lipa Lodge - still the great place for me I left a long review already after my wife and I first visited. Since the place has changed little in the past 20 years, it has not changed much since a few months ago. But I do have a few observations. 1. The people who work at Lipa Lodge are just scrumptious. Not welcoming in a ‘I studied hospitality and was well trained’, but more in a non-verbal ‘This is my home, I love being here, I am so happy you’re enjoying your time - now, what can I do to help’ 2. No weed. Well, it’s allowed, but rarely do guests here use it as I never smell it. This is big as smelling weed being smoked all day is a vacation killer. 3. Most chill, quiet place. No parties, no loud music, kids do visit, but they all seem to be happy. Great for resting my heart. 4. A perfect place to find your center. While Lipa Lodge is not promoted as a western-style yoga healing center, I found it an amazing place to sit and practice meditation for a n hour a day. People do their yoga routines every morning on their own at the beach or on roofed platforms. The vibe is just perfect for that. If you need an un-organized retreat, it’s your place. 5. The owner is just the most welcoming, beautiful person. 6. Mai - thank you for the hug every morning. I can''t wait to stay#3"
> **- Hanaan Rosenthal (5/5/5)**

> "The staff were friendly and helpful. The property is great. We loved our room. My only negative was the price of breakfast. We go out for dinner with beer and it was less than the charge for one of us for breakfast. Fortunately there were places close by that offered better deals on breakfast. It truly is a beautiful spot with great sunsets."
> **- Pene Luchessa (4/5/5)**

> "My wife and I planned to be in Thailand for a week, and not on the beach. Life had other plans. On day 1 my retina detached. We were in Udon Thani. After an emergency surgery we had to stay in Thailand for a few weeks. We decided to spend a week in Koh Samui and I got the last spot in Lipa Lodge, a one bedroom with beach view. We picked it because the Lipa Noi area is less touristy and sunset facing. The island is small enough that $10 taxi will get you anywhere. We were not disappointed. Lipa Lodge is beautiful. The gardens, pool, beach and buildings are designed with privacy and simplicity. The staff is just a bunch of relaxed, joyful people that made every part of our stay delightful. The breakfast buffet was delicious with omelette to order, good strong coffee, an assortment of fruit and another Thai dish or two. The pool is meticulously maintained and the beach is right off the gardens, private and serene. The room itself was very well designed and more than big enough for a couple to get romantic without getting on each other :) We had an amazing week of rest and so looking forward to coming back. I think we found our vacation spot!"
> **- Hanaan Rosenthal (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lipa-lodge-beach-resort-1.jpg','081 978 5529','75 Lipa​ Lodge​ resort, 4, Tambon Lipa Noi, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.lipalodgeresort.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.257+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.257+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lipa-lodge-beach-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/lipa-lodge-beach-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=3913195767076750162',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('litaliano-restaurant','standard','cmr07igxv00ghq8xdrtw9le89','L''italiano Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Wa wa wiya! Such good pizza and DELICIOUS lasagna! I ordered the one with chicken and pork. The waiter was so sweet and the owner as well, we called before to make sure they’re still open and he said he’s gonna wait for us to arrive! thank you for a great dinner!"
> **- Inbar Nissim (5/5/5)**

> "Authentic Italian food. Happy every time when we eat here. Pasta is superb just like you eat in Italy. Anyway, my favourite is steak wagyu (sorry I forgot to take picture every time just took an empty plate 😅😂) recommended!"
> **- Sky yy (5/5/5)**

> "One of the best and fresh pizza, i have ever had..! I am from india, and pure vegetarian.. they listened our brief with so much patience, and made pizza for us beyond our expectations.. its was so delicious. Place is small but very well decored. Will recommend for sure."
> **- Arpit Patel (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/litaliano-restaurant-1.jpg','086 080 7032','34/1 Moo 1 Fisherman Village, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Samui, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.259+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.259+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/litaliano-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/litaliano-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=14538114082019784109',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('little-coconuts-early-learning-center','standard','cmr07igxx00giq8xdmcq48afw','Little Coconuts Early Learning Center','## Top Reviews
> "We sent my 4-year-old grandniece to Little Coconuts Nursery in Samui for 3 weeks, and she absolutely loved it. She didn’t speak English at first, but she learned so quickly during her time there, which really amazed us.  One thing we truly appreciated is that they have a camera feed, so parents and family can check in and watch from a distance, which gave us great peace of mind. The fees are affordable and include meals, which is a big plus.  She’s now back in Malaysia, but she keeps asking if she can come back to this nursery again. That alone says everything. Highly recommended!"
> **- Zaza Meerveld (5/5/5)**

> "Don''t enroll your children here if they don''t speak English well. There was no support from the teachers or principal. My daughter didn''t understand much, and it turned out the children were rude, teasing her, interrupting her play and tasks, and she was even hit a few times. When she defended herself, the children complained to the teacher, who yelled at my daughter. After all, it''s easiest to blame someone who can''t defend themselves. And my daughter couldn''t say that someone hit her first. I spent two days on camera to confirm my daughter''s words. There was a particular problem with one boy. I reported the problem to the principal, but she did nothing. My daughter asked the teacher not to sit next to the boy, but she still sat her next to him. My daughter was so stressed about preschool that she stopped eating, so after two and a half weeks, I took her out. Furthermore, for 5- and 6-year-olds, there''s too much learning; children sit in front of the board for hours without moving. They squirm and fidget, and you can see they''re hidden. Didn''t you know that at this age, children need more exercise? They need the opportunity to exercise! Furthermore, they boast about healthy eating, and the feature provides sweets for children. The website also states that children have coconut water and juices available, but there was nothing like that; each child must share their own water. I don''t recommend it!"
> **- Ewelina Mikrut (1/5/5)**

> "Our son spent just over a year at coconuts as a 2-3 year old. We noticed over time great progression in his development, communication and all round behavior.  A caring and safe environment, Sam and the team keep up the great work. Thank you."
> **- Joakim Holmes (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/little-coconuts-early-learning-center-1.jpg','098 194 1797','157/53, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'http://littlecoconutsdaycare.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 4:30 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifwy001zq8xdppgaj2cs','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.261+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.261+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/little-coconuts-early-learning-center-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/little-coconuts-early-learning-center-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4271968124017154763',NULL,NULL);
