> "They have their own factory and you can choose your favorite colors and thickness on cushion."
> **- Johnny Erlandsen (5/5/5)**

> ""
> **- Kathryn (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pechvadee-furniture-1.jpg','+66817199361','176/6 7 ถ. ทวีราษฎร์ภักดี Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/share/1DYBcno87x/?mibextid=wwXIfr','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:30 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.810+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.810+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pechvadee-furniture-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pechvadee-furniture-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pechvadee-furniture-3.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pechvadee-furniture-4.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12432319720912749382',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('pepenero','standard','cmr07ihd800lmq8xdvvltp7be','Pepenero','## Top Reviews
> "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ A True Taste of Italy in Koh Samui As an Italian living in Thailand for many years, I can honestly say that finding a restaurant of this caliber is rare. My experience at Pepenero was simply outstanding. The cuisine is elegant, authentic, and prepared with top-quality ingredients. Every dish reflects passion, skill, and respect for Italian culinary traditions, presented with the attention to detail you would expect from a fine dining restaurant in Italy. A special compliment goes to the Chef, whose signature creations are nothing short of exceptional. Each plate is a masterpiece, combining incredible flavors, perfect balance, and beautiful presentation. The atmosphere is warm, sophisticated, and romantic, while the service is professional, attentive, and genuinely welcoming. If you are looking for an unforgettable Italian dining experience in Koh Samui, Pepenero is undoubtedly one of the finest restaurants on the island. Congratulations to the entire Pepenero team for bringing a piece of Italy to Thailand. Highly recommended, and I will definitely return. 🇮🇹🍷✨"
> **- Luca Foschi (5/5/5)**

> "One of the best Italian restaurants in Thailand, nice and fancy restaurant with a very premium quality.. The owner is super nice and he kept trying to bring complementary finger foods to our baby also they are willing to do whatever you fancy even if not on the menu. highly recommended"
> **- osama tolis (5/5/5)**

> "a straight A!!! top service, top advice, good wines and very good food. An absolute insider tip. If you love real Italian cuisine, come here. Top class!!!"
> **- Thorsten Sauer (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pepenero-1.jpg','091 175 0707','4, 5, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://pepenerosamui.com/','["Monday: 6:00 – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: Closed","Wednesday: Closed","Thursday: Closed","Friday: 6:00 – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 6:00 – 11:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.812+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.812+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pepenero-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pepenero-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15822489820381738651',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('phalarn-inn','standard','cmr07ihdb00lnq8xd4bd3oz4h','Phalarn Inn','## Top Reviews
> "I have no idea who was those guests who wrote 1 stars reviews but… It is great place to live, relax and chill. Amazing swimming pool with crystal clear water, cozy clean and simple Thai style bungalows, friendly stuff, green garden around all mentioned above. We spent here a lovely week, and miss that place so much. You can walk to the beach in 5 minutes, visit one of the best Thai food restaurants or go to massage. All places available just by foot."
> **- Vladimir Rizun (5/5/5)**

> "Unfortunately my report is not good. Lets start with the owner. She''s a highly strung neurotic loud mouthed obnoxious person with no idea how to talk to customers let alone run a resort. Every minute of the day she is shouting at her staff or her poor husband who is the complete opposite. Most of the time all you hear is her horrible voice. As for the rooms...they''ve seen better days, but our bed was quite comfortable. Everything is rather old with many fixtures and fittings having noticable damage. The resort is next door to Lomprahya ferry service."
> **- Bob Black (1/5/5)**

> "What a strange experience at this resort. First of all the owner named Sugar gave us a very condescending,sarcastic and in general rude and extremely arrogant narrative on why she raised her prices when we tried to make a deal. She went nuts! As we are travelling by bicycle and it was getting late we stayed anyway as there is also a lovely swimming pool recently renovated by Sugar''s husband who is the complete opposite in character. We stayed three nights in a room with one light working and broken toilet bum gun  no TV!  900 baht. Anyhow this is the thing  later we were acuse of breaking the lights and damaging a TV that didn''t exist. Basically try a different resort.!"
> **- David (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phalarn-inn-1.jpg','077 247 283','28/1 M.4 Maenam Beach, ตำบล แม่น้ำ Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.4,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.815+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.815+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phalarn-inn-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phalarn-inn-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=18177828344986404678',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('phangka-paradise-resort','standard','cmr07ihdf00lpq8xdgn7t057v','Phangka Paradise Resort','## Top Reviews
> "10/10 3 star hotel. Was well looked after during my stay and both hosts were so so nice.  Greeted every morning with an incredible breakfast of fruit, coffee and an option of traditional Thai style breakfasts. I had a comfortable room with good A/C. It is very quiet and peaceful but far from tourist hot spots (both a blessing and a curse). There are friendly dogs. The furniture around the pool is slightly dated but usable.  Deffo worth a couple of nights stay while in Samui as it’s easy to access the Doc for pig island/Anthong national park, as well as some of the waterfalls on the park."
> **- Joe Groves (5/5/5)**

> "Good place for relax Very quiet beach Sunset is the best time There is bar and resturant also"
> **- SallY PJ'' (5/5/5)**

> "Best place for us. Family athmosphere, clean beach and pool. Manager Ann and chef Bibi at their best ❤️"
> **- Mateusz Wejchert (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phangka-paradise-resort-1.jpg','077 310 848','Taling Ngam, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ihdd00loq8xde04nm02v','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.819+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.819+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phangka-paradise-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phangka-paradise-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13582876133918630592',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('phensiri-thai-restaurant','standard','cmr07ihdh00lqq8xdhxm1so07','Phensiri Thai Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Im a big fan of Thai cuisine and this place has pleasantly surprised me. Their menu is large and will suite different tastes. Some dishes are completely not spicy. I love my spices so opted for a bit of heat. All ingredients are super fresh, cooked to perfection and served in a speedy manner with a smile. We were so impressed that came back 3 more times to dine there. It is my advice to book the table in advance. They will try to accommodate you without the booking but you may need to wait. There are 3/4 parking spaces at the rear which are almost always full. Parking is available 100 metres away on the corner towards the beach."
> **- Natalia Percival (5/5/5)**

> "Fantastic, authentic, soul food no doubt. Every dish was absolutely on point - the best meal we had in Samui. Can''t say the same about the service sadly. We were made to wait unnecessarily (almost like a punishment) when we can clearly see several empty tables.  We had to repeatedly immediately asked for mosquito spray as we were getting bitten incessantly. The waitor can even make a joke that "
> **- Gursheel Dhillon (4/5/5)**

> "The restaurant was very full, and the staff were quite friendly. The food did take a little while to arrive, but honestly, it was absolutely delicious.  This is the most refined Thai cuisine I’ve ever had. No wonder they won a Michelin award — if you ever get the chance, you definitely have to try it at least once."
> **- 唐有建 (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phensiri-thai-restaurant-1.jpg','077 945 151','80/30 ถนน เลียบหาดเฉวง, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.phensiri.com/','["Monday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.821+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.821+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phensiri-thai-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phensiri-thai-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=11554471251947261321',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('phetchbuncha-samui-stadium','standard','cmr07ihdk00lrq8xd4h11ckrx','Phetchbuncha Samui Stadium','## Top Reviews
> "Great place to spend an evening. Sat ringside, got blood on us, made faces with one of the judges! Saw a couple of 15 y/o beat much older opponents. Great night"
> **- Gee Keyz (5/5/5)**

> "Very nice. Authentic Muay Thai boxing place. Air conditioned stadium. Ringside VIP seats for 2000 BHT and normal tickets for 1000 BHT. Every Monday, Wednesday and Friday program with 6-6 matches. International fighters as well. Food, drinks are availavle before and during the program. Ticket booking via WhatsApp."
> **- Peter Kovacs (5/5/5)**

> "This was my second Muay Thai fight experience — the first one was in Bangkok — and this one felt much more traditional and authentic.  The atmosphere was very entertaining and exciting. There were many tourists, but it still felt very real. I sat in the first rows and it was absolutely worth it to see the fights up close. The focus and intensity of the fighters is really impressive.  It’s definitely worth visiting this stadium if you’re in Koh Samui. You can also order food and drinks directly from your seat, which makes the whole experience very easy and enjoyable."
> **- Cinthia Piedrahita (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phetchbuncha-samui-stadium-1.jpg','084 772 6739','G3C4+XF3, Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,'https://phetchbuncha.com/','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: Closed","Wednesday: 9:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Thursday: Closed","Friday: Closed","Saturday: 9:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.824+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.824+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phetchbuncha-samui-stadium-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/phetchbuncha-samui-stadium-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5321434650976883975',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('photo-koh-samui','standard','cmr07ihdm00lsq8xdzfwpiwu6','Photo Koh Samui','## Top Reviews
> "Our search for the perfect photographer to capture our special moments in Koh Samui was exhaustive. We wanted to have a photo shoot with our wedding dresses and other outfits, and the locations were very important to us. After looking at countless online reviews and contacting numerous photographers, we were intrigued to find that many of the most reputable ones vouched for Octav Cado. His response time was significantly faster than others, and he patiently and thoroughly answered all of our many questions. His professionalism and quick communication made it an easy decision to choose him.  Before our trip, Octav''s guidance was phenomenal. He asked about our preferences and for current photos to better understand us, providing valuable advice on everything from locations to outfits. He proved to be more than just a photographer; his coordination for the entire experience was flawless. He arranged for a yacht rental, a makeup artist, and a companion videographer, making our planning effortless. The final price for everything was incredibly reasonable, especially considering the high quality of service and the stunning results we received.  During the photo shoot itself, Octav''s dedication to his craft was clear. He was unfazed by the windy or hot weather, focusing solely on getting the best possible shots. We were initially unsure of how to pose, but he guided us through every position, making us feel comfortable and confident. He even helped with our dressings to ensure everything looked perfect. At times, he endured significant difficulty to get to the ideal position for a beautiful shot, particularly on the boat, which was challenging. His commitment to the art was truly inspiring.  Within a short time after the shoot, he provided the photos, and we were absolutely astonished. He had perfectly captured the vision we had in mind. The images were breathtaking and perfectly reflected the atmosphere and emotion of the day. We are so incredibly happy with the results. We highly recommend Octav for any photography or videography needs. He is a master of his craft, and his passion is evident in every picture."
> **- Ami Omi (5/5/5)**

> "We had an amazing experience with Octav on Koh Samui. From the beginning, he was very friendly, professional, and easy to communicate with. During the photoshoot he made us feel comfortable and relaxed, which was especially important for a family session.  The photos turned out absolutely beautiful — natural, elegant, and full of atmosphere. He has a great eye for light, composition, and capturing real moments. We are very happy with the result and truly appreciate his work.  If you are looking for a talented photographer on Koh Samui, we can highly recommend Octav. Thank you again for a wonderful experience.  M."
> **- Martin Uvira (5/5/5)**

> "We had make some wedding photos on Koh Samui. Very proffesional, willing and nice approach. I can recommend for all people, what want really nice and proffesional photos from holiday."
> **- Rosťa Jordán (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/photo-koh-samui-1.jpg','061 816 3485','128, 95, Tambon Mae Nam, Maenam, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://photokohsamui.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07iftc000rq8xdiyhsa78o','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.826+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.826+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/photo-koh-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/photo-koh-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15681832100564418860',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('pi-samui','standard','cmr07ihdp00ltq8xdbmfqyuse','Pi Samui','## Top Reviews
> "Amazing food. Really good pizza pasta and dessert. I would recommend the funghi pizza. Everything we had was great. Good vibes also, a cute band played outside. The staff was super nice as well."
> **- Noam Wolf (5/5/5)**

> "Wow - years ago this was just a never ending construction zone - now a place to get awesome food and service! Very authentic Thai food - excellent service. Very helpful stuff - might be for some to much. Portions are great in size - Thai food - like it should be. Thank you - we come again! Yes a bit higher prices - but worth every bhat."
> **- Björn Röthig (5/5/5)**

> "We visited Pi Samui Beach Restaurant to eat and relax. The location is beautiful and the place itself looks great, which is why it was disappointing that the overall experience didn’t match the setting. Especially considering the prices. First, the menus were in very poor condition. They looked like they had been soaked in water and dried again, wrinkled, worn, and not something you expect from a restaurant at this level. Small details like this matter more when you are paying premium prices. The food was not okay. The pasta bolognese I ordered was undercooked, which made it unpleasant to eat. We also ordered coconuts, and both seemed old or not fresh. The flesh was very difficult to scrape off, which usually indicates that it has been sitting too long. The service was also not particularly nice. It felt like the smiles were forced and not genuine, which created an uncomfortable atmosphere. At one point I went for a swim with my child, and when we came back we were told not to sit on the chair to prevent future guests from getting the cushions wet. While we understand the concern, the way it was communicated didn’t feel welcoming. A better solution would have been to offer a towel to sit on, or move us to another table with chairs without cushions. We were not offered any alternative or choice. We had visited this place before quite some time ago, and the experience back then was completely different. There was an exceptional English gentleman who really represented the entire place. He greeted us with a genuinely warm smile and made sure we had everything we needed. We truly felt special because of his service, and that is one of the main reasons we decided to come back. Unfortunately, he was not there this time, and it seems that since then the service has dropped significantly and the overall quality has been lowered,while the prices remain the same. Service should never be underestimated, no matter what the customer orders. Good service is what makes guests feel welcome and is often the reason people choose to return. This place has a lot of potential because the location is genuinely beautiful. But when it’s not cheap, details matter, service, food quality, and overall professionalism. With some improvements, this could easily become a great spot again. For now, the experience did not live up to expectations."
> **- Niko (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pi-samui-1.jpg','093 438 4995','24, 84, Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://pisamui.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifsv000nq8xdrwnu123q','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.829+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.829+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pi-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pi-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8537020238851398127',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('pijit-motorbike-and-car-rental','standard','cmr07ihdq00luq8xdqfodpbmy','PIJIT Motorbike And Car Rental','## Top Reviews
> "Would recommend 100%! Great place to rent a scooter right next to the pier. The staff is very friendly and helpful. The scooter was in great shape (good brakes, good mirrors, lights worked fine, a lot of space in the buggy).  I rented the cheapest scooter for 250thb per day. The scooter was absolutely fine for getting around the island (even when hilly, i''m 85kg + 12 kg luggage).  For deposit you can leave your passport, but i was offered to leave my countries'' ID-card and 4000thb deposit. As easy as that 👍👍"
> **- Ward Meijers (5/5/5)**

> "Great bike rental! My friends and I rented two bikes for two weeks. The woman was very helpful and gave us a discount. I highly recommend this bike rental service to everyone; they have the warmest and most sincere people."
> **- Mark (5/5/5)**

> "Best Rental shop in Samui. Amazing service, booked last minute while on the ferry over to Samui. The bike was ready as soon as we got off, and the process was very simple, the bike itself was nearly new and was in very good condition. Easy return and full deposit returned to me, would highly recommend and will definitely use again."
> **- 50 Cent (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pijit-motorbike-and-car-rental-1.jpg','089 875 7737','247 อ่างทอง Tambon Ang Thong, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/share/pYk4fTbmAeefBzCA/?mibextid=LQQJ4d','["Monday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 7:30 AM – 8:00 PM"]','cmr07ifui0012q8xdzn158clv','cmr07ig1h003iq8xdb1g9nifo','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.830+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.830+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pijit-motorbike-and-car-rental-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pijit-motorbike-and-car-rental-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12282271074900616976',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('pinkys-nails-spa','standard','cmr07ihds00lvq8xdwbvt67yz','Pinky’s Nails & Spa','## Top Reviews
> "Nice, clean and very friendly staff, that borrowed me shoes with no toe until my nail polish had dried. My girl had her first gel nails, which made here very happy."
> **- Charlotte Ryman (5/5/5)**

> "I was there for about 2.5 hours to get my nails done. This included nail extensions and a gel manicure with a design. They did such a great job and were very friendly!! I didn''t expect there to be cats but i really enjoyed the company of the furred staff🐈‍⬛."
> **- Laurine Eltrich (5/5/5)**

> "I am so happy with my set! Staff was really sweet and accommodating, also spoke English really well and could talk me through the process. Tools were cleaned and disinfected after every use. :)"
> **- Annabelle M. Amha (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pinkys-nails-spa-1.jpg','061 924 1963','147, 5, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://pinkysnailspa.netlify.app/?utm_source=google&utm_medium=maps&utm_campaign=gmb','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.832+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.832+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pinkys-nails-spa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pinkys-nails-spa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17624253212180187270',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('pinnacle-resort','standard','cmr07ihdv00lwq8xdpdr8fd2h','Pinnacle Resort','## Top Reviews
> "Rooms were really nice. Had a garden view. But the electrical sockets were very loose. Not a single socket was working properly for plugging the charger. Initially we were given 2 rooms on the 3rd floor and in one of the rooms water from AC was leaking. After informing the reception they gave us 2 rooms on the ground floor. Same type rooms. We had to carry our  luggages up and down the stairs. No staff were there to help us carry our lugguages.  There was shortage of staff as informed by the lady at the reception. The food at the restaurant was good( we had lunch there on the last day of our trip) . It''s the pool and the beach of this property that is awesome and makes it worthwhile. Overall the staff were courteous and quite responsive. FYI Coco palms is the adjacent property."
> **- AJAY BEHERA (4/5/5)**

> "Had a  really wonderful stay at Pinnacle. It’s right on the beach, and although at the end of the bay and quite far from most things, would be good if you’re looking for a calmer place to stay. The room was spacious with a comfortable bed and had everything you would need. The bathroom had 2 different shower heads (fixed and handheld). They provide beach towels upon arrival in your room, or you can also ask the restaurant on the beach. They also provided toiletries (shower cap, qtips, toothbrushes and shaver) and water bottles daily. Breakfast was also great with a decent variety of options including fruits and fresh eggs that can be made to order. The grounds were quite beautiful and well vegetated which created a nice atmosphere. There were plenty of lounge chairs along the beach as well as around the pool, and I didn’t normally have a hard time finding an empty chair. There is also a spa where you can get a massage for a very comparable price to the massage parlours along the road. The massages are done along the beach on a 2nd floor open air room which was nice.  The only thing I would give feedback on was to the receptionist upon my check in. Upon giving me my room key she loudly announced my room number, and the exact location of the room for others in the lobby to overhear, and as a solo traveller this made me a little bit uncomfortable.  Overall, I felt safe and comfortable at this resort, but hope that they can avoid doing this to future solo travellers."
> **- D Lee (4/5/5)**

> "We have just stayed 6 days at this resort. We had an amazing time here. From the moment you step inside it feels like walking in a botanic garden. The bungalow was also great. Spacious, good air conditioning. Only the shower doesnt get so hot. It was hot, cold, hot, cold. But its so hot outside that a cold shower didnt bother us that much. The view from the swimming pool is amazing. Direct view at the sea. The staff was also very friendly and helpfull. They cleaned the bungalow every day. And put new towels every day. The breakfast was also good. Not a five star restaurant. But nothing to complain about.  We didnt understand why there are so many reviews that its so remotely located. That there is nothing around. There is everything around. Just outside there are lots of other food places. There is even a 7-11. On 1200 meters. About 15 min walk. Also places where you can rent a scooter just couple of meters to walk. I didnt had a international licence with me. So could not rent a scooter. But you can just get a Grab taxi with the Grab app. And taxi is there in 2/3 min. And can take you to lots of places.  Also the matrass was in the beginning very hard. But in the days after they put new Topper matresses in all the rooms. Wich made it softer to sleep.  If you want a quiet relaxing place to stay, With natural environments, And still easy acces to all the highlights. I can definetely recommend to stay at this place."
> **- Ben Waart (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pinnacle-resort-1.jpg','077 427 308','26 Bontji Moo 4, ตำบล แม่น้ำ อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.2,0,0,0,NULL,'https://samui.pinnaclehotels.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.835+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.835+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pinnacle-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/pinnacle-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17154171953832087654',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('piri-piri-flaming-grill','standard','cmr07ihdx00lxq8xdp4m0yvsh','Piri Piri Flaming Grill','## Top Reviews
> "Came in for dinner. Service was excellent, friendly staff. Husband ordered half chicken snd ordered Piri Piri wrap, both came either chips. Food didn’t come quick but that’s ok as you can see them making everything fresh to order. Drinks a little more expensive than other places but food makes up for it. Our food was delicious and the extensive selection of sauces on the table was brilliant. Note they add 7% vat to the bill which we didn’t notice on the menu. Would recommend."
> **- Glasgow girl (4/5/5)**

> "Service was good, immediately shown to a table and our server took the order but forgot to bring both drinks.  Food came quickly which was piping hot, and tasty! Very similar concept to Nando’s, with different sauces available too.  Would recommend a visit if you’re craving some peri peri chicken!"
> **- Kimberley Ramsay (4/5/5)**

> "The staff here were very attentive and helpful I cannot fault any of the staff here apart from the chef who neglected to cook my chicken. As you can see from the pictures it is still clucking. Not a happy customer considering this was the most expensive meal of my three weeks travelling."
> **- Megan Norris (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/piri-piri-flaming-grill-1.jpg','064 809 8725','124, 148 Thanon Had Lamai, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.2,0,0,0,NULL,'https://piripiriasia.com/koh-samui/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:12.837+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:12.837+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/piri-piri-flaming-grill-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/piri-piri-flaming-grill-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9575999419901279485',NULL,NULL);
