INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('sapphire-ocean-samui-charter','standard','cmr07ihrp00raq8xdpnv14vyd','Sapphire Ocean Samui Charter','## Top Reviews
> "The boat was well equipped and maintained. Hong, our guide, was wonderful and super engaging and playful with the younger kids in our family. Nut and Film - our other crew members - were equally attentive and friendly. Overall we had a fantastic and well executed day! It started with picking us up at the beachfront of our hotel, then to the Angthong Marine Park (we visited first to avoid the large crowds so that the climb up and down to the Emerald Lagoon wasn’t rushed for our little hikers), then to a spot north of the park to privately snorkel, followed by lunch (we preordered so that the food was ready for us when we arrived), next to a private beach cove (which unfortunately was covered with plastic rubbish but our team quickly cleaned the beach with help from us) and then back to the beachfront of our hotel in Bophut. The experience was fully enjoyed by all in our family, from the youngest to the oldest. I highly recommend this company - booking was a breeze and communication up to our tour and throughout our experience was impeccable."
> **- Mitzi Sáles (5/5/5)**

> "Amazing experience! Frank and team communicated very well since booking months ago, answering any and all questions, and ensuring we can trust in his team and get excited for the trip.  The boat was as clean as the pictures, and the team kept the boat extremely clean during the ride as well. You can tell they take great care of their boats.  The itinerary was also perfect, lining up a day that fit our needs and hit all of the highlights - snorkeling on the coral reef, seeing the national park, heading to a very tasty lunch, and spending time relaxing on the beach, before heading back.  It was well worth the money."
> **- Amanda G (5/5/5)**

> "We had an absolutely unforgettable day with Sapphire Ocean Koh Samui! From start to finish, the whole experience was fantastic and totally worth it.  The boat was spotlessly clean and very comfortable, and our crew, Film, Nut, and Hong, were incredible. They were friendly, professional, and attentive throughout the entire trip, making everything feel smooth and effortless.  Before we even set off, they asked us to place our food orders, which meant we didn’t have to wait later at the restaurant, a thoughtful touch that saved time and let us enjoy every part of the tour without fuss.  During the day we visited around 4–5 stunning islands, including one with a breathtaking viewpoint that was perfect for photos. We also had an amazing snorkeling session in crystal-clear water, with plenty of beautiful marine life to see.  Lunch was served at a restaurant, and the food was delicious and fresh, easily one of the highlights of the trip. Afterward, we headed to a private beach where we relaxed, swam, and just enjoyed the peaceful surroundings.  By the end of the day, we were completely blown away, it felt like so much more than just a boat tour. If you’re visiting Koh Samui and want a well-organized, enjoyable island-hopping adventure, this tour is totally worth the money. Highly recommended!"
> **- OptimalOptimus (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sapphire-ocean-samui-charter-1.jpg','062 660 5582','plai laem soi3，bo put ，ko samui boput, อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://sapphireoceansamui.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifv2001aq8xdag7cvjgf','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.333+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.333+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sapphire-ocean-samui-charter-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sapphire-ocean-samui-charter-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9294483859936174293',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('sarana-beach-villas','standard','cmr07ihrs00rbq8xdupjcvftm','Sarana Beach Villas','## Top Reviews
> "Simply amazing, right on the beach with minimal people. Ours to enjoy mostly on our own. Our only mistake was that we should have stayed longer. The villas were modern and new and very comfortable. The private plunge pool was a welcome relief returning at the end of the day. These villas are close to all amenities that we required including walking distance to 7 Eleven and fruit stores. Laundry service across the road and some nice restaurants nearby. Could not rate these properties highly enough and definitely plan to return."
> **- Brad Weir (5/5/5)**

> "We stayed here in December 2023 and loved it. The location, decor, and facilities are amazing and for us this felt like a luxury stay. Easy check in and check out and very clean.  The view from the bedroom on the mezzanine floor in a morning was stunning. It is in a quieter area than some of the more tourist spots - plenty of beach restaurants and bars but if you want to be visit a busier area you can easily order a taxi.  We would definetely recommend and look forward to staying again."
> **- Sharna and Katie (5/5/5)**

> "We were the fortunate folk to be the first ever “residents” at Sarana Beach Villa. The decor, the ON beach location,private pool and Deb and Ricky’s warm welcome made a very memorable holiday for us. Great variety of restaurants within easy walking distance, plus a pharmacy and a 7-Eleven. Khun Yips little restaurant directly across the road is superb - so cheap and delicious, plus she happily delivers your meal. The nearby laundry service shop added to the genuine Thai experience !"
> **- Carol Horton (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sarana-beach-villas-1.jpg','080 825 0910','Building number 73, sub-distric, 14 village number 6, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifs1000cq8xdfo2aau32','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.336+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.336+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sarana-beach-villas-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sarana-beach-villas-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13835810379737026240',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('saree-lagoon-villa','standard','cmr07ihrv00rcq8xdwiesre55','Saree Lagoon Villa','## Top Reviews
> "We stayed here for seven days and did a late checkin due to our plane being delayed, we were welcomed in the complete dark by the people from the front desk whilst being very helpfull. The villa''s were nice and clean and it was a nice quiet place Just on the side of one of the easily accessible roads. Would defenitely recommend.🫡"
> **- Youri Schouten (5/5/5)**

> "Lovely comfortable villa with a great pool. Quiet too. Restaurant p''Orn is amazing family run with best food in that area hands down and half the price of beach fronts gaffs."
> **- Brian Mcgilp (5/5/5)**

> "Clean , Nature all around , calm , the swimming pool is amazing , and the people are very nice and helpful !"
> **- Les Pièces Vintage (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/saree-lagoon-villa-1.jpg','089 678 9371','Lipa Noi, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.339+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.339+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/saree-lagoon-villa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/saree-lagoon-villa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=1815173623796425724',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('sareeraya-chefs-table','standard','cmr07ihrz00rdq8xd8qwlrpbg','Sareeraya Chefs Table','## Top Reviews
> "Thank you so much to Chef Dara and her team for an amazing New Year''s Eve dinner in Koh Samui! They came to our rental villa and prepared a private dining experience that was lovely and incredibly delicious. Both the presentation and flavors of the meal were top notch. The service was friendly and professional. They took care of everything from start to finish. We highly recommend Siri Dara Samui Chef for an excellent dining experience in Koh Samui."
> **- Ariya Lapan (5/5/5)**

> "Chef Dara exceeded all of our expectations. Every single dish was presented so beautifully and tasted amazing. Our best meal in Thailand!! She and her team were also so friendly and she explained each of her dishes so well. Would definitely recommend and well worth the money!"
> **- Sandy (5/5/5)**

> "Our cooking class with Dara at Siri Dara Chef’s Table was an absolute highlight of our trip to Koh Samui! From start to finish, the experience was immersive, educational, and so much fun. Dara is not only an incredibly skilled chef but also a warm and engaging host who made us feel right at home in her beautiful kitchen.  We learned to cook authentic Thai dishes using fresh, local ingredients, and Dara guided us through every step with patience and expertise. She shared so many valuable cooking tips, cultural insights, and personal stories that made the experience even more special. The best part? Enjoying our delicious creations in a cozy, intimate setting!  If you’re looking for a hands-on, unforgettable culinary experience in Koh Samui, this is the class to take. Whether you’re a beginner or a seasoned cook, Dara will make sure you leave with new skills, amazing memories, and a happy (and very full) stomach. Highly recommend!"
> **- Donna Buonanno (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sareeraya-chefs-table-1.jpg','094 517 8916','28, 143 Moo1 Soi Maenam 1, Tambon Mae Nam, Koh Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://instagram.com/siridarasamui?igshid=YmMyMTA2M2Y=',NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.343+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.343+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sareeraya-chefs-table-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sareeraya-chefs-table-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17451415552122429697',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('sareeraya-villas','standard','cmr07ihs100req8xds862rtp2','Sareeraya Villas','## Top Reviews
> "Fabulous boutique hotel, staff very friendly and attentive. Location is perfect with a lovely part of the beach at your disposal. We were there for my 70 th birthday and they made a lovely decoration on our bed and brought a cake to my room. My only regret was bothering to pre hire a car as they provide courtesy pick up from the airport return and Chewang is a nightmare to drive and parking is nigh impossible, there are regular baht buses that pick up from outside the hotel for a cheap cost. The room was luxurious and spotlessly clean. The balcony had great views of the beach. Breakfast was very good. All in all a great holiday, we will be back."
> **- sorawit wongtamat (5/5/5)**

> "stayed for 3 nights and it was a nice experience! we enjoyed the happy hour (buy one get one free on select drinks), our private pool, direct beach access, and the breakfast."
> **- Jamie Lam (5/5/5)**

> "I recently stayed at Sareeraya Villas & Suites and want to give an honest review focused on one key issue: the room size and location are not as advertised. •	The so-called 70 m² suites start directly along the main road. We had no idea these rooms were roadside. If we had known, we wouldn’t have booked them — at least not at that price. •	Once inside the room, it was immediately clear that the space was nowhere near 70 m². After raising the issue, the hotel sent two engineers to measure it. Their result confirmed my own quick measurement: 49 m². •	I was told that all rooms sold as 70 m² are in fact this size. So anyone booking these suites should expect roughly 50 m², not 70. •	I asked for a price adjustment to match the real size. Instead, I received a bottle of wine. Nice gesture, but it doesn’t fix the fact that I paid for a larger room than I got. •	To be clear: the staff is amazing. The ladies at the check-in were exceptionally kind, helpful, and welcoming. My issue is only with the misleading room description and the reluctance of management to correct the pricing.  Bottom line: Great people, but the advertised room sizes are simply not accurate. If you expect a true 70 m² suite, you won’t get it — and the rooms along the road are far from the quiet experience you might expect at this price point."
> **- Tom Tom (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sareeraya-villas-1.jpg','077 914 333','100, 1 Chaweng Beach Rd, Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.sareeraya.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.345+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.345+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sareeraya-villas-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sareeraya-villas-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=2676899578650604765',NULL,NULL);
