INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('sweden-village','standard','cmr07ihyk00ttq8xdkj7gfsg9','Sweden Village','## Top Reviews
> "The night market in Fisherman’s Village is without doubt one of the highlights of Koh Samui and a place we returned to multiple times during our stay.  What makes this night market special is not just the food and shopping, but the overall atmosphere. The market stretches along a long part of the beachfront and the main street, creating a lively yet relaxed setting with the sea right next to you. In the evenings, the area is largely closed to cars and scooters, which makes it safe, walkable, and very enjoyable to explore at a calm pace.  The food options are excellent and varied. There is a wide selection of local street food, fresh seafood, Thai classics, snacks, desserts, and international options. Many of the small stalls are run by locals, and the quality is generally very good. Prices are reasonable, and it’s easy to try several dishes in one evening.  Beyond food, the market offers a nice mix of handicrafts, souvenirs, clothes, and small local products. It feels more authentic and less chaotic than some of the larger night markets elsewhere, and it never felt overwhelming despite being popular.  Another big plus is that the night market manages to stay lively without being noisy. Even with many visitors, the atmosphere remains relaxed and friendly, making it suitable for families, couples, and groups alike. It’s also easy to combine the market with a walk along the beach or a visit to one of the nearby cafés and restaurants.  Overall, the Fisherman’s Village Night Market offers a perfect balance of local culture, food, and atmosphere. Whether you come for dinner, an evening stroll, or just to soak in the vibe by the sea, it’s absolutely worth a visit — and likely more than once."
> **- Jesper Errboe (5/5/5)**

> "Just come for the fireshow and it is worth it . Get the info review about here also got fireshow besides than akhbar . And come early as 4pm free shuttle from hotel.  So not many shop open . At night only they open . Selling food , bag cloth and etc. go back at the drop off point to call a grab to the hotel , in front of 7e . The grab cost about 380Baht to the sarann. Didn''t explore much at night as we rush to go back. Nice place will definitely come again."
> **- dokioff (5/5/5)**

> "Fisherman''s Village has one of the best atmospheres I’ve experienced in Thailand. The whole place is full of energy, music, lights, great people, and an amazing vibe from the second you arrive. Every street feels alive with bars, clubs, market stalls, restaurants, and people from all over the world all enjoying the moment together.  One thing that really stood out to me was the street food — honestly some of the best food you can eat. So much flavour, so many choices, and everything cooked fresh right in front of you. Whether you want seafood, Thai food, desserts, or late-night snacks, there’s something everywhere you turn.  It’s the kind of place where you can walk around for hours, take in the atmosphere, meet good people, listen to live music, shop, eat amazing food, and just enjoy life. A must-visit if you’re in Koh Samui. ✨"
> **- Leroy Matthews (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sweden-village-1.jpg',NULL,'H25J+9HJ, Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.580+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.580+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sweden-village-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sweden-village-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sweden-village-3.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/sweden-village-4.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=11388955683857341114',NULL,NULL);
