> "New boards, good service, price is very reasonable (300 per day). We enjoyed the experience 🤙"
> **- Kirill Antonov (5/5/5)**

> "Calm place with clean beach, sups and cafe. The staff are amazing"
> **- Valeriia Dolha (5/5/5)**

> "Calm and happy place"
> **- MoonS (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-little-sup-samui-1.jpg','083 022 8083','Taweerat Pakdee Road Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/thelittlesupsamui/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.782+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.782+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-little-sup-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-little-sup-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=254913142268151278',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-living','standard','cmr07ii4800w6q8xdvvr4pf0x','The Living','## Top Reviews
> "Wonderful Stay – Highly Recommended!  I thoroughly enjoyed my month-long stay at this villa in Thailand. The staff were incredibly friendly, and any language barriers were easily managed using Google Translate or by speaking with Kittabrun, who speaks excellent English and was always happy to help.  I stayed in one of the bungalows with a private pool, which was a perfect size and ideal for relaxing. There’s also a shared full-length pool available if you fancy a proper swim – both pools were always clean and well maintained. The garden surrounding the bungalow was private, spacious, and secure – we even felt comfortable leaving items outside with no issues.  The groundsman and maids were fantastic – super friendly and very efficient. Any minor issues that popped up during the stay were quickly resolved without hassle.  I had read some reviews mentioning insects, but we had no real problems during our stay. In four weeks, we spotted just two insects inside and a few mosquitoes early on. As long as you avoid leaving doors open, you’ll be absolutely fine.  The complex itself has a very relaxed, peaceful vibe. Even in shared areas, it often felt like you had the place to yourself. The WiFi was strong and reliable throughout my stay, which made working remotely smooth and stress-free. Netflix was also available in the bungalow, perfect for unwinding in the evenings.  The location is great – just a 10-minute drive or a 30-minute walk to Chaweng Beach. Scooters are cheap and easy to rent, but if that’s not your thing, Grab taxis (like Uber) are available. I’d also recommend hopping on a local tuktuk from the main road – most places can be reached for just 100 baht per person, which is a real bargain.  A special mention goes to the cats living on the property – they became part of the experience. They’re no trouble at all unless you choose to befriend them with food!  Overall, the villa offers excellent value for money compared to similar properties on the island. I’m already looking forward to returning next year."
> **- W A (5/5/5)**

> "We spent 3 months here a nice time. There were 2 small "
> **- Michael W. (4/5/5)**

> "We had a great time at Living Pool Villa. Samui now everywhere is expensive but this place gives feeling of cozy, easy going and relax to stay. Room is very big surrounded with beautiful trees with the space to cook and eat or chill during the day. We stayed at Villa2 and feeling like stay at friend’s home. Owner, Krittibun with his team take care with proactive mindset with good service mind.  Closed to 7-11 it is very convenience"
> **- Phimmuuk Lohaakul Winborg (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-living-1.jpg','081 124 6026','80 Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/TheLivingPoolVillasKohSamui',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.784+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.784+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-living-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-living-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4955759657478426567',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-lodge-hotel','standard','cmr07ii4b00w7q8xdrd6ineeb','The Lodge Hotel','## Top Reviews
> "We were pleasantly surprised by this hotel! Despite the low price point during the busy season, it delivered in a big way.  Pros: Fantastic location near shops and restaurants. The room literally opens onto the sand. The staff is top-tier; they were very helpful with our luggage and airport transport. Great extras like beach gear and mosquito screens.  Cons: Our ground-floor room was close to the street, so it can be noisy at night.  Maintenance Note: The bathroom looks updated, but there was a significant water leak from the shower that flooded the floor.  Overall, it’s a wonderful spot if you want to be steps from the ocean, though I’d recommend an upper floor if you are sensitive to street noise."
> **- Shay Nissel (5/5/5)**

> "I am rating only food, service and beach. This beach is OK, there are more better beaches at Koh Samui, but for Fisherman village is a good spot couse you can find some shadow there if you wanna use beach during the day. We were not a hotel guests we just came for beach. They let us sit at the chairs on the beach couse sunbeds are only for hotel guests. Service I will rate only 1* couse no one came to ask what we want, I had to go and request the menu also after that I had to go to restaurant to order food and no one came to clean the table after and we were sitting there for hours. I had fried rice with beef, beef was very hard, not recommend this dish. I didn''t like the food much and I think it was quite pricy for Thailand to pay for fried rice which was not a good quality. I dont remember 100% but I think it was 280baht."
> **- Zuzana Zajacová (2/5/5)**

> "Our review relates exclusively to the communication and the handling of our cancellation.  We had booked a stay from March 5 to March 7 and contacted the property 19 days before arrival because we were unsure whether we would be able to travel.  We were informed that a refund would only be possible if we could provide documentation proving that we were unable to travel. At the same time, it was mentioned that the situation could be reviewed if the room were rebooked. Based on this, we cancelled the booking so the room could be listed again.  After our cancellation, it became clearly visible online that there was no longer any availability for the period from March 5 to March 7, which strongly suggested that the room had been booked again. Nevertheless, a refund was refused with reference to the original cancellation policy.  While this may formally comply with the booking terms, the way this situation was handled is very disappointing from our perspective. We cooperated and cancelled early so the room could be offered again, yet we are the only ones left with the financial disadvantage.  In a tourism-driven destination like this, we would have expected considerably more goodwill and fairness in dealing with guests in such a situation."
> **- Alan Berlin (1/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-lodge-hotel-1.jpg','077 425 337','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.lodgesamui.com/lodge-annex.php',NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.787+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.787+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-lodge-hotel-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-lodge-hotel-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=7301727462285624060',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-look-out-bar','standard','cmr07ii4d00w8q8xdsf9q3pup','The Look Out Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Very friendly Staff and an amazing view to the see, during enjoy your drink. The Look Out Bar is a part from Pavilion Samui Villas & Resort."
> **- Chris S. (5/5/5)**

> "Cannot comment on food but they have decent drink prices for a hotel especially beach front bar. Happy hour cocktails bogof 4.30-6.30 about 220 baht each. You can definitely find cheaper but not from what we saw with the setting and view this place has."
> **- Claire Guerri (4/5/5)**

> "Lovely service, awesome and good drinks. There is no better location. Good prices and music. Lovely place. The workers make the stay the best."
> **- Theo H.N (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-look-out-bar-1.jpg',NULL,'F28X+X94, Maret, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 8:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.789+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.789+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-look-out-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-look-out-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17310262133153419696',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-lounge','standard','cmr07ii4g00w9q8xdqylywy4j','The Lounge','## Top Reviews
> "Absolutely amazing experience at Trap House Samui!  From the moment we arrived, the team was incredible so welcoming, attentive, and genuinely friendly. You can really feel the positive energy and passion behind this place. The service was flawless and made us feel truly taken care of.  The food was outstanding: packed with flavor, beautifully presented, and perfectly prepared. Every dish we tried was a hit.  If you’re in Samui, this place is a must-visit. We’ll definitely be back highly, highly recommended!"
> **- Momentsoleil (5/5/5)**

> "This place has serious soul. The kind of spot you walk into and immediately feel the vibe — warm, genuine, no pretense. The Wray & Nephew speaks for itself — whoever is behind that bar truly respects the rum. And the rum punch? Dangerously good. The kind you’re still thinking about the next day. 🥃 Then the Jamaican patties arrive and suddenly you’re nowhere near Thailand anymore. Flaky, golden, packed with flavour — completely authentic and absolutely addictive. This isn’t just a restaurant, it’s a little piece of Jamaica dropped right into Samui. A total gem. Go. 🇯🇲🔥​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​"
> **- Ingrida Allen (5/5/5)**

> "Because it was off-season, we were alone all evening... a shame because this place is highly recommended! The food was fantastic, the view is amazing, and the staff is incredibly friendly! We chose this spot to avoid being surrounded by Instagrammers ;) Tip: the shuttle taxi is waiting down the hill, don''t go up by motorbike!"
> **- N. Nieboer (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-lounge-1.jpg','099 793 0232','5, Tambon Bo Put, Ko Samui District, District, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Smaui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 1:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.792+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.792+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-lounge-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-lounge-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=3286921897821163778',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-magic-house','standard','cmr07ii4i00waq8xdi9do55vm','The Magic House','## Top Reviews
> "Top 5 of the best (most calm and positively charged) stores I’ve been in (this includes visits in Sweden, Los Angeles, New Orleans, Greece, Germany, Czech Republic etc)  Genius combination of art, antiques and metaphysical items. A store to explore! (Don’t rush)  I did not try any of the sessions this time, but I hope to in the future."
> **- Linn Lindström (5/5/5)**

> "It''s a very good store with many varieties of stones. I like this store very much:)"
> **- Watchanun Tanacharoenwat (5/5/5)**

> "Stop by this special shop on Samui island. Whether you are buying a gift to bring home or you are looking for a creative way to spend the afternoon. The Magic House has brought true magic to the island of Samui. You can stop by and walk through the gallery of exceptional art pieces while picking up a beautiful crystal or two. I recently took an ink painting class with the owner instructing us. The class supplies you with what you need and you get to take home supplies as well as some new pieces of your own artwork. It’s definitely a spot to check out."
> **- jeannie garland (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-magic-house-1.jpg','061 753 9713','194, 1, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://themagichousesamui.com/','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 5:00 PM"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.794+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.794+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-magic-house-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-magic-house-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13129968755377382181',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-mud-coffee-and-eco','standard','cmr07ii4k00wbq8xd1sgffcnn','The Mud Coffee And Eco','## Top Reviews
> "On my way home from one of the best nights of my life. The location was wonderful with parking, beautiful view, and gorgeous interior. The staff was absolutely fantastic and so attentive. We had a few cocktails, starters, mains and affogatos. The best part of the night was the guitarist/singer who was beyond incredible and made me question if I should do my wedding here lol. I highly recommend this restaurant for couples or family!"
> **- Tiffanie Dumas (5/5/5)**

> "This review is for the restaurant only. The food itself was good. The experience was marred by a scowling, short and rude waiter. The position seems to have gone to HIS head. He clearly couldn’t care less about customer service or making a good impression. A group of 5 of us our dinner came out at all different times over the course of 20 minutes leaving some of completely finished before others had received any food. Meh. I wouldn’t return without trying others first."
> **- Jay (3/5/5)**

> "We only ate here, great location lovely food at a great price, the staff were warm and welcoming and went out there way for you. Great atmosphere and live music every night, was always busy. It was so good we went back for a second time."
> **- Timothy Greco (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-mud-coffee-and-eco-1.jpg','081 959 5155','57, Angthong, 1, Tambon Ang Thong, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100063479653715','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 9:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifxh0027q8xde6xqk8o6','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.796+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.796+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-mud-coffee-and-eco-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-mud-coffee-and-eco-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15766864991584677826',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-mud-eco-hotel','standard','cmr07ii4m00wcq8xd64crgcmu','The Mud Eco Hotel','## Top Reviews
> "Wow! This is the most beautiful resort i have ever been. The staff is amazing, everybody is insanely kind. The bed is soft, rooms are very big & so is the bathroom. The view is perfect, location is right at the beach, with a very clean swimming pool as well. Breakfast & diner is amazing, a lot of food to pick from & everything taste so good! I’ve had te best massage i’ve had in Thailand so far. It is perfect here, I don’t want to leave!"
> **- Sanne Van Gelder (5/5/5)**

> "What an amazing place! I only wish I could have stayed longer than one night.  The hut is spacious and beautifully designed inside. It has everything you could possibly need - and more - including grinding coffee machine, flippers, beach towels, a robe, a torch, a toothbrush, and more. The huts are very cozy, and the common areas are just as inviting.  The sea right in front is truly special, and the sunsets are absolutely stunning.  The staff are incredibly lovely.  One comment which would eco even more the place is having the complimentary water now plastic bottles in glass ones.  Otherwise, truly a wonderful experience! 🫶🌴🥥"
> **- Yael Fattal Lariccia (5/5/5)**

> "We came as a group of 10 for dinner (without staying at the hotel).  The food was fairly good - nothing particularly outstanding, but enjoyable overall.  Prices are on the higher side since it is part of a hotel compared to eating outside, though the atmosphere makes up for it.  The vibe was pleasant and relaxed, and the staff were friendly and welcoming, which added to the experience."
> **- Legally Hungry (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-mud-eco-hotel-1.jpg','081 959 5155','57, 1, Tambon Ang Thong, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifxh0027q8xde6xqk8o6','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.798+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.798+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-mud-eco-hotel-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-mud-eco-hotel-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12869324300795857686',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-mud-restaurant','standard','cmr07ii4o00wdq8xdfw9xl4m6','The Mud Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "On my way home from one of the best nights of my life. The location was wonderful with parking, beautiful view, and gorgeous interior. The staff was absolutely fantastic and so attentive. We had a few cocktails, starters, mains and affogatos. The best part of the night was the guitarist/singer who was beyond incredible and made me question if I should do my wedding here lol. I highly recommend this restaurant for couples or family!"
> **- Tiffanie Dumas (5/5/5)**

