> **- Malikeh Salimi (5/5/5)**

> "Amazing food and the owner is so kind and friendly! We came here twice for dinner during our 4 night stay. If you have a bigger group, I would recommend making a reservation just to be safe!"
> **- Alyssa Victoria (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sea-restaurant-1.jpg','087 472 4097','Mae Nam, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.tripadvisor.com/Restaurant_Review-g1182465-d7070856-Reviews-The_Fish_Restaurant_Mae_Nam-Mae_Nam_Ko_Samui_Surat_Thani_Province.html','["Monday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Tuesday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Wednesday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Thursday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Friday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Saturday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Sunday: 11:30 AM – 10:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifs1000cq8xdfo2aau32','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.863+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.863+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sea-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sea-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12442503574477806568',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-sea-view-bar-at-melati','standard','cmr07ii6h00x3q8xdcngb45z5','The Sea View Bar At Melati','## Top Reviews
> "The View Restaurant at Melati Beach Resort & Spa is known for its relaxing views overlooking Thongson Bay on Koh Samui Island in Thailand. While tasty, the food is a bit pricier than other places and may take quite a long time to arrive. Details below 🕵🏻‍♂️🥢  While the service staff is very friendly, sometimes takes the food takes forever to arrive.  Really turned our evening sour when we waited 54 minutes for our meal to be delivered finally around 9:50pm. Hungry, bored, and left with the hotel’s slow WiFi we almost left to order delivery from outside the hotel. Last call is at 10pm/22:00 so we weren’t even able to place an order for dessert even though we were still hungry from the small portion once we were finally able to eat…  The restaurant offers a mix of international and Thai cuisine, focusing on fresh seafood and local ingredients.  Guests can enjoy their meals in a stylish, open-air setting, perfect for taking in the decent sunset views, as the sun sets on a non visible side from where you sit here.  The restaurant also offers a selection of fine wines and cocktails to complement the dining experience.  Service available in English, Spanish and Thai.  Wheelchair accessible location and handicap friendly.  Some vegan options as well as menu options for children.  Parking included as hotel parking. Located on the opposite side of the entrance, right next to the beach.  Outdoor, roofed sitting only. No climate control besides a few fans here and there.  Some pest controls to help with mosquitoes, but sometimes not enough. Also some roaches roaming the deck at night. Flies during the day.  Beware the wind can blow items into your face, including some of the smaller menu sheets."
> **- R (3/5/5)**

> "Food was mid, some dishes were good some okay. Ordered 6 drinks total and only one of us finished a glass. One of the worst whiskey sours definitely, would not recommend"
> **- Igor Volhonski (2/5/5)**

> "Kinda monopolist on this beach(though can''t say its designed to accept guests from the beach) using it for the worst: highest prices, smallest portions(pay 4 to buy 2 to eat the default sized 1). Food is ok qualify ofc, but really nothing special. Waitress was tired of life itself. If you can walk, why not grant her rest..."
> **- m k (2/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sea-view-bar-at-melati-1.jpg',NULL,'H3PG+G55, Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.2,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.865+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.865+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sea-view-bar-at-melati-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sea-view-bar-at-melati-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8217434242311019223',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-seahorse-ferry','standard','cmr07ii6k00x4q8xdtc7oovzp','The Seahorse Ferry','## Top Reviews
> "I took the boat from bangkok to Ko Samui. I paid 3.5k. I regret. Overpriced food and drink. The staff are aloud to carry on drinking after 10.30 but not guests. I couldnt get breakfast at 10.30. Phone charger didint work in my room. No wifi.. There is also nothing to do on board. Pool table was covered up. Live music was alright. Also poor swrvice in restaurant. Just one girl seems to work hard there."
> **- Nomad chef (1/5/5)**

> "Lovely to have the route samui bangkok , yes still a bit of work to do especially on web as well as booking which is not easy at all .At board the rooms are very essentials and unless you take the suites there is no restroom bit at the end of the day is max 23 hours cruise . Dining on the upper deck is very romantic and nice and you have also the live music .Menu is just very basic and quality I would say so and so but price are not exaggerated even tho not cheap. Was worth to do it a d I would like to do again. Once they have improved the service ."
> **- Explorer X (4/5/5)**

> "Ok but need a much better website apart from the out of date information on Facebook"
> **- Mike McNamee (2/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-seahorse-ferry-1.jpg','085 842 6021','GWPM+GHQ, Koh Samui, Songserm, Thailand',NULL,NULL,3.9,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: Closed","Thursday: Closed","Friday: Closed","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM"]','cmr07ig1n003kq8xd72v6yb3r','cmr07ig1h003iq8xdb1g9nifo','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.868+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.868+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-seahorse-ferry-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-seahorse-ferry-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=469826250268938244',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-secret-brunch','standard','cmr07ii6m00x5q8xdjnepeeiv','The Secret Brunch','## Top Reviews
> "Wow!  With only 2 days left of our trip we found this place and are already wanting to come back!  I had the egg and cheese jalapeño bagel and it was incredible perfectly toasted with melty cheese and just the right spicy kick. The mango smoothie was fresh, thick, and bursting with tropical flavor, and the coffee was honestly fantastic!! rich, smooth, and expertly brewed.  Great vibes, amazing food, and some of the best coffee on the island. A must-visit brunch spot!"
> **- Jonny Harding (5/5/5)**

> "Managed to find a lovely coffee shop in Lamai, and I''m gradually working my way through their pastries and baked goods ... It''s a hard life, but someone has to do it! Not only is the coffee great - top marks for the latte art - but the entire Secret Brunch team here are friendly and super-efficient. There''s  always a lovely energy about this place every time I visit - pretty much every day for the past couple of weeks!  Worth mentioning too, that the facilities are spotless and the wi-fi is fast and reliable.  More importantly though, today was the turn of the cinnamon bun ... the verdict, 10 out of 10!"
> **- Simon (5/5/5)**

> "Great little brunch spot! We tried their energy balls — super tasty and perfect as a snack. They also have a nice selection of local Thai kombuchas, which we really enjoyed. Friendly service, great atmosphere, and overall a lovely place. Highly recommend!"
> **- Edvin Kibus (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-secret-brunch-1.jpg','063 617 4396','124/279 M.3 Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM","Sunday: 7:00 AM – 5:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.870+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.870+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-secret-brunch-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-secret-brunch-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9286875760793731439',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-shack-steakhouse-grill','standard','cmr07ii6o00x6q8xd20080jsr','The Shack Steakhouse Grill','## Top Reviews
> "We went to The Shack based on a recommendation from our resort, and it ended up being a great choice. My husband has somewhat pickier, more American/western tastes, while I tend to enjoy just about everything, and we both really enjoyed our meal here.  We both ordered steak. My husband had the Japanese Wagyu, and I had the Australian fillet. I paired mine with a Malbec, and he had a local beer. He also ordered two jumbo prawns. To start, they brought complimentary garlic bread, and at the end of the meal they treated us to limoncello as a dessert course, which was a very nice touch.  The steaks were excellent—high quality and cooked perfectly. We both chose the garlic mashed potatoes as our side. They were fine, though nothing particularly memorable.  The atmosphere was welcoming and relaxed. The staff were attentive, kind, and clearly worked well as a team. Even the manager stopped by to welcome us and brought over some homemade chimichurri sauce for us to try. We appreciated the American/western-style menu as a nice break from Thai food during our trip.  We also enjoyed the music and décor. They played American oldies throughout the evening, and the walls featured music and pop culture icons like Elvis and Marilyn Monroe. As John Coltrane fans, we especially appreciated seeing his poster. There was even a Beatles poster featuring the band in front of an American flag.  From the moment we arrived until we left, we felt genuinely welcomed. The manager, our server, and several other staff members greeted us and said goodbye. We were also offered warm rolled hand towels to clean our hands, another thoughtful touch.  The restaurant offers open-air dining right along the street near Fisherman’s Village. While there are no ocean views, it makes for excellent people-watching. Service was attentive, food arrived quickly, and everything we ordered was very good.  One tip: make reservations. They are busy, and you should not expect to walk in and get a table. We tried on our first night without a reservation and couldn’t get in. We made reservations the next day for that evening and had no problem getting seated.  We would definitely recommend The Shack and would happily return."
> **- Tierney Becton (5/5/5)**

> "10/10 food and service, the steaks were amazing and so were the sides and sauces. Although chimichurri sauce is an option, you get a complimentary jar of chimichurri for the table so I’d say try one of the other sauces. The garlic butter scallops were also delicious!!! Great wine selection and free limoncello shots to finish!! Friendly & courteous staff - we’ll definitely be back :)"
> **- Tia (5/5/5)**

> "This is my sixth time here—and I’m sure you can understand why. It’s truly worth it to dine here. The food has never disappointed me, not even once.  My favorite is the crab leg starter, followed by a main course of steak and lobster topped with cheese. I also absolutely love their homemade sauces—I wish I could take them home!  The staff are incredibly friendly and provide excellent service. And as always, I’ll definitely be coming back again."
> **- Rutcharin Panichtanunya (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-shack-steakhouse-grill-1.jpg','081 425 5710','88/3 Moo 1 Fisherman''s Village, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'http://theshackgrillsamui.com/','["Monday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 6:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.872+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.872+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-shack-steakhouse-grill-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-shack-steakhouse-grill-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17718068599723335444',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-shamrock-irish-pub','standard','cmr07ii6q00x7q8xdcrnx69o5','The Shamrock Irish Pub','## Top Reviews
> "Amazing musicians play here almost every night. The best! And for that reason alone, it''s a favorite bar on Lamai. The bland cocktails and the long queue for the pool table are secondary. The music is amazing!"
> **- Taisiya Lyubimova (5/5/5)**

> "Only went there for drinks, good music with a live band 6 nights/week starting at 9:30. The night off varied. Service generally good but obviously a bit slower on very busy nights, a trainee started the last night we were there so even this is being addressed. Happy hours between 3 and 9. Great place for a few drinks and a dance, we went there for both my and my wife''s birthday."
> **- Carl Greenall (5/5/5)**

> "No food. They have happy hour for cocktails at 99B. I ordered a Mojito and a Pina Colada, watery and tasteless. Left before the live band started and will not be back."
> **- Friendly Customer (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-shamrock-irish-pub-1.jpg','081 309 3395','Maret, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Tuesday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Wednesday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Thursday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Friday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Saturday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Sunday: 2:00 PM – 2:00 AM"]','cmr07ifx90024q8xdg1rcf50m','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.874+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.874+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-shamrock-irish-pub-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-shamrock-irish-pub-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=18068407170437862520',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-siam-restaurant','standard','cmr07ii6s00x8q8xd86jzbkzk','The Siam Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "I can only recommend this restaurant. The staff was amazingly kind and thoughtfull.. The rastaurant is beatiful, the food is amazing. You can choose food from different cuisines and everything was delicious! Been there several times and always liked coming back!❤️"
> **- Kristyna (5/5/5)**

> "Delicious Thai food! We ate here three nights it was that good. Staff are friendly and accommodating! Very nice atmosphere with the running water. A gem if you''re staying at Chaweng! Would return in a heartbeat"
> **- Nicola Davies (5/5/5)**

> "Such a pretty and calming atmosphere, Vietnamese fresh spring rolls with shrimp are the BEST here🙏🏼 🧘🏻‍♂️"
> **- Lilian Ulman (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-siam-restaurant-1.jpg','081 924 7029','Thaveeratpakde 87/2, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.876+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.876+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-siam-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-siam-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=3803990495985790434',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-source','standard','cmr07ii6v00x9q8xdkgncytvd','The Source','## Top Reviews
> "Prior to discovering The Source, I used to do detox programs on Koh samui using colemas and psyllium husk drinks. They were ok, but I find the Source detox program far superior  The Flow elimination formula is very powerful, so there''s no need for colemas. This makes the program very convenient and if you purchase Detox to go, it is easy to do it at home. However, the experience is much better if you do the whole program on Samui, having the benefit of the complementary activities like yoga, meditation, steam room,  heavenly Thai massages and unforgettable sessions with lovely Master Jet Lee, who will thoroughly reset every little bone in your body and brighten your mind. So far, I have done The Source detox four times, once on samui and three times Detox to go, and always find the program easy to complete, the juices help stave off hunger, and the clarity and energy increase every day as the body cleanses. Uniquely to this program, the results stay much longer, and sometimes the weight loss continues after the program as the body craves healthy, energising foods. Ivor is very knowledgeable, he provides support throughout the program, and answers every single question in great detail, with lots of helpful information. If you want to do something good for your body and mind, try this - you will be amazed."
> **- Jacqueline Manevska-Hamilton (5/5/5)**

> "My father was diagnosed with stage fourth laryngeal cancer last year, they said he wouldn''t live for more than six months. So we refused chemotherapy and opted for a natural cure. I emailed Ivor at that time and he responded immediately,  giving us very helpful guidance on how to change our diet and incorporate some of his herbal formulas. The lung and liver formulas helped improve my father''s lungs and liver, which the doctors said had metastasized. We had a liver flush and it also helped him feel better. He slept well and ate better, and after almost a year he''s still healthy and able to reintegrate into life. I am truly grateful to Ivor and his herbal formulas once again."
> **- mi meo (5/5/5)**

> "At first, I approached it with some distance—it was my first experience combining energy work and chiropractic treatment. During the session, I realized how much tension my body was holding, and I could feel my spine naturally realigning. Afterward, there was a clear sense of lightness, deep relaxation, and a noticeable change in posture—even though I thought everything was fine before. I truly recommend it—this is a real, tangible shift."
> **- Regina Bukowska Świat (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-source-1.jpg','089 067 9856','179, Beach, Thanon Had Lamai, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.thesourcesamui.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 6:00 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.879+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.879+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-source-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-source-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5268140120161568845',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-stay-chaweng-beach-resort','standard','cmr07ii6y00xaq8xd8atq7ro4','The Stay Chaweng Beach Resort','## Top Reviews
> "Great clean resort, centrally located, very nice staff. The pool is good to cool down. Beach is on the cover side. Breakfast is included and plenty. Room is neat, well appointed with comfy bed. Safe and fridge in the room. Complimentary drinks and snacks in the lobby, also scooter rental and tour offerings are available."
> **- Andrew Regos (5/5/5)**

> "Overall, the hotel was good and the value for money is definitely worth it. However, there were two things that felt very outdated and unreasonable for 2026: Guests are charged a penalty if they lose the room key card — which is quite unbelievable nowadays. Guests are also charged if a glass is broken in the room, which feels a bit excessive. In addition, there is no proper table on the balcony for drinks or glasses, so the chances of accidentally breaking something are actually quite high. Aside from these issues, the stay was good and the price was fair for what you get."
> **- Don Leibo (4/5/5)**

> "The rooms are very small. Do not expect you can see ocean from your room. If you need just a room for sleep yhe hotel is good. As I say the rooms are very small. Also the beachfront of the hotel is super small. You find there beach bags for sitting but no sunbeds for this is no space. The pool is long so you can nice swimming if you not want go in the stunning ocean. Breakfast is nothing special just basic. The location is central chaweng so if you love the chaweng beach and the nightlife perfect."
> **- Nicky Scarabello (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-stay-chaweng-beach-resort-1.jpg','077 415 200','162 5 ตำบล บ่อผุด Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.2,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.thestaysamui.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.882+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.882+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-stay-chaweng-beach-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-stay-chaweng-beach-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=2354063951499668288',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-stoned-table-samui','standard','cmr07ii7000xbq8xduwkf3z2z','The Stoned Table Samui','## Top Reviews
> "Authentic Thai Vibe, Amazing Food & Chill Atmosphere ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ If you''re looking for a genuine, laid-back local experience rather than a fancy restaurant, this is the place! The atmosphere is unbeatable – sitting on bean bags right by the water, just soaking in the island vibe. The food is high quality and delicious. While they offer great Western options (like pizza and burgers) for those who prefer them, I highly recommend trying their Thai dishes to get the real authentic taste – the flavors are just on point! Another huge plus is their flexibility: the menu states that any order can have vegan substitutions, which was great for us. The staff is super friendly and the portions are generous. Highly recommended for a perfect, chill meal!"
> **- gal tza (5/5/5)**

> "It''s very nice atmosphere. The staff was great. The food was ok. My crispy chicken burger was good but tuna salad was way too sweet for me. There will be a few dog walking around near the table with the bean bag seating which could be irritating for me. By the way, I had the table with chairs so no problem for me 😆"
> **- duangkamon thongmark (4/5/5)**

> "A nest in Koh Samui. A secret place. Between Nathon and Lamai, this little restaurant is well worth leaving the hustle and bustle of Lamai behind. Located right on the water, it offers a spectacular sunset. The simple yet elegant and thoughtfully designed decor invites you to relax and escape the hustle and bustle of everyday life. The food is delicious, prepared using family recipes. And everything is fresh. I highly recommend it."
> **- David En plus (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-stoned-table-samui-1.jpg','093 575 1808','76 Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07igdj008fq8xdhc2mye6x','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.884+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.884+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-stoned-table-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-stoned-table-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10004200111741179393',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-sunset-beach-resort','standard','cmr07ii7300xcq8xdhiglaltn','The Sunset Beach Resort','## Top Reviews
> "We had a lovely stay at this hotel. The staff are truly amazing — a special thank you to Joy, who made sure we were well taken care of throughout our stay. Her kindness and attentiveness made a big difference.  The location is fantastic! It’s far from the hustle and bustle, which makes it perfect for a relaxing getaway. I would definitely recommend renting a scooter, as there are plenty of great local restaurants nearby (some even within walking distance).  The rooms are spacious and clean, which we really appreciated."
> **- Honorata Janas (5/5/5)**

> "A true haven of peace. The hotel may be a bit dated, but it is very well maintained and spotlessly clean. The staff are exceptional, with a rare level of kindness. Located in a quieter area, away from the hustle and bustle of tourist hotspots, it is the perfect place to relax and experience Thailand in a different way."
> **- Cédric T (5/5/5)**

> "Beautiful sunset views in a quaint family owned resort. Our first impression was very good, they called us after our flight landed to ensure we found the shuttle and asked if we wanted anything from the kitchen as it was closing we would arrive. The breakfast had made-to-order eggs, fresh fruit, cereal, espresso coffee/cappuccino, and a variety of bread & croissants. There’s a few restaurants within walking distance. There’s good snorkeling off the beach & there’s a break in the coral right in front of the resort to allow for deeper swimming. The price is excellent for what you are getting. The location is on the quiet side of the island about 1 hour drive from the airport, however most boat tours to neighboring islands will pick up at this resort. Definitely go on the Red Baron to view the national park and take a Koh Tao tour for snorkeling. The staff is very friendly & helpful. The laundry service was nice and inexpensive. We loved that they packed a breakfast for us when we had an early flight for our departure.  Upon arriving there was a note on our bed that said the resort was doing a “soft opening”, which meant the spa was closed and the restaurant had limited menu. The toilet in the room has a glass door that limited privacy. No bidet. The rooms are not sound proof. We could hear some noise from the neighbors and street, but it was still very quiet."
> **- KB Brietzke (they them) (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-beach-resort-1.jpg','098 830 9940','126/9 Nara-Taling-Ngam Rd, Tambon Taling Ngam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.thesunsetbeachresort.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ift8000pq8xd7yujz20i','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.887+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.887+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-beach-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-beach-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17399510601757250973',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-sunset-beach-spa','standard','cmr07ii7500xdq8xdfu40tal4','The Sunset Beach Spa','## Top Reviews
> "We had a lovely stay at this hotel. The staff are truly amazing — a special thank you to Joy, who made sure we were well taken care of throughout our stay. Her kindness and attentiveness made a big difference.  The location is fantastic! It’s far from the hustle and bustle, which makes it perfect for a relaxing getaway. I would definitely recommend renting a scooter, as there are plenty of great local restaurants nearby (some even within walking distance).  The rooms are spacious and clean, which we really appreciated."
> **- Honorata Janas (5/5/5)**

> "A true haven of peace. The hotel may be a bit dated, but it is very well maintained and spotlessly clean. The staff are exceptional, with a rare level of kindness. Located in a quieter area, away from the hustle and bustle of tourist hotspots, it is the perfect place to relax and experience Thailand in a different way."
> **- Cédric T (5/5/5)**

> "Beautiful sunset views in a quaint family owned resort. Our first impression was very good, they called us after our flight landed to ensure we found the shuttle and asked if we wanted anything from the kitchen as it was closing we would arrive. The breakfast had made-to-order eggs, fresh fruit, cereal, espresso coffee/cappuccino, and a variety of bread & croissants. There’s a few restaurants within walking distance. There’s good snorkeling off the beach & there’s a break in the coral right in front of the resort to allow for deeper swimming. The price is excellent for what you are getting. The location is on the quiet side of the island about 1 hour drive from the airport, however most boat tours to neighboring islands will pick up at this resort. Definitely go on the Red Baron to view the national park and take a Koh Tao tour for snorkeling. The staff is very friendly & helpful. The laundry service was nice and inexpensive. We loved that they packed a breakfast for us when we had an early flight for our departure.  Upon arriving there was a note on our bed that said the resort was doing a “soft opening”, which meant the spa was closed and the restaurant had limited menu. The toilet in the room has a glass door that limited privacy. No bidet. The rooms are not sound proof. We could hear some noise from the neighbors and street, but it was still very quiet."
> **- KB Brietzke (they them) (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-beach-spa-1.jpg','098 830 9940','126/9 Nara-Taling-Ngam Rd, Tambon Taling Ngam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.thesunsetbeachresort.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ift8000pq8xd7yujz20i','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.889+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.889+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-beach-spa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-beach-spa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17399510601757250973',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-sunset-restaurant-bar','standard','cmr07ii7800xeq8xdod1htz0f','The Sunset Restaurant & Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Amazing little bar, with awesome view of the bay and the incoming planes just outside the entrance to the big Buddha island. We had chicken satay and chips with a wine and Leo beer, lovely. Would I stop by again, absolutely. We had seats facing the bay and some sun on our legs at 2pm, looks like, as per the name, it’s a great spot for sunset. Clean toilets."
> **- Adrian Everest (5/5/5)**

> "If you’re looking for a relaxing beachfront spot in Koh Samui with amazing sunset views, Sunset Cafe is a fantastic choice. 🌊 Atmosphere The cafe offers a peaceful, laid-back vibe right by the sea. The sunset views are absolutely stunning — perfect for couples, friends, or even solo travelers who want to unwind. The terrace seating creates a cozy and romantic setting in the evening. 🍽️ Food & Drinks The menu has a nice variety of Thai and international dishes. Everything is fresh, flavorful, and beautifully presented. Their seafood dishes are especially impressive, and the cocktails are refreshing — perfect for sunset time! 😊 Service The staff are friendly, welcoming, and attentive without being intrusive. Service is smooth and professional, making the whole experience even more enjoyable. 💰 Value for Money Prices are reasonable considering the beachfront location and overall quality. Definitely worth it for the experience.  ⸻  Overall: Sunset Cafe in Koh Samui is a wonderful place to enjoy delicious food, refreshing drinks, and one of the best sunset views on the island. I would absolutely visit"
> **- Andreea Costache (5/5/5)**

> "Literally, the best place to eat, work or vibe. The atmosphere and the jazzy music perfectly match with the quality food and service. The staff and owners are adorable. If I had to eat one last meal for my entire life it would be be their vol-au-vent or their salmon tartare ! Thank you the Sunset for existing and having the most beautiful view ever. 😝🙏🏻"
> **- Ines Iovino (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-restaurant-bar-1.jpg','061 249 0597','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.thesunsetsamui.com/','["Monday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: Closed","Sunday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig6y005pq8xd4jrvheih','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.892+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.892+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-restaurant-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-sunset-restaurant-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15723129422167187097',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-tent','standard','cmr07ii7a00xfq8xdjr2700en','The Tent','## Top Reviews
> "I cannot recommend highly enough! We had one of the most significant evenings of our lives there, as I proposed to my partner. The entire experience was simply perfect. I would especially like to highlight the incredible attention to detail and the excellent service provided by Kwan and her entire team. They went above and beyond to ensure our evening was unforgettable, even navigating some challenging weather conditions. Their warmth and professionalism truly made this moment perfect for us. The food was also outstanding and exceeded our expectations. If you are looking for a venue for a special occasion or simply a first-class culinary experience in a dreamy atmosphere, this is the place to be. A huge thank you to Kwan and the whole team for their dedication—you made this evening truly special! We will definitely be back."
> **- Merlin (5/5/5)**

> "A great restaurant right on the beach. I went there in June. It was very relaxed. The waitress, Ice, is very attentive, super friendly and lovely. The food was really very good. Even though the prices are a bit higher, it’s good value for money. I’d definitely recommend it."
> **- CHH (5/5/5)**

> "A wonderful first evening in this lovely restaurant. Delicious three course dinner, compliments to the chef, with a panoramic view on the Golf of Thailand. Our waitress Kung was a delight, super friendly, kind and helpful. It was a delight to be here and enjoy good food and good company. Happy to have met Kung, a perfect example of Thailand''s hospitalty. We will be back. ❤️"
> **- Leen Maegh (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-tent-1.jpg','077 905 888','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.salahospitality.com/samui-chaweng/eat-drink/the-tent-beachfront-restaurant-and-bar/','["Monday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 6:30 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.894+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.894+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-tent-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-tent-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17910854246348721681',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-terrace-restaurant','standard','cmr07ii7c00xgq8xdyp1hexzl','The Terrace Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Lots of food selections — everything fresh, well-prepared, and clean. They even offer a special à la carte menu with dishes you can order for free as part of the breakfast buffet!  Totally worth staying here just for the breakfast alone. The staff are attentive, cheerful, and provide fast, friendly service throughout. A truly satisfying start to the day!"
> **- Orange (5/5/5)**

> "The atmosphere at the restaurant this morning was wonderful. The breakfast selection was very diverse, and the service was excellent. We were looked after by Natty, who took great care of our table. Natty gave fantastic recommendations for both food and drinks and made our experience even better. We will definitely come back again if we have the chance."
> **- Oat KQTC (5/5/5)**

> "Gorgeous place, incredible food and amazingly friendly staff who really look after you. A little pricier but you pay for the experience and the view!"
> **- Beth Bidwell (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-terrace-restaurant-1.jpg','077 230 500','38/2 Moo 3, Borpud, Chaweng Beach, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Tuesday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Wednesday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Thursday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Friday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Saturday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM","Sunday: 6:30 AM – 10:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.896+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.896+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-terrace-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-terrace-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=9908827643297515374',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-thai-tapas','standard','cmr07ii7e00xhq8xdqo1nxk2r','The Thai Tapas','## Top Reviews
> "Absolutely amazing experience! The food was incredibly delicious, fresh, and beautifully presented with vibrant colors. The service was outstanding—friendly, attentive, and welcoming from start to finish. The owner was exceptionally generous and kind, making us feel truly valued as guests. Everything about this place exceeded our expectations. Highly recommended to anyone looking for great food, warm hospitality, and a memorable dining experience! We will definitely be back. 😊🍽️"
> **- nerya oren (5/5/5)**

> "I won’t exaggerate saying the best food I had in Thailand so far! Food was super I ordered lamb curry so delicious that it opened my appetite to eat tacos, which was also nice. Staff are very very friendly, the owner very nice he goes around tables with staff. Food came super quickly and hot fresh. Must give a try if you are in koh samui 😍 I give it 10/10"
> **- Zolatales By Walaa (5/5/5)**

> "The food was stunning and the staff were amazing. The restaurant itself is beautifully decorated and has such a relaxed, Greece vibe — a real contrast to the chaos of Thailand outside, which can be a welcomed step away for a brief time! Service was 10/10, and Nora really went out of her way to look after us and point us in the right direction for things to do. Would highly recommend!​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​​"
> **- Phoebe Simpson (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-thai-tapas-1.jpg','096 924 9636','29, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://web.facebook.com/The-Thai-Tapas-107753751923880','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: Closed","Wednesday: Closed","Thursday: 12:30 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 12:30 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:30 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 12:30 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.898+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.898+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-thai-tapas-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-thai-tapas-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15200586645552438158',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-view-restaurant-bar','standard','cmr07ii7g00xiq8xdlm7xsvm5','The View Restaurant & Bar','## Top Reviews
> "Daeng, Kikky and the whole team were amazing. This is by far one of the best experience we had in Thailand. The hotel was fantastic, the swimming pool and the view a dream. Thank you all for making our 10 days stay so wonderful."
> **- Aziza van der Hoek (5/5/5)**

> "Absolutely impeccable service, amazing food selection, reasonably priced, above and beyond Thai hospitality, and of course -- breathtaking view!  We stayed at the resort for two weeks and had dinner here on 3 separate occasions, each better than the last."
> **- Rob MacDonald (5/5/5)**

> "I had such an amazing time at the View kitchen & bar. Cocktails were amazing and food so delicious, so many choices for everyone. The staff is awesome. They are always smiling and willing to help you with anything. Nothing is a problem for them. Pin and Two miu have been really great and helpful throughout my stay at the hotel. Definitely recommend it, totally worth it. And the view from the restaurant is just stunning!!!"
> **- Mary Stamouli (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-view-restaurant-bar-1.jpg','081 137 9897','9/123-124, ตำบล แม่น้ำ อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://mantrasamui.com/dining/','["Monday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.900+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.900+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-view-restaurant-bar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-view-restaurant-bar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16310127494321869678',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-view-restaurant','standard','cmr07ii7j00xjq8xdahrjf0nt','The View Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Daeng, Kikky and the whole team were amazing. This is by far one of the best experience we had in Thailand. The hotel was fantastic, the swimming pool and the view a dream. Thank you all for making our 10 days stay so wonderful."
> **- Aziza van der Hoek (5/5/5)**

> "Absolutely impeccable service, amazing food selection, reasonably priced, above and beyond Thai hospitality, and of course -- breathtaking view!  We stayed at the resort for two weeks and had dinner here on 3 separate occasions, each better than the last."
> **- Rob MacDonald (5/5/5)**

> "I had such an amazing time at the View kitchen & bar. Cocktails were amazing and food so delicious, so many choices for everyone. The staff is awesome. They are always smiling and willing to help you with anything. Nothing is a problem for them. Pin and Two miu have been really great and helpful throughout my stay at the hotel. Definitely recommend it, totally worth it. And the view from the restaurant is just stunning!!!"
> **- Mary Stamouli (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-view-restaurant-1.jpg','081 137 9897','9/123-124, ตำบล แม่น้ำ อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://mantrasamui.com/dining/','["Monday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM","Sunday: 7:00 AM – 11:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.903+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.903+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-view-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-view-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16310127494321869678',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-villager','standard','cmr07ii7l00xkq8xdof8kajc4','The Villager','## Top Reviews
> "Excellent location. Few minutes walk from the beach, loads of shops and restaurants to cater for all the tastes. There is steet market which open ever other day. You will definitely need a beech towel, if you don''t have one can rent it from the hotel. Room are of decent size with basic facilties, two bottles of water, and tea and coffee provided every day. Nightly rate is reasonable for what the hotel offers. If you need or not like something, do approach the staff first. Found them to be very friendly, spoke good English, and kept the room clean. We also used the 24-hour laundry service without any issues. Overall, this hotel is fine for a short stay."
> **- Nadeem Khan.London (4/5/5)**

> "The villager is in a great location, close to the beach, night market, restaurants and stores. I was located in the purple building for my stay. The cleanliness of the room was questionable. Extremely run down, the furniture was super out dated, room was filled with mosquitos, bathroom was filled with drain flies, a few cockroaches and multiple ticks found throughout the room. The sheets had holes and stains, did not look clean. Majority of the staff were very kind and helpful. However, one staff member working at the front desk (a women, did not get her name), was extremely rude and passive aggressive. I asked for an extra bath towel as our shower had tiles missing from the shower floor. Which would leak onto the bathroom floor flooding the whole bathroom, everytime it was in use. After expressing this to the lady at the front desk I was felt like I was lying about the situation and it was diabolical I was asking for an extra towel. All good I’ll use the one from the filthy floor to dry myself.  Overall, Koh Samui is a beautiful destination to visit. The villager is in a great location, has a nice pool and majority of staff are great. However, it’s not very clean but I guess that’s what you get for going low budget."
> **- Emily Parisis (4/5/5)**

> "Amazing place to stay in Fisherman’s Village. Close to beach & walking street. Great value. Staff so helpful and friendly. Has everything you need for a lovely stay. Thank you :)"
> **- B Yung (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-villager-1.jpg','093 647 9185','Thanon Laan Thong Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.4,0,0,0,NULL,'http://thevillagersamui.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.905+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.905+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-villager-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-villager-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4276803660816218398',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-vintage-shop','standard','cmr07ii7n00xlq8xdkrr50ipu','The Vintage Shop','## Top Reviews
> "Good place to buy a nice clothing for appropriate price. A lot if good options for men. For myself found cool shorts"
> **- Анастасия Панфиленко (5/5/5)**

> "Call yourself a Lo Head? Or simply just a fan of Polo Ralph Lauren but happen to be on the island? This place is a must visit.  I''ve visited many a vintage store in my days, yet never have I witnessed such a well organised and niched selection. A large variety of polos, t shirts, long sleeves, rugbys, sweatshirts and button shirts in all sizes and colours.  Prices all hovering around at least market value, closer towards premium  - but some really nice bits in here and a good mix of modern era and true vintage Polo.  Some Polo denim, vintage Levis, Lacoste, Tommy Bahama and band shirts thrown in the mix also.  Dropped in on two separate occasions this week, both times the staff were super friendly and welcoming.  A dangerous place to visit if you happen to have plenty of space leftover in your suitcase!"
> **- Kal Leonard (5/5/5)**

> "Top quality shirts shorts everything original. Must watch when you in Samui Lamai great shopping experience"
> **- Andre Koch (Brandler) (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-vintage-shop-1.jpg','093 020 6560','124, 88, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://thevintageshopclothing.com/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 9:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifs5000eq8xdeu148200','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.907+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.907+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-vintage-shop-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-vintage-shop-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10853037179927942965',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-waterfront-boutique-hotel','standard','cmr07ii7p00xmq8xd8okhicp2','The Waterfront Boutique Hotel','## Top Reviews
> "The Waterfront Hotel was a lovely place to stay. The room was good value for money with a comfortable bed and spacious bathroom; it had a sea view and was located with easy access to both the pool and beach. The pool was superb with steps for easy  access and plenty of sun loungers  available for use. The staff were helpful and pleasant. The location was perfect for the restaurants and shops in Fisherman’s village - yet the hotel remained restful and relaxing. We will be returning."
> **- Caroline P (5/5/5)**

> "This hotel is PERFECT!! I loved it so much that I stayed in all day! The pool is very nice and clean and has places to seat. There is also a bar right next to the pool so it’s extremely nice. The room is clean and very comfortable and spacious. The bathroom and shower is also in very good condition and very clean. All of the workers are very very nice. So I recommend for everyone to come here!!! Also I celebrated my birthday here and they arranged my bed very pretty and nice for me so it was a very good experience!!❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️"
> **- Rachel Bell (5/5/5)**

> "As much as I wanted to love this little gem, very disappointed. Location is great within fisherman district. The beach front is gorgeous but unusable (dirty). The garden and the pool are the highlight of the place, beautiful! The rooms are old and smelly (sewer). Not dirty, everything is clean but the place needs major TLC, from the furniture to the plumbing. The front desk is sweet and helpful. She booked us a great driver for the day! Very communicative as well. Overall I think you could find much better for the price."
> **- Natalie Flournoy (2/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-waterfront-boutique-hotel-1.jpg','081 531 3409','71, 2, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,'https://thewaterfrontbophut.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifre0005q8xdxq1t2ih4','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.909+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.909+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-waterfront-boutique-hotel-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-waterfront-boutique-hotel-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13010079079136559362',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('the-wishing-tree-turkish-restaurant','standard','cmr07ii7r00xnq8xd07k53c3v','The Wishing Tree Turkish Restaurant','## Top Reviews
> "Everything was honestly perfect. The restaurant itself was great, the decoration was really nice and cozy, and the food was absolutely delicious. Every dish was full of flavor, fresh, and well presented — you could tell care was put into everything. The atmosphere made the whole experience even better.  overall, amazing place, amazing food — I’d definitely come back without hesitation."
> **- Mister Benz (5/5/5)**

> "Very tasteful food! The employees are so kind and very nice. Really recommend this place if you want to eat Turkish food. And don’t forget to drink Turkish tea🤩"
> **- Emma Björkman-Özgür (5/5/5)**

> "This place cannot become better! Everything from staff and their attention to details that make your stay a little bit extra special to the the team in the kitchen cooking the meat to perfection with spices that make you want to order more food by the first bite.  The owner is present and very good with the staff and guests, love the dedication to his craft and work.  If you come here with a group make sure to take the mix grill and have a relaxed dinner with the beautiful jazz playlist in the speakers and make sure to side order one pide.  Thanks to everyone in the staff!"
> **- Dan Darmetko (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-wishing-tree-turkish-restaurant-1.jpg',NULL,'31, 1, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrv000aq8xdn6zpp33d','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:13.911+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:13.911+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-wishing-tree-turkish-restaurant-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/the-wishing-tree-turkish-restaurant-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8072403368702877230',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('thicha-furniture','standard','cmr07ii7t00xoq8xd4tu50v02','Thicha Furniture','## Top Reviews
> "Permanently closed 🙄☹️Unfortunately, it didn''t survive, I think due to the catastrophic Covid-19 period."
> **- Claude G (1/5/5)**

