INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vibes-samui-hostel-cafe','standard','cmr07iiag00yuq8xdsy2nxm0m','Vibes Samui Hostel & Cafe','## Top Reviews
> "Perfect stay at this hostel. Great food, music playing. Free pool table and the workers are extremely kind and helpful. Would definitely recommend"
> **- D4nNyP4rK3r11 V2 (5/5/5)**

> "Stayed here twice, rooms are nice and beds are comfortable. Workers are all very lovely, and breakfast is always good, recommend!"
> **- Nicole Montgomery (5/5/5)**

> "Great hostel, cheeky pool table that’s really fun to play with your friends, food was cheap and really delicious! Would recommend to anyone in samui"
> **- Jacob Spencer (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vibes-samui-hostel-cafe-1.jpg','099 170 7223','G3RF+928, Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'https://vibessamuihostelandcafe.top/','["Monday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.008+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.008+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vibes-samui-hostel-cafe-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vibes-samui-hostel-cafe-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=12226259522162349115',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vibration','standard','cmr07iian00yvq8xdr29qouhs','Vibration','## Top Reviews
> "Vibration is an absolute gem and easily one of the best music bars on Koh Samui.  The attention to detail in the décor and overall finish of the venue is outstanding. Every corner of the bar has been thoughtfully designed, creating a stylish and immersive atmosphere that feels both intimate and inspiring.  The drinks menu is extensive, with a great selection to suit all tastes, and the prices are incredibly fair for the quality on offer.  The live musicians were exceptionally talented, and the sound quality was excellent — crystal clear and perfectly balanced, allowing you to truly appreciate the performances.  What really makes Vibration special is the ambience. It strikes the perfect balance between chilled, welcoming, and vibrant. Whether you''re there to relax with a cocktail or enjoy some top-quality live music, the atmosphere makes you feel instantly at home."
> **- Edward Mellor (5/5/5)**

> "A beautiful place with crazy, boundless jam sessions and an atmosphere of love and freedom. The home of live music 🎶 on the island 🏝️of Koh Samui! ✨🤍✨"
> **- STORMSON Music (5/5/5)**

> "Vibration Bar is one of those places you don’t really plan too much… you just end up there and it turns into a solid night. It’s not trying to be better than everywhere else, it just has its own thing going on and people seem to feel that.  The open mic and jam nights are probably the best part. It’s not polished or overthought, people just jump in, play, sometimes a bit rough, sometimes seriously good, and somehow it all works. You get proper moments where the whole place just locks in with whoever’s playing. Feels real, not like a show being put on.  The vibe’s easy as well. You can sit back and just watch, or end up chatting with random people, or somehow get pulled into the music without even planning it. No pressure, no weird energy.  Drinks are decent across the board, but yeah the coconut rum stood out for me. Kind of like Malibu but not as flat, got a bit more depth to it, slightly dangerous because you don’t really notice how fast you’re drinking it.  Overall just a really nice balance. Fits in with the rest of the scene but gives you something a bit more relaxed, a bit more honest. I had a great time there, definitely one of those spots I’d go back to without thinking twice."
> **- Luke Pol-in (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vibration-1.jpg',NULL,'14, 53, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/share/1N9yPU6wmv/','["Monday: Closed","Tuesday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Wednesday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Thursday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Friday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Saturday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07ifx90024q8xdg1rcf50m','cmr07ifrv000aq8xdn6zpp33d','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.015+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.015+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vibration-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vibration-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8933140740956387486',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vida-cleaning','standard','cmr07iiap00ywq8xdi374jo81','Vida Cleaning','Discover Vida Cleaning, a premier Property Services located in Bophut, Koh Samui. Find reviews, hours, and contact information.','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-cleaning-1.jpg','+66993106665','115, 26, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,0.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.vidacleaningservices.com/','["Monday: 6:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Tuesday: 6:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Wednesday: 6:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Thursday: 6:00 AM – 6:30 PM","Friday: 6:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Saturday: 6:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 6:00 AM – 6:00 PM"]','cmr07ifrn0007q8xdq29pgizw','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.017+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.017+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-cleaning-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-cleaning-2.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-cleaning-3.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10894426534574362624',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vida-mandala-art-samui','standard','cmr07iiar00yxq8xdwoylykfo','Vida Mandala Art Samui','## Top Reviews
> "A fantastic workshop. Vida was talented, brilliant, kind and lovely! My six year old LOVED the workshop too. A beautiful, relaxing way to spend the day. Thank you Vida. If we come back to Koh Samui we will come again!"
> **- Bee Bee (5/5/5)**

> "The workshop was absolutely fantastic! The atmosphere was welcoming and inspiring, and Vida was incredibly creative and patient. We learned the basics of dot painting and had fun to explore our creativity in the process. There was unlimited coffee and loads of smiles. We highly recommended to do this.  Also a great bonus is you get to keep the tools so you are able to use your newfound skill at home."
> **- Deborah Steinle (5/5/5)**

> "Today I attended a master class by Vida, and it was a truly beautiful experience. Vida is an amazing woman and a master of her craft — kind, attentive, and deeply caring. She explained everything with patience and supported us throughout the entire process. Her studio is very cozy and filled with a sense of calm, peace, and warmth. It was my first time drawing a mandala, and I’m amazed by the result. I absolutely loved the experience. Thank you from the bottom of my heart — I will definitely come back ☀️🫶"
> **- Selena Kim (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-mandala-art-samui-1.jpg','092 953 3552','11, 57 Soi Wat Naphalan, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://vidamandala.simplybook.asia/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Sunday: Closed"]','cmr07iftx000xq8xdn0s5qzbi','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.019+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.019+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-mandala-art-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vida-mandala-art-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5572662912646456551',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vikasa-life-cafe','standard','cmr07iiat00yyq8xdfqoqeec1','Vikasa Life Cafe','## Top Reviews
> "🩷🩷🩷 BEST vegetarian food with the MOST beautiful view 🌴 I honestly did not expect to fall in love with this place THIS much 😭  The burger… WOW. That patty was something absolutely unbelievable!!! One of the most delicious vegetarian burgers I’ve ever tried 🥹🔥  The Mexican box was incredible, the Arabic box was pure comfort and full of flavor, and the falafel… FINALLY 😭🧆 I found the BEST falafel in Koh Samui!!!  Everything tastes so fresh, flavorful and made with love. Sitting there with this dreamy view and eating food like this felt like pure happiness 🌿✨  Already one of my favorite places in Samui 🤍"
> **- Elvira (5/5/5)**

> "This place is a high-end retreat with a beautiful wooden restaurant area. Although the meals are quite pricey by island standards, I think they’re worth trying. We’ve been here three times because we’re looking for a calm atmosphere without the typical digital nomad crowd, if you know what I mean. For guests with dietary restrictions, they’re very on point, and for someone like me, it’s interesting to explore their creative vegan dishes. They also offer half-day yoga classes, which I’d love to try next time."
> **- Vina A.T. B (4/5/5)**

> "Vikasa Life Café is a fantastic place to visit, even when coming alone. I came here several times by myself after a yoga session, and it was always a great experience. It’s also perfect for brunch. While it’s quite pricey, the coffee is excellent and the food is truly amazing, fresh, and satisfying. The stunning view makes it an ideal spot to relax, unwind, and enjoy some quiet time, and the staff are very friendly and welcoming, which makes solo visits feel especially comfortable. A beautiful place for brunch, reflection, and great coffee — highly recommended."
> **- Marisa Jasmin Kastner (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vikasa-life-cafe-1.jpg','077 422 232','211 Bontji Moo 4, Koh Samui, Thailand, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Samui, Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://vikasa.com/life-cafe/','["Monday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Tuesday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Friday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Saturday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Sunday: 9:00 AM – 9:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.021+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.021+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vikasa-life-cafe-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vikasa-life-cafe-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=264016352202436095',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vikasa-yoga-retreat','standard','cmr07iiaw00yzq8xd3ge5efsi','Vikasa Yoga Retreat','## Top Reviews
> "Stunning location with top notch healthy food and service. Some of the best ocean views I’ve ever seen. It’s worth the trip to the island just to come here. Highly recommended for yoga but also relaxing. The spa was very good. Rooms are very comfortable with healthy snacks inside. The only downside are the stairs but using the buggy service really helps."
> **- P T (5/5/5)**

> "We stayed at Vikasa in Koh Samui for three nights, and without any doubt, it was a truly special experience. This place radiates a unique, deep, and authentic energy that you can feel from the very first moment.  The staff was always incredibly kind, welcoming, and helpful, making us feel at home at all times. The yoga teachers were outstanding: an exceptionally high level of professionalism, experience, and communication, with classes suitable for every level, from beginners to more advanced practitioners.  I had already been here two years ago for a longer stay and had a wonderful experience, but this year, together with Francesca, we truly fell in love with this place all over again. It managed to surprise us once more, exceeding even our best memories.  The location is simply perfect: beachfront, surrounded by nature, and at the same time strategically positioned to explore Koh Samui and the nearby islands. An ideal balance between practice, relaxation, and discovery.  We leave with deep joy and heartfelt gratitude for such an intense and rejuvenating experience. We will definitely return and can only highly recommend Vikasa to anyone who wishes to practice high-quality yoga and enjoy Koh Samui in a truly magical place.  Thank you from the heart ❤️  Renato & Francesca"
> **- Renato Rottmann (5/5/5)**

> "I came to Vikasa for the Recharge personal program in October. From the moment I arrived, the staff were welcoming, helpful, and went above and beyond to make sure my stay was everything I could have imagined. The program itself includes all the yoga classes on offer at the White Prana Sala, with the addition of daily private sessions to work through the Recharge program material. The content was just what I needed, and Kara was a beautifully wise and safe guide through it all. I was also supported by Eva, who made sure that I always felt comfortable at Vikasa and was there to answer any questions I might have. My prana cabana room was beautiful, the balcony looked over the beach and I spent hours just sitting outside listening to the birds, watching fireflies, and meditating to the sound of the waves. The food here is next level, so incredibly delicious, and the vegan ice cream is something I could (and did!) happily eat every day. Yes, there are a lot of stairs, but they are a great warmup for your practice, and the infinity pool is always there to cool off in. I often had the whole pool to myself, which was gorgeous. I would highly recommend a Vikasa personal program if you want to spend a week in a beautiful location, working on your practice and yourself. Thank you to everyone there for such a beautiful stay! Oh, and I can''t forget Sally''s massages, they were HEAVEN!"
> **- Felicity Lathrop (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vikasa-yoga-retreat-1.jpg','077 422 232','211 Bontji Moo 4, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.vikasa.com/','["Monday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Sunday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.024+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.024+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vikasa-yoga-retreat-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vikasa-yoga-retreat-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10398319622617657974',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('villa-anushka','standard','cmr07iiax00z0q8xd50wkawy3','Villa Anushka','## Top Reviews
> "Mind blowing experience at Villa Anushka!  The Villa has astonishing views from the infinite pool. Everything was always clean. The personnel is fantastic, friendly and take care of everything you can think about.  Looking forward to come back! This is the place to stay at Koh Samui.  Thanks for everything 🙏🙏"
> **- Jose Manuel Bermejo (5/5/5)**

> "We are a bunch of 12 friends who just spent 4 nights at Anushka and it was absolutely phenomenal. The view is unreal and the entire villa is just stunning! The staff here could not do enough for us and the food they served was delicious! We booked them to cook for us one evening and it was sooooo tasty. I highly, highly recommend staying here and hope to return one day"
> **- Louise Pierre (5/5/5)**

> "Superb! We stayed for 5 nights and it was one of the most refined and restorative stays we’ve experienced. The villa offers true understated luxury: absolute privacy, impeccable design, and a rare sense of calm from the very first moment, supported by an exceptional staff who are present when needed and invisible when not. Felt to me like a private residence. A place you leave feeling deeply rested and already wanting to return"
> **- Rebeca S. Barriuso (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-anushka-1.jpg','912 667 513','82, Ban Koh Faan, 53 Village No.3, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.villaanushkakohsamui.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ig5c0051q8xdykrbexft','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.025+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.025+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-anushka-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-anushka-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=18150912969572991395',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('villa-cima','standard','cmr07iiaz00z1q8xdloazzrsv','Villa CiMa','## Top Reviews
> "This villa is truly a hidden gem. The architecture is stunning, and every detail has been thoughtfully designed to create a luxurious yet welcoming atmosphere. The highlight, without a doubt, is the breathtaking view—every single room offers a stunning panoramic vista of the sea, allowing you to wake up to the sound and sight of the ocean every day. Location-wise, it is perfectly positioned. It is incredibly easy to reach from the airport, making it an ideal choice for families traveling with children or elderly members who prefer a stress-free journey. The villa provides the perfect blend of privacy, serenity, and comfort. It was the perfect setting for our special family time together. If you are looking for a beautiful, convenient, and unforgettable escape, I cannot recommend this place enough!"
> **- NATTASHA JANTABUT (5/5/5)**

> "A true sanctuary of peace and comfort. This stunning villa is a hidden gem, perfectly located just a 15-minute drive from Samui International Airport. The atmosphere is incredibly serene and inviting, making it an ideal escape for families or anyone looking to unwind. Every detail of the villa is thoughtfully designed to provide a relaxing and memorable stay. Highly recommended for those seeking a tranquil retreat in paradise..I will come back again 100%🤍"
> **- ปาณิศรา สงพราหมณ์ (5/5/5)**

> "Absolutely stunning villa! The rooms were spacious, clean, and beautifully designed. The villa was fully equipped with everything we needed, including complete kitchen facilities and household amenities, making it comfortable to stay in all day. The private pool was amazing, and the view was breathtaking, especially during sunrise. The atmosphere was peaceful and perfect for a relaxing getaway."
> **- Thanapon Wangkeaw (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-cima-1.jpg','098 404 7528','Bo Put, Ko Samui District, Surat Thani, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://brand.page/cima',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ig5c0051q8xdykrbexft','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.027+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.027+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-cima-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-cima-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10322932410258491880',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('villa-lunasole','standard','cmr07iib100z2q8xdaru70xpd','Villa LunaSole','## Top Reviews
> "Located in Bo Phut. 5mins walk to the beach and 10mins walk to fisherman’s village night market and the wharf. You can find coco tams there too. Maria was extremely friendly. Helped me out by booking the cab for us from the pier. Response was prompt. Helped us in booking a day tour to Koh tao and assisted in renting us a bike.Property is located inside a lane and was cosy. Although there’s no breakfast available, there are various places where you can eat here. Will definetly be coming back to stay at this place again. 🙂"
> **- anup thakur (5/5/5)**

> "A nice small hotel located just off the main road in a quiet area, walkable to the Fisherman’s village night market. The rooms were spacious and clean, small hob and microwave were provided if you want to cook in your room. The manager Maria and her 2 staff were on site most of the day and were frequently asking if every thing was OK. There is a small clean swimming pool and sunbeds with shade in a well kept garden area. All rooms have a decent size balcony. An added bonus was the on site washing machines with detergent supplied, this was free of charge.  I feel the  need to comment on a recent post that stated;  "
> **- Paul Campbell (5/5/5)**

> "Lovely spot. Rooms are all looking at the pool the pool is lovely treat partly shady areas to sit. My room had a kitchen not sure about the rest of the units but it had everything I needed and I was happy here. 10 minute walk to the beach several restaurants close by. Vegetable Fruit Stand at the main rd.  would be happy to spend a month here. Loved it"
> **- teresa lukianiec (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-lunasole-1.jpg','093 597 8727','No. 105, 146 Moo 1, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://lunasolesamui.com/',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.029+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.029+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-lunasole-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-lunasole-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=14688943376559339241',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('villa-tanamera','standard','cmr07iib300z3q8xdw64m82ou','Villa Tanamera','## Top Reviews
> "Why 4 stars?  Large ceramic pots of water used as decoration around the area, they attract mosquitos because they are filled with water.  The lady at the front desk room on the right was very nice. Keep in mind, there is no front desk at this hotel, walk in the front and knock on the door at the right. I asked her if a taxi in the morning at 6:45 is okay. She said she would call a taxi for me. The next morning, she did not answer her door, I was trying to turn in the key and get a taxi. I tried to knock a few times. But no worries, I left the key on the ledge next to her door and walked out the front and walked 20-30 meters to get a taxi.  The pool is a bit green, looks old, not sure if the water is green or if it’s the stained algae on the tiles. I saw people swimming, I did not swim, I was here for the beach.  The room are nice, old but nice. Mine was a deluxe villa. In October 2023 the price was 1800 baht on Agoda.  The room had bath and hand towels, also has beach towels. The room is a 2 bedroom villa with 2 full bathrooms and 3 air conditioners. The villa is the complete downstairs, there is a balcony downstairs and private patio upstairs with filthy old furniture. You can see the ocean from both balconies.  See my photos for additional comments."
> **- Doctor Kutchapeckeroff (4/5/5)**

> "Small Resort directly on the main street but nearby the beach and having a small swimming pool. If you need a quiet stay ask for the rooms nearby the beach. We took the cheapest room (street side) but surprisingly there wasn''t too much noise at night. Quiet large and comfortable room with good king-size bed, cabinet and chairs to sit and for the luggage. Also the small kitchen is well equipped (kettle, microwave, cups, dishes, cutlery, pans and more) all you need even if you want to cook.. Modern bathroom big enough and clean. Strong air conditioner, TV with plenty of channels and a small balcony, what do we need more ? 😂"
> **- P. Winter (5/5/5)**

> "Excellent value for what the place offered.  Oceanfront villa was spacious for our group of 4. Our unit was quiet, set back farther from the busy street and we enjoyed spending time sitting on the deck in the morning and during sunset. When the waters are calm, it’s nice take a quick swim in the ocean. The staff was very friendly with information and accommodating to our requests.  Highly recommend."
> **- Lil L (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-tanamera-1.jpg','062 303 3323','34/28, ตำบล บ่อผุด Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifrv000aq8xdn6zpp33d','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.031+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.031+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-tanamera-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-tanamera-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=17363712675983635730',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('villa-thimala','standard','cmr07iib500z4q8xd6kri8pak','Villa Thimala','## Top Reviews
> "Gr8 location, food and services on place."
> **- Sajmon Jumpinwood (5/5/5)**

> "Thimala Villa is a nice Place for a relaxing Stay at Koh Samui and is located at Bo Phud the north of Koh Samui."
> **- Chris S. (4/5/5)**

> "Very big and comfortable with a big swimming pool a few restaurant  around and a nice beach in the beach there are many corals with a kayak"
> **- Shang Wang (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-thimala-1.jpg','081 099 1839','17 2 Plail Laem Soi 5, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.thimalasamui.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifv2001aq8xdag7cvjgf','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.033+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.033+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-thimala-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/villa-thimala-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8025960540852659845',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('viper-room','standard','cmr07iib800z5q8xdmuu1wlk7','Viper Room','## Top Reviews
> "Best evening spot we found in two months on Samui. Great rock music, amazing hosts — Rob and his wife — and a cozy, welcoming vibe. We met so many interesting people here, and when we first arrived, the whole bar helped us find a place to stay and get our bearings. Truly a heartfelt place. Oh, and by the way — the local food here is absolutely delicious!"
> **- Olga Kovaleva (5/5/5)**

> "In short: An absolute gem for rock and metal lovers! 🤘  The Viper Room Rock Pub has an incredible community - we met so many amazing people, and the atmosphere is just fantastic. The possibility to request music makes it even more special, ensuring every visit is uniquely tailored to the guests.  Talking to the owner was another highlight - he is such a cool and friendly host. And he for sure truly understands the heart of rock and metal culture.  If you''re addicted to heavy riffs and electrifying vibes, this place is a must-visit!  We’ll definitely be back. Keep metal and rock alive and heavy! 🤘🔥"
> **- Tobias Schneider (5/5/5)**

> "If your a punk, metal, rock fan and have a passion for music Rob the owner is your man sat here playing music all night. Cheap drinks it’s lucky they close because I wouldn’t leave. UK travelers positive welcoming place"
> **- Jessie Mulhern (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/viper-room-1.jpg','081 728 5495','124/444, ตำบล มะเร็ต อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Tuesday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Wednesday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Thursday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Friday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Saturday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM","Sunday: 6:00 PM – 2:00 AM"]','cmr07ifx90024q8xdg1rcf50m','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.036+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.036+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/viper-room-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/viper-room-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=5221562274288116202',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('virtual-kitchens-miss-olive-oyl','standard','cmr07iibb00z6q8xdvyh3yjvc','Virtual Kitchens @ Miss Olive Oyl','## Top Reviews
> "Nice restaurant with nice setting. The Tom Yum was tasty and very nice, came with rice. My wife had the vegetarian tacos which she enjoyed.  Value is the only gripe, especially when you can get food for much better value at the same quality.  To be expected from a busy tourist hotel."
> **- Glenn Wilkinson (4/5/5)**

> "The staff is very nice. The foods and drinks are great to try 💖✨😚"
> **- Bunyawee Kusapan (MIA) (5/5/5)**

> "The best food we’ve had while travelling Thailand. Highly recommend the beef massaman and pad thai but so far everything we’ve tried has been amazing! Lovely staff and great views over the beach"
> **- Melanie Walker (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/virtual-kitchens-miss-olive-oyl-1.jpg','077 914 700','63 182 ตําบล Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.saiihotels.com/kohsamui-villas/dining/miss-olive-oyl/','["Monday: 7:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Tuesday: 7:00 – 10:30 AM, 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 7:00 – 10:30 AM, 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 7:00 – 10:30 AM, 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Friday: 7:00 – 10:30 AM, 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Saturday: 7:00 – 10:30 AM, 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Sunday: 7:00 – 10:30 AM, 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifsv000nq8xdrwnu123q','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.039+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.039+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/virtual-kitchens-miss-olive-oyl-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/virtual-kitchens-miss-olive-oyl-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=2318427151493034014',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('visit-natural-detox-resort','standard','cmr07iibd00z7q8xd9fbc8bif','Visit Natural Detox Resort','## Top Reviews
> "I rarely return to the same place twice — but VNDR was the exception. I came back this year with one of my now best friends, whom I actually met here during my stay last year. That probably says everything about the kind of place this is.  What makes VNDR so special is the sense of community. It is no surprise that so many people come back for a 2nd, 3rd, 4th or even 5th stay.  I also love their “You do you” approach. Whether you want to go all in with hiking, strength training, Muay Thai, breathwork, meditation, ice baths and activities, or prefer a slower pace, the programme genuinely works for everyone. No pressure, no judgment.  The staff are incredibly kind and truly make the stay special. Everything is very clean and well looked after. The rooms have everything you need.  And then there is Wild Tribe Café — honestly, some of the best food on Koh Samui in my opinion. Fresh, delicious, beautifully prepared and clearly made with a lot of care. The menu is so extensive that even after staying several weeks, you won’t get bored.  Bonus tip: the massage place directly opposite VNDR became one of the highlights of my stay too.  If you are looking for a place focused on community, wellbeing, movement and amazing food — this is it."
> **- Isabelle Hermes (5/5/5)**

> "Amazing retreat, I really enjoyed my time and would have loved to extend if I had the time. The staff is absolutely incredible. They made me feel like I was coming home from the first minute. The schedule is very diverse, something that really stood out to me compared to many other options. I really enjoyed the combination of morning hikes, yoga and strength training. The staff facilitating those sessions is very knowledgeable and delivered fantastic sessions. And finally the food was just amazing! Such a variety of healthy and delicious dishes. I can recommend it to everyone and hope to come back one day."
> **- Marina Illerhues (5/5/5)**

> "My time here was simply amazing! The program has a wide range of activities, from hikes, bike rides, yoga, full body workouts, breath-work, meditation to traditional Muay Thai. As a beginner the intensity was always fine tuned to my level and gradually challenges were introduced. The staff were so accommodating and helpful. The cleaners Ferry and Phon always smiling and wishing all a good morning, the reception staff always available and the Wild Tribe Café crew always caring and service minded. Special mentions go to the trainers Netta and Taylor. Both are good company, knowledgeable and very dedicated. More importantly both helped me achieve my fitness goals, always gently pushing me to the next level. This included Netta setting the tempo during my last hike up the mountain and in turn me breaking my personal record. Originally I booked for 4 weeks and I ended up staying 9 weeks… I believe that says it all! In short, I highly recommend!"
> **- Patrick Loftus (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/visit-natural-detox-resort-1.jpg','082 848 1909','129 3, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'https://visitnaturaldetoxresort.com/','["Monday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM","Tuesday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM","Wednesday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM","Thursday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM","Friday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM","Saturday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM","Sunday: 8:30 AM – 8:30 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.041+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.041+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/visit-natural-detox-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/visit-natural-detox-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10732954020889757909',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vitaxcell','standard','cmr07iibe00z8q8xdxdmn00jb','VitaXcell','## Top Reviews
> "I’ve had stem cell treatments in a number of places over the last ten years and honestly nowhere compares to Vitaxcell; the quality of treatments, the quality of care, the quality of fresh stem cells and the quality of the personnel. I don’t think you can find a better place for preparing your body for stem cells and for stem cells. Yes, it’s for the serious minded but this is not like going to the hospital. It was fun. Truthfully. Such a great environment and such nice staff. I actually looked forward to each treatment. That’s a first."
> **- Kevin Bird (5/5/5)**

> "I can not recommend Vitaxcell highly enough. From start to finish, the experience was nothing short of incredible. The entire team demonstrated professionalism and genuine care. What truly stood out was the family oriented approach they bring to their work. Ryan, Helena, Dr Ann and the incredible nurses are phenomenal friendly people that really do care about you and your health. They made me feel so valued and supported every step of the way. All my question were answered and addressed any concerns i had were addressed with patience and compassion. My results, absolutely life changing as i was a former professional athlete, golf professional and former boxer, i had a few niggles, (Rotator cuff minor tears, hip and knee issues) after iv and shock-wave treatments all issues have gone and its been over 3 months now and feel amazing and unstoppable. My ball striking in golf has improved with more club head speed, I swing in a flow state again and feel younger both mentally and physically.  Im back boxing and doing gym session pain free with strength and power increases due to the treatments. A New Lease of Life. If you are considering stem cell therapy plus other health treatments this is the company to trust. Their expertise, dedication, and heartfelt approach set them apart"
> **- Crusher Court (5/5/5)**

> "Both my husband and I had some Vitamin IVs here and a few other small treatments. The place is very comfortable and professional and the nurse is very experienced and speaks English. Highly recommend."
> **- RR Retreat (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vitaxcell-1.jpg','063 269 1219','37 59, ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.vitaxcell.co/',NULL,'cmr07ig1d003gq8xdfxkqj28w','cmr07ifv2001aq8xdag7cvjgf','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.042+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.042+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vitaxcell-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vitaxcell-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=16565612759827551172',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('viva-vacation-resort','standard','cmr07iibg00z9q8xd0sm2t4cv','Viva Vacation Resort','## Top Reviews
> "We enjoyed our 3-day stay with the family. The resort is very quiet, and the grounds are beautiful and well-maintained. A few lovely cats live on the property. The beach is calm and beautiful, with two great hammocks and enough sun loungers for guests. There is also a nice pool, a beach bar, and a restaurant. It’s a perfect spot for a peaceful, relaxing holiday. There are only 11 houses on the property, which adds to the private and quiet atmosphere. The staff are friendly, always smiling, and very welcoming. The villa was very spacious – we loved it. Bicycles are available free of charge. The closest 7/11 store is around 900 m away. You can order Grab food or use Grab for transport. Breakfast decent just takes some time as you have to fill the paper and wait for the main dish.  On the downside, the property is old. Although it is clean, the shower and bathtub were not working properly. Hot water also kept disappearing during our stay, which was a big issue when traveling with a baby. The staff came and solved the problem quickly, but unfortunately, it kept repeating in the evenings. I also had one beer at the bar, and it was the most expensive beer we encountered during our 1-month trip in Thailand. Still, despite these small issues, we enjoyed our stay. If you’re looking for a spacious place for quiet holidays, this is a good choice. It feels like real, authentic Thailand."
> **- Paulius Jakelis (5/5/5)**

> "The hotel and staff were amazing, room was absolutely massive…gardens well maintained. The only downside for me was location…being solo traveller it was a long walk to anywhere to get food or have a beer…and it was low season so many places had closed..a great stay for couples or families tho…"
> **- Stu just travelling (5/5/5)**

> "This place is located right next to the beach, offering a breathtaking and unforgettable sunset every evening. In the morning, the tide recedes and you can walk further out into the sea, while in the evening the water returns. Unfortunately, the sea here is not the most inviting for swimming.  I would hesitate to call this a true resort, but it is definitely a very nice place. It is well suited for families and couples looking for a peaceful holiday. However, if you are here to party, this might not be the best choice.  The rooms: In general, you get a spacious house with everything you need. The furnishings are a bit old and the property would benefit from a renovation.  The swimming pool: The pool is beautiful, large, clean, and well maintained, with a fantastic view of the sea.  Getting around: If you want to go into the city or anywhere else, you can easily book a taxi (via Grab or through reception). Bicycles are also available if you prefer to explore on your own.  The breakfast: Simple but sufficient.  The restaurant: The beachfront restaurant is fantastic. You can enjoy drinks, lunch, or dinner here. I highly recommend booking a table for a sunset dinner—it’s an amazing and memorable experience.  Although the property shows its age, it offers great value for money. The highlights are definitely the swimming pool and the stunning sunsets."
> **- Eskeatnaf Mulugeta (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/viva-vacation-resort-1.jpg','077 485 611','19/4 หมู่ที่ 3 Tambon Lipa Noi, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.vivavacationresort.com/','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifsb000gq8xdch1ib0om','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.044+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.044+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/viva-vacation-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/viva-vacation-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6739046124982894303',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('vows-villa','standard','cmr07iibj00zaq8xd7d7uer48','Vows Villa','## Top Reviews
> "I finished my trip in Koh Samui at this location and was pleased with everything! The rooms, food, and staff are amazing. Ask for “Jeeb” at the front desk and she will take very good care of you. Above and beyond service! She helped to make the trip even more special with accommodations and tips on what to do on the island. I can’t wait to come back!  The restaurant staff are terrific! Staff member’s “Sweet” , “Cream” , and “Sugar” have made me and my girlfriends mornings/nights. The food is great too!!"
> **- Justin Bernard (5/5/5)**

> "We had an amazing time at Vows villa. The panoramic suite has the most insane view and the room was everything we hopped for. The only negative point that comes to mind concerns the noise. It can gets very noisy as the rooms are closed to the road."
> **- Laetitia Gerard (4/5/5)**

> "RECOMMENDATION FOR VOWS VILLA:  ATTENTION TO DETAILS!!! From Treehouse , Silver Beach, Four Seasons. Our journey to Koh Samui ended at Vows Villas. One of the most beautiful places filled with so much thought into the making of this place. The architecture is amazing, built with old and new wood mixed with rough concrete put together with so much creativity. Surrounded by the beautiful landscape in the garden you will easily find time to relax by the calm pool overlooking the ocean. Hands down to the owner. 🙌🏼  - But not only that, the attention from the moment we arrived during our entire six day stay, was second to none. Our hostess Fah did the most amazing job and made sure that we had everything we needed. For someone like us who has been travelling a lot around the world, I must say this was one of the best stays we ever had. Amazing breakfast and even better coffee which everyone who has travelled in Thailand knows is hard to find. We also had the luxury of washing our clothes at the villa with no extra charge, free drinking water. It’s just an experience like nowhere else -  warm and welcoming it felt almost like a home with a great view and calmness that this place brings. 10 out of 10 🙌🏼"
> **- oliver worm (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vows-villa-1.jpg','063 073 0132','อ่างทอง 57/101 ถ. ทวีราษฎร์ภักดี Tambon Ang Thong, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifxh0027q8xde6xqk8o6','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.047+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.047+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vows-villa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/vows-villa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6212450317716479168',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-away-spa','standard','cmr07iibl00zbq8xdk67z4ukq','W Away Spa','## Top Reviews
> "My wife took some treatments here and was super happy. Luxurious spa rooms with high quality therapists."
> **- Raphael Maccagnan (5/5/5)**

> "We had a great experience at the Thaimazcal and a 30-minute massage"
> **- Martin Pelletier (5/5/5)**

> "Glory Ukraine"
> **- bent rasmussen (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-away-spa-1.jpg','077 915 999','4, Tambol Maenam, 1, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.marriott.com/en-us/hotels/usmwh-w-koh-samui/spa/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Sunday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.049+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.049+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-away-spa-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-away-spa-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=13108752060250368889',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-koh-samui','standard','cmr07iibm00zcq8xdbgmisrwq','W Koh Samui','## Top Reviews
> "⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐  Our stay at W Koh Samui was nothing short of incredible. The resort is absolutely stunning, with breathtaking views, beautiful villas, and world-class facilities. From the moment we arrived, we were made to feel incredibly welcome.  A huge thank you to Gift, Natty, Andre, and Tony for their exceptional hospitality and for always going above and beyond to make our stay unforgettable.  Special recognition also goes to Chef B, Chef Manoj, Chef Ragz, Chef Oat, and Chef Wat. The food throughout our stay was outstanding, and their talent, creativity, and attention to detail made every dining experience a highlight of our trip.  The service across every department was flawless, our accommodation was spacious, luxurious, and comfortable, and every aspect of our stay exceeded expectations.  Thank you all for making my sister''s and my stay so special and for creating memories that we will cherish forever. We cannot wait to return to this incredible resort."
> **- Taz Kaur (5/5/5)**

> "We had a week long, amazing stay at the W Koh Samui. Service levels are impeccable and “whatever, whenever” philosophy is evident throughout. We stayed at one of the beachside villas which I’d highly recommend if you are looking for quick access to a high quality beach with a private pool.  The W beach is standout with the ability to see both sunrise and sunset clearly. Given its on a small peninsula you can also get shelter from the wind regardless of which direction its blowing (predominantly was a mild easterly during our stay).  Food was excellent, and the breakfast buffet was the best Ive had. We also loved the Sip Bar on the beach - special thanks to Ting who works at the bar and was always friendly and up for a chat.  The layout of the resort is great, with a bit of elevation allowing for sweeping views from the restaurant and main resort pool. The onsite spa is of very high quality and has a large sauna which is free to use. I also think W is located well within Koh Samui - not too far away from the main tourist attractions (Fishermans Village just down the road).  If you are looking for a luxury escape to Koh Samui, I highly recommend the W!"
> **- Matt Wong (5/5/5)**

> "We stayed at the W Koh Samui from May 8–11 to celebrate my mother’s birthday, and the experience exceeded every expectation. Even before we arrived, the reservations team and management reached out with such warm and thoughtful emails, asking how they could personalize our stay. It immediately made us feel genuinely cared for. We traveled with our 5 month old baby, and the hotel went above and beyond by providing a bottle sterilizer, baby bath seat, crib, and baby amenities, details that made a huge difference for us as parents. For my mother’s birthday, they provided us with a complimentary birthday cake, which was a lovely touch. Everything was exceptional- The staff, the villa, the cleanliness, the restaurants, the beach, and especially the attention to detail throughout the entire stay. True five-star hospitality in every sense. We had an amazing time and already can’t wait to come back. Highly, highly recommended."
> **- gal elkaslasy (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-koh-samui-1.jpg','077 915 999','4, Tambol Maenam, 1, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.marriott.com/en-us/hotels/usmwh-w-koh-samui/overview/?scid=f2ae0541-1279-4f24-b197-a979c79310b0',NULL,'cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.050+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.050+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-koh-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-koh-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=4794720360258171853',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-namu','standard','cmr07iibo00zdq8xdtac25j9d','W Namu','## Top Reviews
> "After drinks at their beautifully situated Woobar (but with over loud, mind-numbing music), we were then taken by electric buggy to this delightful beachfront restaurant, where we sat at a table on the beach.  The Japanese menu had a good selection of sushi and sashimi and then some very interesting options for main courses. It was difficult to decide, but eventually we shared some smaller dishes:  * Edamame beans with sea salt * Selection of sashimi and nigiri * Thai spider roll: soft shell crab tempura, coriander chipotle mayo, pickle papaya  And then for main, we had:  * Andaman Sea Snapper: broccolini, dashi beurre blanc with ikura and avruga * Orange Miso Duck Breast: Home made tonkatsu, kinako and barley risotto, celeriac, nameko  Everything was excellent. The highlight for me was the soft shell crab - really superb. The fish and duck dishes were also really good and it was so lovely sitting on the beach, watching the sky change colours into dark.  The service from Pablo and his team was excellent and they presented my partner with a lovely little birthday cake.  A very nice evening BUT they had similar mind-numbing music as their Woobar playing far too loud. The view and atmosphere was so lovely and then wrecked by inane noise. They did turn it down when asked, which was nice—but really, should guests have to work this hard for a bit of relaxing ambience?  Restaurants and bars, please: look at your surroundings, look at your guests, and maybe—just maybe—pick music that reflects your special place, and doesn''t sound like a car alarm having an existential crisis!  (Also posted to my food blog on Instagram @AbbeyKing16)"
> **- Dave (5/5/5)**

> "The food was so so, decoration was a bit old and it was hot inside the restaurant. I had hamachi which was good only if they served it with deep fried seaweed (which was not served at first). Maki roll was tasteless."
> **- Nuch Suppanuch (3/5/5)**

> "I had a chance to try the Japanese restaurant here, and everything was absolutely delicious. I enjoyed every dish, both savory and dessert. The atmosphere is wonderful, with indoor tables, counter seats in front of the chef, and outdoor seating as well. The views are beautiful, and there’s also a nice sip bar and beach bar area. Overall, I really loved everything about this place."
> **- rapatr matinrat (4/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-namu-1.jpg','077 915 999','4, 1, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.5,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Tuesday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Wednesday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Thursday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Friday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Saturday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM","Sunday: 5:30 – 10:30 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.052+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.052+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-namu-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-namu-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=8173956154424054448',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-sip','standard','cmr07iibq00zeq8xd96dr2xc3','W Sip','## Top Reviews
> "We walked to W Beach and approached the bar to order one Chang beer. Before ordering, I asked for the price and was told it would be 270 baht for a small bottle. I stated that this price was excessive and unreasonable. The bartender reacted very rudely, became visibly annoyed, and almost shouted at me, telling me that if I didn’t like the price, I should leave. He then told us to bring our own drinks instead. This behavior was unprofessional and unacceptable."
> **- Deividas Gaudinskas (1/5/5)**

> "GO HERE AND WATCH THE SUNSET, truly it’s a hidden gem. So clean, vibey and amazing. Unlike the other places, it’s quite, the staff are amazing, the fairy lights are nice and intimate, the cocktails are amazing and the food is INCREDIBLE. there was a dj here some days and we literally spent hours here. Amazing"
> **- Kiara Borgonha (5/5/5)**

> "Netty. Was. Here. Actually I was the only person here the resort looks like it is struggling to fill the hotel rooms and tables in the restaurants.  I won’t discount the food it was delicious and very large portions; even for the salmon salad starter.  But 17% in service and VAT fees is 145 baht that made me feel ripped off, completely taken advantage of and therefore ruined my whole lunch. Pick one or the other; why charge both?"
> **- Netty (2/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-sip-1.jpg','077 915 999','4/1 Moo 1 Tambol, ตำบล แม่น้ำ Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,2.9,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.054+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.054+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-sip-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-sip-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15493051335047603982',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-the-kitchen-table','standard','cmr07iibs00zfq8xdkfuow57d','W The Kitchen Table','## Top Reviews
> "We had the privilege of experiencing Chef Bee’s exclusive tasting menu as part of Marriott Bonvoy Moments.  Every dish was carefully curated based on Chef’s hometown and history, carefully taste tested and executed perfectly.  Chef bee came out to explain to us each dish in detail; how the dish was created and how the flavours mix well together  One dish that particularly impressed us: Tom Khamin Hoi Shell involved an artistic display of using charcoal to heat up a tumeric soup in a coconut bowl. Curry leaves were also heated in the fire to create a symphony of scents alongside the beautifully presented dish.  The toddy palm ice cream is so unique, with Chef Bee explaining how they make use of their local toddy palm, scrap off the meat and squeeze the juices to get the flavor out. She even went to the kitchen to let us try the raw extract, further highlighting how personal the whole experience felt.  Best meal we ever had, even trumping the Michelin starred meal we had the day before. This menu will be available from Dec 2025 so don’t miss out!!"
> **- Jun Hao Kam (5/5/5)**

> "I went to W koh Samui with my family.The Chef Manoj made extra efforts to provide Indian meals for us:Best was Masala Tea,Dosa.He prepared grilled Salmon with grilled vegetables with Indian touch. All the staff members were very cordial and polite."
> **- nidhi rajotia (5/5/5)**

> "We ate breakfast here daily - which was truly the best breakfast buffet we have ever experienced. There’s something for everyone at any age - Savory, Sweet, eggs to order and more and more. We also loved having Lunch in this restaurant! Some dishes were stars that we remembered for the rest of the trip."
> **- Elaine Shur (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-the-kitchen-table-1.jpg','077 915 999','4 4, 1, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.3,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Friday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 12:00 – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.056+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.056+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-the-kitchen-table-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-the-kitchen-table-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=431524554369542688',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-weddings','standard','cmr07iic100zgq8xd0os8zdqf','W Weddings','## Top Reviews
> "Stephanie is an incredibly talented photographer and photo editor based on Koh Samui. From the moment we met her, she made us feel relaxed and comfortable, and she was an absolute pleasure to spend three hours with. She was amazing with our young children and truly brought out their best, which is no small feat!  We are in love with our photos and honestly finding it so hard to choose which ones to print large, frame, and put on our walls because they’re all beautiful. Stephanie is friendly, professional, and genuinely gifted at what she does. Absolutely book her — she is the best.  I found her on a Samui Facebook group. So glad I did.  Hope to see her again someday. We will return to Samui. We love it there."
> **- Nikohl Upton (5/5/5)**

> "Cannot recommend Stephanie enough. She is super nice, flexible and took amazing shots of my husband and I as a late wedding photoshoot and the edited final pics are jaw dropping."
> **- Hajnalka Major (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-weddings-1.jpg','097 361 7500','83, Maenam 3 Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.instagram.com/uniquemarriageproposals','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07iftc000rq8xdiyhsa78o','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.065+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.065+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-weddings-1.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=186102890422107245',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('w-woobar','standard','cmr07iica00zhq8xdope78lmk','W WooBar','## Top Reviews
> "We came to the W Hotel''s Woobar and Namu Restaurant for my partner''s birthday as they looked rather special.  We started, at the Woobar bar, up on the hillside, overlooking the sea - a wonderfully situated bar, with stunning views.  The cocktail menu had a good selection of classics and signatures. I tried a classic Margarita and one of their specials Thai Mai. Both very well done.  This was a really nice start to the evening apart from the atmosphere-wrecking music! Awful.  We absolutely hate this trend of taking a breathtaking setting—like the Woobar’s spectacular view—and drowning it in the same mind‑numbing, over‑amped beat for hours. Lucky us! We even had a DJ… though I’m not sure why, since absolutely nothing changed in the hour we were there. I thought a DJ''s was to match music to the atmosphere and audience. He was absolutely useless. The place was almost deserted. Maybe it was this awful, ambience-wrecking cocophony.  Restaurants and bars, please: look at your surroundings, look at your guests, and maybe—just maybe—pick music that reflects your special place, and doesn''t sound like a car alarm having an existential crisis.  We wouldn''t sit here again being assaulted by this terrible, mindless cocophony, despite the fabulous view."
> **- Dave (3/5/5)**

> "A gorgeous bar with a stunning view.  Fabulous great quality cocktails and the best service.  The bar itself and view from the rooftop are gorgeous a very cool venue.  Very empty which meant it lacked a bit of atmosphere but definitely worth a visit none the less it would he great for sunset."
> **- Jet_Set_Gypsea (4/5/5)**

> "A super beautiful bar that we visited one evening, and were able to enjoy a drink under an open starry sky. The bar is located on top of a small mountain, with a view of the sea. The staff was super super nice, and did a lot to make us feel welcome. We started with a seat close to the pool, but these seats were uncomfortable to say the least, as they consist of metal chairs without cushions. When one of the seats islands became available, we were fortunately offered this one. Our drink was one of the place''s signature drinks, and therefore we expected a lot. Unfortunately, we expected more than we got, because it didn''t taste very good, to say the least. When a drink has a high price, in my world there is also an expectation of a particularly good taste. And yes, it is probably a question of taste, but this experience did not give us the courage to spend more money, so we left the place again."
> **- M Brix (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-woobar-1.jpg','077 915 999','4/1 Moo 1 Tambol, ตำบล แม่น้ำ Koh Samui, สุราษฎร์ธานี 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Tuesday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Wednesday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Thursday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Friday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Saturday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM","Sunday: 12:00 PM – 12:00 AM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifte000sq8xdidrd81na','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.074+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.074+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-woobar-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/w-woobar-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10753361463080458279',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('waffle-king','standard','cmr07iicj00ziq8xdr7dhztfx','Waffle King','## Top Reviews
> "Great spot to grab your coffee, smoothie, and Waffles with ice cream… great prices. staff is very nice and welcoming.. highly recommend…"
> **- Orange Elephant (5/5/5)**

> "Really good and affordable waffles with friendly staff. Clean and tidy with a great location near the harbor.  Well worth a visit!"
> **- oscar Andén (5/5/5)**

> "An amazing hidden gem that not only offers good service but the most amazing homemade ice cream. The passion fruit ice cream is one of the best I’ve ever had. Highly recommended."
> **- Petronella Fourie (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/waffle-king-1.jpg','093 356 2315','247, Tambon Ang Thong, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.7,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig1h003iq8xdb1g9nifo','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.083+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.083+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/waffle-king-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/waffle-king-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15389251770569399028',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('wanngram','standard','cmr07iict00zjq8xdi1lodsiw','Wanngram','## Top Reviews
> "We visited Wanngram five times during our stay on Koh Samui and completely fell in love with this place. It’s truly something different from most restaurants on the island. The food is exceptional their duck with lychee sauce, caesar salad and the baked shellfish are absolutely phenomenal. Honestly, everything we tried was delicious and beautifully prepared.  On top of that, the service is very warm and friendly, which makes the whole experience even better. We will definitely come back next time we are on Koh Samui.♥️"
> **- Cukrfree (5/5/5)**

> "We had heard great things about Wanngram and were not disappointed! To begin, the location was easily reached with parking readily available. The atmosphere was relaxed, quiet and elevated casual.  Each dish ordered was divine. We ordered the lobster gnocchi, kingfish, steak and fish. Each dish had their own vibrate and deep individual flavours which were thoroughly enjoyable and unique. This excellence was replicated in the service which was consistent, timely, and attentive throughout. The price, although on the higher end, was very much reflective of the quality of ingredients and overall dishes.  By far one of the best restaurants we have been to in Koh Samui!"
> **- E Czar (5/5/5)**

> "A fine dining experience in a remarkable room.  Filled with object d art and vintage furniture, this place is laid-back cool.  Wanngram has an excellent wine list and very attentive staff.  Food presents as a mix of modern Thai and classic European. Wonderfully presented and delicious.  The lobster gnocchi and the seared scallops with Japanese sweet potato are outstanding.  Worth dressing up for!"
> **- Pete Thompson (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wanngram-1.jpg','081 142 3162','53 แม่น้ำ 5, Tambon Mae Nam, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84330, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.9,0,0,0,NULL,'https://www.facebook.com/wanngram/','["Monday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 10:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifs1000cq8xdfo2aau32','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.093+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.093+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wanngram-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wanngram-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=15078904783346374442',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('wanora-resort','standard','cmr07iid100zkq8xdnyhb4d7a','Wanora Resort','## Top Reviews
> "We stayed here for 6 nights and overall had a great experience. The lady there was really kind and provided good service.  However, there were quite a lot of rules mentioned in the rule book in the room, which felt a bit overwhelming. They also charge extra for cleaning and a few other things.  Additionally, the chimney in our cottage wasn’t working, but apart from that, everything else was good."
> **- Srijana Chhetri (4/5/5)**

> "The resort is located in a wonderful quiet location. The owner was very helpful to us. Very kind owners. Thank you!"
> **- Rudi O''Donoghue (5/5/5)**

> "Stayed here for 5 months and it was a great stay. The rooms block out sound from outside nicely, but all the rooms are basically long stay guests too so everyone is pretty respectful.  Large separate bedrooms (small 1 bedroom apartment style units) Lovely swimming pool, and a very kind owner! Thank you mak Orawan!!"
> **- Colten Sloan (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wanora-resort-1.jpg','077 900 066','16/66 Moo 6, Maret, Lamai, Koh Samui Tambon Maret, Lamai Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.101+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.101+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wanora-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wanora-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=10367014868903216671',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('wattanapat-hospital','standard','cmr07iidb00zlq8xdysa8v957','Wattanapat Hospital','## Top Reviews
> "My husband and I were involved in a very serious traffic accident with multiple injuries, and I spent the first two weeks in the intensive care unit.During one of the hardest times of my life, I experienced an incredible level of care, kindness, and humanity in this hospital that I will never forget.  The nurses and staff in the ICU were unbelievably kind, caring, and helpful. Whenever I needed anything, someone came within seconds. They washed and cared for me from head to toe every day, and they even braided my hair for me. Despite my condition, I was always treated with dignity and compassion.  The doctors checked on me daily and carefully monitored everything. Because my condition was very critical and my husband was extremely worried, Dr. Dear constantly updated him about my condition and always took the time to explain everything.  When I was transferred to the regular ward, I had the exact same positive experience. The nurses were incredibly attentive, loving, and always there whenever I needed help. Especially during situations that felt uncomfortable or embarrassing to me, such as being washed or having my diaper changed, they never made me feel ashamed. Instead, they always reassured me that it was completely normal and part of their job.  After several weeks in the hospital, I began struggling mentally and went through depressive phases. Whenever the nurses noticed me crying, some of them would sit with me for up to 30 minutes just to comfort me and cheer me up. That kind of compassion means more to me than words can describe.  The wound care team was also amazing. The man who cleaned my wounds every day was incredibly kind and made me feel completely comfortable. The nurses from the wound care department were equally gentle, professional, and caring.  One moment I will never forget was my birthday during my stay in the ICU. I was heartbroken that I had to spend it in a hospital bed, but Dr. Joy, the gynecologist, and the nurses still managed to make it a beautiful day for me. They brought me a cake and even a gift. I will always be grateful for that kindness.  There was also another doctor — unfortunately I cannot remember his name — who showed exceptional kindness. I had asked him why I had a heavy coating on my tongue even though I do not smoke and had barely eaten. He explained everything to me very patiently. I told him it would be enough if he simply told my husband where to buy the proper products. But the next morning, during his rounds, he personally brought me a mouthwash and a tongue scraper. I will never forget such a thoughtful gesture.  The rooms were also excellent: very large, modern, and always clean. A cleaning service came every day. We had our own bathroom, a kitchen, TV, WiFi, and even a couch so my husband could stay and sleep beside me. The view was beautiful as well.  I would never wish a hospital stay on anyone. But if someone ever needs medical care, I truly hope they receive the same level of treatment and compassion that I received here.  Thank you to the entire staff — doctors, nurses, cleaning staff, and everyone involved.You have my deepest respect. Despite all the pain and injuries, you made my stay as comfortable and positive as possible.Thank you from the bottom of my heart."
> **- Selin Baba (5/5/5)**

> "The doctors and staff are great, but the prices for medications are three times higher than at the nearby pharmacy. I don''t think it should be that way. There are a lot of staff at the reception desk in the hospital, but it’s not clear why so many are needed. Another downside is that they speak English very poorly, which is surprising for an international hospital. Even if you have an appointment scheduled for a specific time, there’s no need to rush. Doctors consistently run behind schedule, and waiting at least 30-45 minutes past your appointment time seems to be the norm. The hospital clearly lacks a dedicated manager who could help improve communication with international patients and ensure that doctors adhere more closely to their scheduled appointment times."
> **- Konstantin P (1/5/5)**

> "I gave birth to my baby girl here 🥰  The hospital is wonderful, with caring staff, professional doctors, and excellent service.  A special thank you to the entire team who was by our side during one of the most important moments of our lives. Your kindness, attention, and dedication meant so much to our family🙏  We are truly grateful and would highly recommend this hospital!"
> **- Daria Lugovaia (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wattanapat-hospital-1.jpg','077 965 889','555, 555 หมู่ที่ 1 ถ. ทวีราษฎร์ภักดี Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.0,0,0,0,NULL,'http://samuihospital.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ig1d003gq8xdfxkqj28w','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.111+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.111+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wattanapat-hospital-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wattanapat-hospital-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=2159137836249893649',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('wave-of-samui','standard','cmr07iidi00zmq8xd5853et6a','Wave Of Samui','## Top Reviews
> "Very spacious cafe. Lovely staff. Coffee is decent but there are better options around for the same price. My girlfriend really liked her matcha, which I think might be their specialty."
> **- Philip Smith (4/5/5)**

> "We came all the way from Chaweng specifically for the matcha, but unfortunately it was sold out. So we ordered something else instead, which turned out to be really delicious.  We came back the next day to finally try the matcha — but sadly, still no luck. On our third visit, we finally managed to get one — a strawberry matcha — which we enjoyed יחד with a croissant and some cake.  The cakes were absolutely amazing! Unfortunately, the matcha itself wasn’t really our taste. But just because we didn’t like it doesn’t mean it’s bad — it’s just not our thing. We’ve simply had better ones before.  That being said, the atmosphere is great and the service is excellent. Definitely still worth a visit!"
> **- Björn Wildung (4/5/5)**

> "We accidentally found this café while walking during sunset in Nathon. We were pleasantly surprised by this place — it has a very nice atmosphere. There’s air conditioning, everything is new, and the interior is pleasant.  The staff and the owner warmly welcome you. You can order any drink you like — there’s a wide selection of delicious coffee, including premium matcha, tea, various croissants, sweets, and cold beverages. They also offer crocodile jerky and beer.  Later, I came here several times to work on my laptop — it’s a comfortable place to get some work done."
> **- Dmitrii D (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wave-of-samui-1.jpg','065 193 6156','310 2, Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84140, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.8,0,0,0,NULL,'http://www.instagram.com/waveofsamui.cafe','["Monday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM","Tuesday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM","Wednesday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM","Thursday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM","Friday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM","Saturday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM","Sunday: 8:00 AM – 7:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ig1h003iq8xdb1g9nifo','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.118+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.118+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wave-of-samui-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wave-of-samui-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=11033359911060432327',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('we-care-cleaning-services','standard','cmr07iidl00znq8xdjpt1epiq','We Care Cleaning Services','## Top Reviews
> "I have been using the services of WeCare since two years, whether professionally or at home, for cleaning concrete outdoor floors at the Karcher, windows or indoor tile floors, as fabric armchairs and sofa. Their work is impeccable. Accordingly, I recommend this company."
> **- Benjamin CHAPLAIS (5/5/5)**

