INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('wellence-medical-clinic','standard','cmr07iie600zuq8xdy2goh3vm','Wellence Medical Clinic','## Top Reviews
> "I highly recommend this clinic. I’ve had both the CO2 laser treatment and the Salmon DNA treatment, and the entire experience was excellent from start to finish."
> **- Iryna desmarchelier (5/5/5)**

> "The clinic is exceptionally clean and well-maintained. The doctor demonstrates a high level of expertise, and the staff are consistently attentive and helpful. For anyone still considering, I highly recommend giving this clinic a try."
> **- D K (5/5/5)**

> "I visited here for Juvelook 3 times, and I received the best treatment from Dr. Jurusit. He kindly explained how the product works. After the treatment, I feel my skin has improved."
> **- TuNz Nirut (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wellence-medical-clinic-1.jpg','080 094 4551','119, 1, Tambon Bo Put, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,5.0,0,0,0,NULL,'https://wellencemedicalclinic.com/','["Monday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Tuesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Wednesday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Thursday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Friday: 10:00 AM – 8:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 6:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 6:00 PM"]','cmr07ifst000mq8xdudn7dwk1','cmr07ifqw0003q8xdu2hrq6e7','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.142+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.142+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wellence-medical-clinic-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/wellence-medical-clinic-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=1464148374727053084',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('whale-cafe-three-trees-resort','standard','cmr07iie900zvq8xdw5g03j82','Whale Cafe @ Three Trees Resort','## Top Reviews
> "Beautiful atmosphere, right by the water and aesthetic decor. I ordered to the fried rice with pineapple and chicken + a passion shake. The presentation of the meal was beautiful and the rice was quite tasty with good flavour, however I found the chicken to be a bit dry. The passion shake was incredibly, super refreshing and juicy to keep cool because there is no fan/air conditioning in the cafe. Overall I and a positive experience and would recommend."
> **- Emery Ellis (4/5/5)**

> "This restaurant exceeded my girlfriend and I expectations. First off as soon as we got to the restaurant’s lobby, smiles and greetings. Pulled chairs when we got to the table and towels on the lap to avoid a mess. Drinks were Happy Hour so 2 for 1 and tasted very good. Food was cheap money wise yet so good. I had the fish burger which was absolutely fenomenal and my girlfriend had a rice dish with pork, which she loved as well. The place is beautiful and kept clean. Big plus is i have a peanut allergy and it was taken care of very smoothly. All around a great restaurant. Very recommended."
> **- Tristan Genest (5/5/5)**

> "Great place with amazing food, excellent service, and a stunning view directly on the beach. Highly recommended. We loved coming here for lunch—try their combos, they are huge and delicious."
> **- AHMED.A (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/whale-cafe-three-trees-resort-1.jpg','083 789 6298','F22J+7Q2, 4169, Thesaban Nakhon Ko Samui, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.6,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,'["Monday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Tuesday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Wednesday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Thursday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Friday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Saturday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM","Sunday: 11:00 AM – 9:00 PM"]','cmr07ifpj0000q8xdet31f7qd','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.145+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.145+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/whale-cafe-three-trees-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/whale-cafe-three-trees-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=7367573058139165479',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('whispering-palms-suite','standard','cmr07iiec00zwq8xddu82lgfi','Whispering Palms Suite','## Top Reviews
> "Clean, well maintained condotel. Large apartment rooms of 1 or 2 bedrooms. Full kitchen, lounge diner, bedroom separated by sliding doors, bathroom with bath tub and shower, and a large balcony or terrace. Three buildings, each with 3 floors, set around two good sized swimming pools surrounded by palm trees. Short stay or long term rentals available. Free breakfast on short stays. Free wi-fi. Free shuttle in to Chaweng four times a day. Located a 5 minute drive from central Chaweng. Motorcycle rental. Car park. 24 hour security."
> **- Roger Bird (5/5/5)**

> "Upon arrival there was no clear indication of where we were supposed to go, the reception was along the pool side, down a narrow corridor, we had the drag 4 cases past a pool to check in.  The man in the reception advised it was 200THB per night for cleaning, this has to be paid even without the room being cleaned, this was very disappointing and put a negative spin on this accommodation from the start, the staff do not have a very good understanding of what is going on and their English is very poor meaning half the time I was unsure what was actually going on. There was no instructions of where the gym, sauna was or any info on breakfast.  Breakfast was terrible, one choice of cerial, some pineapple and watermelon, hard boiled egg, bread/toast and coffee, the breakfast is hosted in the front romm of one of the apartments.  The pool floor area is ok, but as soon as you are two steps away from that the tiles are very slippy, I fell and hurt myself whilst a cleaner seemed to walk past smiling as I lay in the floor!  There is 1 parasol for both pools, the main pool is ok, but there are very few sun loungers, the pool near reception looks like there is some kind of waterfall feature that doesn''t work and at one point looked like there was a water jet sitting area that no longer works  We has a big room that allows you to leave the electricity on whilst you are out and the air con can stay on too!  This place seems like a retirement home and is a good 5-10 walk from the main road where you can get a taxi, you can ask the staff to order a taxi but they often just look at you as they try to understand.  The veiw from the back balcony is attached to this review.  Gym is small but they have one that is a plus, there is a pool table in the gym too.  The man who wears orange top is helpful and carries the cases to the room, but apart from that, the staff are not very engaged with the guests"
> **- Danny Hands (2/5/5)**

> "Very private & peaceful, good surroundings. Highly Recomended. Fully equipped rooms and spacious. Strong WiFi and very helpful staff. Fully equipped Gym and 2 large pools and sauna ."
> **- Jasmeet Korr Mettapharuay (5/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/whispering-palms-suite-1.jpg','077 484 488','1/23, G2PV+GQ8 ตำบล บ่อผุด อำเภอเกาะสมุย สุราษฎร์ธานี 84320, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'https://dreamscapesdevelopment.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifuw0018q8xd0skvb1rt','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.148+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.148+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/whispering-palms-suite-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/whispering-palms-suite-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=2649768125278568413',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('white-sand-samui-resort','standard','cmr07iied00zxq8xdnqq3aawz','White Sand Samui Resort','## Top Reviews
> "This was our first time coming to Koh Samui and we were looking forward to starting our trip with a resort stay. Unfortunately White Sand Samui Resort did not hit the mark, how they are able to qualify themselves as a 4 star hotel is beyond us, they were 2 star with a pool.  Pro - On Lamai beach. Airport transfer went smoothly.  Con - All staff were inadequate and lacked basic customer service. There appeared to be no management on site, the front desk staff are not capable of dealing with anything. Rooms seemed run down and needed to be refreshed/renovated. Pool and beach did not have enough seating, other guests would “reserve” their sun lounges with their towels and then never use the lounges, there were numerous times we baked in the sun waiting for someone to remove their items because they decided they didn’t want to use the lounges in the end. Or we would be waiting for people to leave so we could swoop in. There were times it was just us 2 in the pool and no one else around yet every sun lounge had someone else’s towels? We never dined in the restaurant purely because our interactions with bar staff were dull and slow, the menu didn’t look appealing and we ate elsewhere. When we came back after dinner around 9pm we asked the Front Desk if we could have some drinks and we will take them to the room, we were told no that everyone had gone home. There were 2 people at the Front Desk, what is the issue with getting 2 beers from the fridge and charging it to our room? I’ve never stayed anywhere that has denied a sale. The hotel is showing signs of aging and neglect.  Neutral - this is at a quiet end of Lamai, if you wish to be somewhere quiet then it is perfect. Note it’s about a 20+ minute walk to get to Lamai centre itself where the markets and shops are.  We are returning to Koh Samui in May 2026, and we have chosen to stay somewhere else. I wouldn’t recommend this resort to anyone."
> **- Ebony Taylor (2/5/5)**

> "This is NOT 4*!! White Sands could and should be 4*. The location is beach facing, the pool areas are pleasant and the rooms are comfortable and well appointed. The issue seems to be that it is managed dreadfully and seems to focus on penny pinching rather than good customer service (not 4*). The reception staff are rude and unhelpful (the way they have been trained I guess). I have attached photos to demonstrate the state of the place etc. When we arrived (Friday evening) we were told that our room would not be available until the next day so they were ''upgrading'' us. We had booked the room 8 months ago and did not want to move rooms after unpacking. There was no management on site as ''it is the weekend''! Eventually after 30 minutes of phone calls we eventually sorted out a solution. This whole experience is not 4*. We were told they regularly overbook and then try and sort it out. There are two sets of steps to the beach. One is completely dilapidated and blocked off and one is a mess and pretty dangerous (not 4*). The sunbeds on the beach are very old and uncomfortable and no sunbeds have any cushions (not 4*). There are not enough sunbeds and yet the resort invites passing tourists to use the sunbed you have already paid for, for THB500 a day (not 4*). The towels in our room were old, frayed and dirty (not 4*). The quilt (duvet) was old and lumpy and took two changes to find one that wasn''t (not 4*). The restaurant furniture is very basic and uncomfortable flat hard wood (not 4*). Housekeeping had to ask permission to give us more tea and coffee as there was only one coffee each and one tea each in our room (not 4*). There is a list of fines on the wall for damage/loss of everything, including even the mattress (I have never seen this in a 4* hotel). There was a power outage by the power company for a whole day (these things happen), which meant breakfast ended an hour early, but apart from a small notice in reception, it was not communicated at all to the rooms (not 4*). The general attitude of the reception staff, the junior managers and even the general manager was the most unprofessional and non hospitality I have ever experienced. We have travelled for 2 months across Malaysia, Borneo and Thailand and this is the worst hotel we have stayed in. It needs some money spending and a complete management overhaul. The staff at the bar/restaurant were great and very customer focused (especially MrA)."
> **- martin walker (2/5/5)**

> "The good:  the staff are courteous, pool is beautiful and bed is comfortable. The breakfast is good with lots of options. Housekeeping service was good with fresh bottled water provided daily.  The not-so-good: we only had hot water two out of four nights. We were “upgraded” from a pool access room to beach front villa, but I don’t think this was an actual upgrade. The room just generally needs some care. Lots of little things needing repair such as the hole in the floor behind the tub, or the broken wood by the entry door lock. There was also a pit of garbage dug into the sand in front of the tree in front of our beach view. Loungers on the deck would have been nice. The air conditioner points directly at your face while in bed, even after adjusting it as much as we could, and it’s too hot to turn it off.  Overall not a bad stay… just needs some care throughout the property and rooms."
> **- Kim K (3/5/5)**','https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/white-sand-samui-resort-1.jpg','095 284 6999','124, F23R+V7R, 5 ตําบล, Tambon Maret, Amphoe Ko Samui, Chang Wat Surat Thani 84310, Thailand',NULL,NULL,4.1,0,0,0,NULL,'https://whitesandsamuiresort.com/','["Monday: Open 24 hours","Tuesday: Open 24 hours","Wednesday: Open 24 hours","Thursday: Open 24 hours","Friday: Open 24 hours","Saturday: Open 24 hours","Sunday: Open 24 hours"]','cmr07ifv6001cq8xd5vsyfm44','cmr07ifrp0008q8xde8dk7pdm','cmqyzwjmd0000iuxdbv41llnf','2026-06-30T05:29:14.149+00:00','2026-06-30T05:29:14.149+00:00','["https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/white-sand-samui-resort-1.jpg","https://pub-3433478e81804444ae052b8316ad0d83.r2.dev/images/businesses/white-sand-samui-resort-2.jpg"]','https://maps.google.com/?cid=6459144622647052808',NULL,NULL);
INSERT INTO "Listing" VALUES('white-sand-weddings','standard','cmr07iieg00zyq8xd3z62p965','White Sand Weddings','## Top Reviews
